(160, 'Erasable printing is here! ', 'We have taken delivery of some exciting new showroom machines in the form of Toshiba’s new printer that erases toner from regular copy paper - so you can re-use it up to 5 times!', '<p><span class="introduction">Some brand new devices have been delivered to the state-of-the-art showroom at Arena Group''s Armitage House. We''re pretty excited about this revolutionary new hardware from Toshiba that prints using erasable toner.</span></p>\r\n<p>We''ve been reading about the imminent launch of this new technology from Toshiba for quite some time. Now that we actually have the devices in our showroom, we have been testing them out and we are impressed!</p>\r\n<p>News of our new arrival has piqued the interest of our customer base too, with many keen to pop in and see the magical machines at work.</p>\r\n<h2>How does it work?</h2>\r\n<p>A multi-functional device (printer, copier and scanner) prints onto standard paper using special erasable ink which can be removed using an eraser unit. Toner is decolourised using a heated  friction technique, known as FriXion Ball, that renders the sheet of  paper usable again.</p>\r\n<p>A very faint impression of the cleared toner can still be  seen but Toshiba says that paper can be re-used upto 10 times*, resulting in reduced paper consumption and a greener way of working. Once the printer detects that a sheet can&rsquo;t be used anymore, it dispatches  it into a different tray but it''s still clean enough to use for handwritten notes.</p>\r\n<p>A compatible line of pens from Pilot use ink that the printer can delete, so writing on documents  you want to erase isn&rsquo;t an issue.</p>\r\n<p>Deleting documents is not always desirable in cases where important  information needs to be captured. Toshiba have addressed this concern by adding  scanner technology that can create an electronic copy of your documents  before they disappear.</p>\r\n<p>For now the device is only capable of printing blue toner, but we hear that additional colours are in development so eventually we could see a full colour machine.</p>\r\n<p>The obvious benefits of this new technology are reduced paper consumption and the associated reduction in environmental impact that stems from printing and copying. For organisations with targets related to minimised carbon emissions, these machines are certainly worth investigation.</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../case_studies/67">Case study: JN Bentley on reduced paper consumption.</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../web/contact_us" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information about these exciting new devices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>*Toner coverage determines the number of times a page can be re-used. The toner is not removed from the page but heated to a high temperature which turns it transparent, leaving a faint image on the paper. Once the toner on the paper becomes too thick for the machine to process it, the printer will reject the page. For this reason, pages with a fairly light coverage of toner will be processed more times than those with heavier coverage.</em></p>', '2013-12-20', 'PIC-e-ST306LP-RD30_S_web.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 707594, '2013-09-10 10:54:20', 'Eco-Print', '2013-09-09 12:25:09', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'erasable-printing-is-here'),
(161, 'Introducing mstore v4 ', 'mstore’s fresh new look and enriched functionality promise to enhance its standing as a market leader in the records management space.', '<p class="introduction">mstore&rsquo;s fresh new look and enriched functionality promise to enhance its standing as a market leader in the records management space.</p>\r\n<h2>Collaboration and determination produce an unbeatable software package</h2>\r\n<p>In consultation with a significant number of existing <strong>m</strong>store users, our experienced development team has, to date, committed over 170 man-years to the creation of <strong>&nbsp;</strong><a href="../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store v4</a>, the latest release of Arena''s electronic document and records management system (EDRMS). Account Manager, Paul Grant, a specialist in our EDRMS, comments;</p>\r\n<p class="indented">&ldquo;collaboration with our clients delivers enhancements to keep-up with legislative changes in our target markets. For example, we have recently added new functionality in response to rules relating to safeguarding and child protection in education. Because we are the software author, we can respond quickly to market trends and customer needs.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Prioritising simplicity, ease of use and accessibility - it''s web-based!</h2>\r\n<p>Customer feedback highlighted simplicity, ease of use and a modern look as development priorities for <strong>m</strong>store v4.&nbsp; This has resulted in an even more feature-rich application with a fresh new look and super-intuitive functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Not only this but <strong>m</strong>store v4 can be delivered as a web-based application that operates inside the most commonly used internet browsers &ndash; including Safari on Apple devices. This delivers several benefits for Arena and the customer, as explained by Paul;</p>\r\n<p class="indented">&ldquo;the web-based application can be deployed remotely &ndash; in an instant, providing the customer has access to an internet browser. Gone are the days of waiting for a technician to visit and install the program on multiple PCs. We can deploy the software onto private or public cloud-based infrastructure, allowing flexible deployment regardless of the customer&rsquo;s IT strategy. Updates are done remotely too, which means no disruption once the system is up and running.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Reflecting common changes to workplace practices, in particular remote working and the growing &lsquo;bring your own device&rsquo; (BYOD) trend, <strong>m</strong>store can now be accessed &lsquo;on the go&rsquo; from mobile devices such as tablets and phones. Paul notes that with the use of a Microsoft server platform there is potential to take <strong>m</strong>store to the cloud - "these are really exciting times".</p>\r\n<p>Paul adds that<strong> m</strong>store v4 also features a brand new API that allows simpler integration with existing applications;</p>\r\n<p class="indented">&ldquo;<strong>m</strong>store works with any software and systems that are already in place so, with the necessary permissions, a user can access any document on their network through one user-friendly <strong>m</strong>store interface, regardless of where those documents are stored.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>The compliance engine of choice within a growing number of market sectors.</h2>\r\n<p>Over the past two years, we have seen our client base for <strong>m</strong>store double, and demand is growing. This uplift follows the launch of our new packaged <strong>m</strong>store  solutions that meet commonly faced challenges unique to  specific sectors including education, credit unions and care providers. Paul explains;</p>\r\n<p class="indented">&ldquo;in all of these  sectors compliance is a priority concern for the majority of  organisations we meet. Legislation is ever-more complex but <strong>m</strong>store,  supported by the right policies and procedures, enables compliance with  the Data Protection and Freedom of Information Acts, for example. This  goes hand-in-hand with a host of other benefits such as freeing-up  office space, savings on document storage, reduced paper consumption, business continuity assurance, improved document security  and so on.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>We continue to develop relationships with existing blue chip clients, who use bespoke <strong>m</strong>store    systems to digitise and manage processes that were formerly  paper-led.  These include mailroom operations and delivery tracking for clients including Leeds  Building Society, Carnival Cruises, The  Card Factory and  Reed Boardall.</p>\r\n<h2>The document experts:</h2>\r\n<p><strong>m</strong>store is a vital element of the overall Arena Group portfolio, completing a full end-to-end document service. We are able to assess the way you work with documents in order to reduce costs and increase transparency in the area of print and copy, whilst also utilising <strong>m</strong>store to digitise paper-led processes. Paul comments;</p>\r\n<p class="indented">&ldquo;we have helped customers to change their employee behaviour in terms of print and copy, through implementing new policies and technology to track costs and manage colour usage for example. Our Managed Print Service takes the hassle and cost out of managing toner and maintenance on devices. When we look at digitising processes with <strong>m</strong>store too, we start to see serious cost savings and multiple other positive outcomes. We are dealing increasingly with customers who want us to scan their entire document archive and install <strong>m</strong>store so that, as far as possible, they can take paper out of the mix. This is particularly the case in education.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p><strong></strong><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store, software for document management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../case_studies?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">Case studies: <strong>m</strong>store in practice</a></p>', '2013-10-09', 'mstore4.png', 'image/png', 355417, '2013-09-10 10:37:02', '', '2013-09-10 10:25:26', '2015-05-06 10:52:57', 3, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'introducing-mstore-v4'),
(162, 'YCCC social media competition winner', 'We''ve been to Headingley to present our Social Media competition winner with her prize.', '<p><span class="introduction">Today we&rsquo;ve been at Yorkshire County Cricket Club to meet our social media competition winner. After the competition ended at the end of August, we drew our winner; <strong>Dorothy Betts </strong>from <strong>Sheffield Cricket Lovers Society. (@SCLoversSociety)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>With the initial prize a signed shirt and meeting an assortment of the YCCC players, Dorothy was delighted to find out that we managed to secure tickets and hospitality to watch the second day of the Yorkshire versus Middlesex match.</p>\r\n<p>With the weather just about holding up, we met a few players including <strong>Jonathan Bairstow </strong>and <strong>Ryan Sidebottom </strong>(pictured above) before play started and Dorothy and her 3 guests were able to enjoy the day&rsquo;s play.</p>\r\n<p>Details of the competition can be found here: <a href="../../../articles/143">http://www.arenagroup.net/articles/143</a></p>\r\n<p>We would like to extend our sincere gratitude to Yorkshire County Cricket Club for their continued support and generous prizes.</p>', '2013-09-17', '2013-09-17 09.25.47.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 147569, '2013-09-17 16:00:03', 'Dorothy meets the players', '2013-09-17 16:00:08', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'yccc-social-media-competition-winner'),
(163, 'Confidential files left on trains, in the wrong hands or just ... on the move?', 'Taking documents out of the workplace can be a risky business but sometimes you need to access them from afar. Find out how mstore version 4 can make your documents safer whilst keeping them accessible to those who need them. ', '<p class="introduction">Taking documents out of the workplace can be a risky business but sometimes you need to access them from afar. Find out how mstore version 4 can make your documents safer whilst keeping them accessible to those who need them.</p>\r\n<p>We''ve all heard the nightmare stories about files, discs or USB sticks accidentally left on trains, resulting in catastrphic data breaches and deep embarrasment to the organisations concerned. Legislation surrounding data protection is becoming ever-more strict, obliging both public and private sector organisations to be wary of the way they collect, store, manage and process personal data about their customers and other stakeholders.</p>\r\n<p>Arena''s new software for electronic document management, <a href="../161" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store v4</a>, has been developed with this in mind. The system can be delivered as a  web-based application that operates inside the most  commonly used  internet browsers &ndash; including Safari on Apple devices. This brings various benefits but, importantly, it means your documents never need to be downloaded onto a mobile device or external hard drive - they need never leave <strong>m</strong>store.</p>\r\n<p>Reflecting common changes to workplace practices, in particular  remote working and the growing &lsquo;bring your own device&rsquo; (BYOD) trend, <strong>m</strong>store  can now be accessed &lsquo;on the go&rsquo; from mobile devices such as tablets and  phones.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/161">What''s new in <strong>m</strong>store version 4?</a></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong><a href="../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store, software for document management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../case_studies?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">Case studies: <strong>m</strong>store in practice</a></p>', '2013-09-02', 'iStock_000020143380Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 414465, '2013-09-21 13:59:34', 'man with bag', '2013-09-21 13:59:37', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'confidential-files-left-on-trains-in-the-wrong-hands-or-just-on-the-move'),
(164, 'Arena Group becomes an Apprenticeship Ambassador', 'After winning Employer of the Year at this year''s Leeds Apprenticeship awards, Arena Group was a natural choice to become a Leeds Apprenticeship Ambassador.', '<p class="introduction">As winners of a Leeds Apprenticeship Award, Arena Group was a natural choice to become a Leeds Apprenticeship Ambassador.</p>\r\n<p>All businesses that won awards were approached to become an Ambassador in the hope that they could share their experience and expertise with other businesses, helping them to develop their own apprenticeship programmes.</p>\r\n<p>With Leeds City Council focussing on improving the employment and skills opportunities for local people, the aim of the Ambassadors is to increase the number of apprenticeships offered in the city.&nbsp; Arena has made a commitment to be pro-active in promoting apprenticeships within Leeds. Having agreed to host and participate in a number of events, Arena will also provide support and guidance to other businesses.</p>\r\n<p>Alongside their new status as an Apprenticeship Ambassador, Arena has recently achieved the <a href="../../../articles/165">Bronze Investors in People accreditation</a>. Having held the standard certification since 1997, this upgraded status shows how Arena continues to improve, recognising the impact that exceptional people can have on the business.</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s assessment had a particular focus on the introduction of Arena&rsquo;s new Leadership Competency Framework. The framework supports employee performance reviews and personal development plans, so the IiP review took a particular interest in ensuring that the initiative is understood in terms of both employee evaluation and progression.</p>\r\n<p>With an award winning Apprenticeship Scheme combined with continued efforts to ensure that leaders are best able to develop their teams, it is no surprise that apprentices continue to play an integral part in Arena&rsquo;s plans.</p>\r\n<p>Martin Wright, Arena&rsquo;s Group Human Resources Manager, commented; &ldquo;The additional Investors in People certification, alongside being appointed as Leeds Apprenticeship Ambassadors is excellent. With some of our management team made up of former apprentices, Arena fully appreciates the value in developing its people.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Councillor Lucinda Yeadon, Leeds City Council executive board member with responsibility for leisure and skills said; &ldquo;it is fantastic to have Arena Group as one of our Apprenticeship Ambassadors. Having businesses on board really helps us to promote the benefits and opportunities that apprentices can bring to a company.&rdquo;</p>', '2013-09-30', 'IMG_0094 edited.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 86705, '2013-10-16 10:57:34', '', '2013-09-25 09:10:09', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'arena-group-becomes-an-apprenticeship-ambassador'),
(165, 'Investment in People pays off for Arena Group with Bronze Accreditation', 'Having been Investors in People accredited since 1997, Arena Group is proud to have recently achieved the upgraded Bronze IIP certification.', '<p class="introduction">After maintaining the standard accreditation for several years, this upgraded status shows how Arena continues to improve, recognising the impact that exceptional people can have on the business.</p>\r\n<p>The assessments were done entirely in the form of interviews; these were held in August this year with a cross section of Arena employees.</p>\r\n<p>With a particular focus on the introduction of a new Leadership Competency Framework, those interviewed included leaders and managers. The framework supports employee performance reviews and personal development plans; the IIP review took an interest in ensuring that the initiative is understood in terms of both employee evaluation and progression.</p>\r\n<p>The IiP framework states; &ldquo;becoming an Investors in People organisation is a tremendous achievement. It demonstrates a commitment to the development and success of your people and a desire to continually improve and grow.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s Group Human Resources Manager, Martin Wright, commented; &ldquo;To not only retain our Investors in People certification but to also be awarded the additional Bronze accreditation is excellent. This reflects Arena Group&rsquo;s commitment to its staff, and their development&rdquo;.</p>', '2013-09-30', 'IMG_0097.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 115411, '2013-10-16 14:26:53', '', '2013-09-25 09:12:16', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'investment-in-people-pays-off-for-arena-group-with-bronze-accreditation'),
(166, 'Steps towards the less paper dream', 'Understanding how to make our businesses more sustainable, more productive and more efficient is a challenge many of us face. Neil Maude shares some simple steps towards reducing your reliance on paper.', '<p class="introduction">Reducing your reliance on paper is not  an overnight transition but there are some simple steps that will get you started in the right direction.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.aiim.org/" target="_blank">AIIM sponsored World Paper Free Day</a> takes place in October - an event that champions digital processes and efficiency in the workplace. With this in mind, we thought we would bring together some simple steps that a business can take towards reducing its reliance on paper.</p>\r\n<h2>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Planning is the first step</h2>\r\n<p>It is possible to reduce paper usage in any organisation, large or small, and   improve your business processes at the same time   &ndash; but only if you   have a clear plan. Take a close look at your business and how paper is used to see where you can pick "low hanging fruit" and achieve the quickest wins.</p>\r\n<p>In an organisation''s effort to reduce paper, often processes are  digitised one at a time or in phases that focus on departments in turn. For example, you might choose to start with <a href="../../case_studies/26?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">accounts payable</a>, <a href="../../../case_studies/36?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">sales order processing</a>, <a href="../../../articles/110" target="_blank">purchase-to-pay</a>, <a href="../../case_studies/35?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">invoices</a> or your <a href="../../case_studies/25?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">mailroom</a>.</p>\r\n<div id="stcpDiv" style="position: absolute; top: -1999px; left: -1988px;">AIIM  research looks at how less paper in the workplace delivers significant  benefits.  - See more at:  http://www.aiim.org/events/paper-free-day#sthash.G8H80BPA.dpuf</div>\r\n<h2>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be pragmatic</h2>\r\n<p>Paper remains the best tool for some jobs and sometimes a piece of paper is the  best way to capture and/or share information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are many systems and complimentary technologies on the market that can capture and digitise data  from paper. This means you don''t need to keep hard copy documents and you can enjoy the benefits of electronic document management such as improved security and quick retrieval.</p>\r\n<h2>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tackle your over-flowing recycling bins</h2>\r\n<p>A review of your print and copy strategy may unlock significant savings. Addressing wasteful and unnecessary printing can seriously reduce your paper consumption. <a href="../../../articles/112" target="_blank">Read our guide on print control.</a></p>\r\n<h2>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Get employees involved early</h2>\r\n<p>A senior management sponsor is a really important first step towards a less paper office, and sharing a vision across the business will generate support. End users who will champion your initiative can also make a big difference.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Security: the flip side to accessibility</h2>\r\n<p>If you are implementing an electronic document and records management system (EDRMS), remember that electronic data  can be lost or stolen in vast amounts.&nbsp; Build in appropriate security from the start, choosing an EDRMS with functionality for user logins, activity auditing and other security features as necessary.</p>\r\n<h3><br />About Neil Maude</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../assets/articles/113/contained_images/8d9e8419f6d7_180_NeilM_ws.jpg?1359557446" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Electronic Document Management General Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:neilM@arenagroup.net">neilM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Neil joined the Arena Group in 2006 and has almost 20 years of  experience in the electronic document management industry, working with  both private and public sector customers.&nbsp; Neil sits on Arena&rsquo;s board of  directors and manages the delivery operations of Arena&rsquo;s EDM business.&nbsp;  His team spend their time developing software, implementing solutions  for customers and providing after-sales software support services, both  in the UK and internationally.</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store - electronic document management </a>(EDRMS)</li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/112" target="_blank">Reducing wasteful and unnecessary printing</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../110?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../articles/110" target="_blank">Taking the paper out of the purchase-to-pay process</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../case_studies" target="_blank">Case studies: Efficient document management</a></li>\r\n</ul>', '2015-08-31', 'Computerpaper.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 29920, '2013-10-23 16:04:49', 'WPFD', '2013-10-22 14:12:58', '2015-09-07 09:25:29', 3, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'steps-towards-the-less-paper-dream'),
(171, '7 Small Steps Towards Big Savings in the Housing Sector', 'In today’s tough market, housing associations must focus on the efficiencies that they can influence to deliver cost savings. Gaining control of print and copy has been proven to create serious financial savings whilst cutting waste and reducing your carbon footprint. Arena''s Sean McGuigan outlines 7 simple steps that can lead to significant savings.', '<p class="introduction">In today&rsquo;s tough market, housing associations must focus on the efficiencies that they can influence to deliver cost savings. Gaining control of print and copy has been proven to create serious financial savings whilst cutting waste and reducing your carbon footprint. Arena''s Sean McGuigan outlines 7 simple steps that can lead to significant savings.</p>\r\n<h2>Review your strategy</h2>\r\n<p>A print and copy strategy with guidelines for staff to follow can be hugely beneficial. From preventing sensitive documents from being left on a printer to enforcing defaults that restrict colour or single-sided printing, a considered approach can deliver multiple benefits. Conscious efforts to change wasteful practices will also nurture a more considerate workforce and lead to greener behaviour.</p>\r\n<p>Julie Greenland, ICT Project Manager of Liverpool Mutual Homes comments; <em class="font_blue">&ldquo;we are seeing a change in behaviour as our staff become more aware of what they are printing. Previously many of them simply didn&rsquo;t know how to change the settings so automating everything has really helped.&rdquo;</em> These new behaviours have had a dramatic effect on print and copy costs; <span class="font_blue">&ldquo;</span><em class="font_blue">We have reduced paper consumption by 40% and our colour usage has reduced from 75% to around 25%.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<h2>Print audit</h2>\r\n<p>Whether your contract is close to expiring or not, a print audit is a worthwhile undertaking. In fact, if your print and copy contract is within six months of expiry then we would strongly recommend an audit. This will help you to specify the best solution for your needs when the time comes.</p>\r\n<p>The audit involves placing some software on your network that will track print and copy output and activity. Installing the software takes a matter of minutes and then it works away in the background &ndash; you won&rsquo;t even notice it&rsquo;s there. After a period of around one month, your print audit provider will present the findings to you. They will suggest any changes you could make to your infrastructure to reduce costs and wasteful activity. Arena offers this service without obligation and free of charge.</p>\r\n<p>Giving yourself at least a month to work through this simple process will clarify your print and copy situation and costs, giving you a baseline to work on improving.</p>\r\n<h2>Managed Print Service (MPS)</h2>\r\n<p>A Managed Print Service always begins with a print audit before proposing areas for improvement. The solution often involves a change to the number, type and position of devices you currently use, placing the ideal number of suitable machines in the most appropriate locations. This means you only have devices where you need them and this alone can have a big impact on costs.</p>\r\n<p>Software monitors toner and replacement cartridges are dispatched when needed. The software also notifies your provider when your machine needs a service &ndash; leaving your employees free to get on with more important tasks.</p>\r\n<p>Walter Leser, IT Manager at Foundation Housing explains; <em class="font_blue">&ldquo;MPS has saved us the time and hassle of ordering and stocking toner and we no-longer need to monitor our devices to spot maintenance issues. All of this is done automatically which means our machines are rarely out of service.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>Furthermore, with MPS your printer maintenance, toner and imaging costs are consolidated in a regular itemised bill from your provider. There are no surprises and costs are transparent for easy budgeting. Often this lowers admin overheads as you are dealing with a single supplier and predictable costs for all purchasing related to print and copy.</p>\r\n<h2>&ldquo;Follow Me&rdquo; Print</h2>\r\n<p>Clever software prevents forgotten pages being left in the printer output tray and tackles wasteful and unnecessary printing as users must visit a printer to release their pages. The risk of confidential documents being left on a printer is reduced, which has obvious security benefits.</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Hall, Head of ICT at Yorkshire Housing, notes; <em class="font_blue">&ldquo;the simple act of requiring employees to visit a printer to release their pages immediately altered their behaviour in a very positive way. Wasted and unnecessary jobs are less common now, and defaults to limit one-sided and colour printing have further fuelled the overall effort."</em></p>\r\n<h2>Print control</h2>\r\n<p>The problem of uncontrolled printing raises various concerns that intelligent print management can address. Print control software increasingly forms the foundation of a Managed Print Service and provides a bucket-load of functionality to control output, keep sensitive documents secure, recover or allocate costs, apply quotas, report on activity and minimise waste.</p>\r\n<p>Print control provides cost transparency, improved document security and greener practices by ensuring that the right documents are printed by the right people at the right time. Add this to MPS and a well thought out print strategy to make print and copy as efficient as possible.</p>\r\n<h2>Framework agreements</h2>\r\n<p>When choosing a new print and copy provider, look for a framework agreement such as those managed by Procurement for Housing (PfH). This saves you the time, cost and effort of going to tender and comparing several providers. An impartial framework provider has done all the hard work for you in order to recommend a preferred supplier.</p>\r\n<h2>Combined approach</h2>\r\n<p>Printing is here to stay, even though volumes may decline, so put the tools in place to let you proactively govern your print infrastructure. Combining tools that monitor, archive and control output with the right mix of hardware, simplified maintenance, &ldquo;just-in-time&rdquo; toner supplies and transparent billing will naturally push costs down. Not only this; a more print aware culture is nurtured, within which employees are far more considerate about what they print.</p>\r\n<p>The next natural step is to consider where paper-led processes can be automated and digitised with the introduction of electronic document and records management (EDRMS). Once this gets underway, serious financial and efficiency savings can be realised, revolutionising your business.</p>\r\n<h3><br />About Sean McGuigan</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/171/contained_images/b180e630ff10_245_SEAN-MCGUIGAN.jpg?1383045240" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Business Development Manager<br />Tel: 0844 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:SeanM@arenagroup.net">SeanM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Sean joined the Arena Group in 2010, he specialises in print and copy  management, Managed  Print Services (MPS) and electronic document  management (EDM). Sean works with both public and private sector  clients, implementing proven strategies to reduce costs, increase  efficiency and establish greener ways of working.</p>', '2014-01-17', 'iStock_000018408496_XXXLarge.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 329910, '2013-10-29 11:23:19', 'PaperHouse', '2013-10-29 09:40:48', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, '7-small-steps-towards-big-savings-in-the-housing-sector'),
(172, 'Green fingered Arena Group volunteers support New Lodge Allotments', 'Arena Group has recently teamed-up with Yorkshire Housing to provide some much needed support to its community allotments in the New Lodge area of Barnsley.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group has recently teamed-up with <a href="http://www.yorkshirehousing.co.uk/" target="_blank">Yorkshire Housing</a> to provide some much needed support to its community allotments in the New Lodge area of Barnsley. A group of volunteers from Arena will clear one plot to win over potential tenants, who will use the site to grow their own produce.</p>\r\n<p>Lucy Cheetham, Community Development Advisor from Yorkshire Housing, tells us; &ldquo;support from Arena will help us to get the allotments into a manageable state to pass on to tenants who will use them to grow their own produce. The allotments are currently very overgrown with weeds, so without support from Arena we would have a real mountain to climb just to get the project off the ground.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Martin Wright, Head of HR at Arena, adds; &ldquo;we encourage our employees to take two annual days out of their usual jobs to support local community and charity projects.&rdquo; Arena has grown over the past 21 years and now employs around 160 people across six UK sites. Martin adds; &ldquo;Supporting our local communities has always been important to us, especially as our business expands. Our volunteers get involved with all sorts of activities from painting and gardening, to hosting interview practice at school careers days or helping out at events for vulnerable groups such as the elderly. This project was a perfect fit for us, and has proven very popular with our volunteers.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The allotments were developed in response to calls from the local community to utilise an area of derelict land; Yorkshire Housing has created 24 plots to be managed by a specially appointed Allotment Society. Lucy explains; &ldquo;tenants will pay the Allotment Society an annual fee of &pound;52 to cover the cost of water, seeds and other necessities. We are encouraging people to work together to create their own sustainable community project.&rdquo; The scheme is the first step towards a larger vision that could see social enterprises formed by young people learning skills on the allotments that they can offer out to the wider community.</p>\r\n<p>Sales Administrator, Leah Whitelock, took part in the day and told us; &ldquo;it&rsquo;s great to get out in the fresh air and help out with a project like this. It&rsquo;s a change from my usual job and it&rsquo;s really satisfying to know that I&rsquo;m giving something back to the community.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Can our volunteers help you?</h2>\r\n<p>At Arena we are keen to give something back to our local communities. We are always seeking community or charity projects for our volunteers, so please get in touch if you would like to apply for a CSR team to visit you!</p>\r\n<p>Simply drop an email to us at <a href="mailto:marketing@arenagroup.net">marketing@arenagroup.net </a></p>', '2013-11-04', 'IMG_0140.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 132166, '2013-11-04 10:03:49', '', '2013-11-04 10:01:47', '2014-10-08 11:56:29', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'green-fingered-arena-group-volunteers-support-new-lodge-allotments');
