(173, 'Cyber security - keeping your data safe outside of the office', 'In this article, Neil Maude discusses the basics of cyber security whilst on the move; covering the simple things which you must consider, plus a few of the more complex ideas behind them.', '<p class="introduction">Recently, the BBC &lsquo;Click&rsquo; programme ran a feature on security when using public WiFi &ndash; such as at your favourite coffee shop.&nbsp; With the ever increasing requirement to access information whilst on the move, business users are going to do this more and more often.&nbsp; In this article, we discuss the basics of cyber security whilst on the move.&nbsp; The simple things which you must consider, as well as a few of the more complex ideas behind them.</p>\r\n<h2>Physical security</h2>\r\n<p>Pragmatically speaking, the most likely way that your data could be lost is if the physical kit is stolen and it is essential to keep this in mind.&nbsp; Whilst &ldquo;out and about&rdquo;, we&rsquo;re using expensive bits of IT kit &ndash; attractive to casual thieves. So just take the obvious precautions.&nbsp; Be aware of your environment and how you might be exposed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>You wouldn&rsquo;t leave your wallet out on the edge of a table at a coffee shop, so don&rsquo;t do it with your smartphone either.</em></p>\r\n<p>A second physical security consideration is how much valuable and confidential data do you have on the device itself?&nbsp; Should you have that much?&nbsp; Can you avoid downloading data to the device?&nbsp; As 3G is getting more universal, we are closing in on a time when we will have access from anywhere &ndash; so you could have no data on the devices you&rsquo;re carrying around, just accessing corporate systems.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>But in the meantime, have you done anything to protect the data which is on your mobile devices?&nbsp; Some things to consider are encryption of the hard drive on your laptop (e.g. Windows BitLocker) and lock codes on devices.&nbsp; You may also want to get one of the &ldquo;remote wipe&rdquo; tools which are available for smart phones and tablets.&nbsp; It won&rsquo;t help to get your kit back if the worst should happen &ndash; but at least your corporate data won&rsquo;t fall into the wrong hands.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>Lost and stolen laptops are one of main causes of fines issued by the Information Commissioner''s Office. Taking reasonable precautions against theft &ndash; including encryption &ndash; is simply not optional.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<h2>Open WiFi &ndash; some problems</h2>\r\n<p>So, assuming that your kit hasn&rsquo;t been stolen, how else might someone get at your data?&nbsp; To understand this, first we need to know a bit about how WiFi works.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To display web pages, received e-mails and communication with corporate systems, your laptop uses WiFi to send and receive &ldquo;packets&rdquo; of information.&nbsp; These packets are sent between your laptop and the WiFi hub via radio waves. &nbsp;&nbsp;And like any radio signal, these packets can be received by anyone who tunes in to the right frequency.&nbsp; Your laptop only acts on the information which is intended for it, but in fact it &ldquo;hears&rdquo; all of the information flying around<a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a>.&nbsp; If you&rsquo;re in a public space with lots of different devices, it&rsquo;s a bit like everyone shouting messages to each other and your laptop filtering out everything but the bit which is intended for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s actually trivial to set a laptop to receive traffic for <em>everyone</em> and this is how hackers start to try to get at your data.&nbsp; So anything sent in &ldquo;clear&rdquo; &ndash; i.e. without encryption &ndash; is open to someone else reading it.&nbsp; And whether WiFi is encrypted depends on how the provider has set up their router, although the vast majority are.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;d think that it would be easy to check if your connection was encrypted &ndash; which it is<a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a> &ndash; and if so, that you&rsquo;d be safe.&nbsp; Unfortunately, there are ways to break many of the common encryption modes used by WiFi routers &ndash; in some cases this might take a few hours, but it can be done &ndash; and then the eavesdropper can capture your data.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>The main thing to know about WiFi is that your packets of information are being transmitted to anyone who is in range of the WiFi transceiver in your laptop, and who cares to listen.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<h2>Man-in-the-middle (or ''MITM'')</h2>\r\n<p>I mentioned there that <em>many </em>encryption set-ups can be cracked and that it may take a while.&nbsp; Being realistic, this probably won&rsquo;t be the case at the particular hotspot you&rsquo;re using &ndash; it&rsquo;s just not worth the effort on the part of the hacker.&nbsp; A much simpler way to trap you is the &ldquo;man-in-the-middle&rdquo; attack.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Conceptually, this would work as follows.&nbsp; A hacker goes into the coffee shop and gets the password to join their network.&nbsp; He/She then sets up their laptop to act as a WiFi hotspot, using the same password and with a name quite similar to the real one (maybe they&rsquo;d call it &ldquo;Shop Free WiFi&rdquo; if the real one is called &ldquo;Shop WiFi&rdquo;).&nbsp; You then come along and try to make a connection &ndash; picking my router instead of the real one. Your laptop and mine make a secure and encrypted connection and the hacker makes an onward connection via the real router.&nbsp; The situation is now that all your traffic flows through the hacker''s laptop.&nbsp; The key point is that your laptops have made an encrypted connection, which the hacker can decrypt at will<a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a>.&nbsp; The hacker is the &ldquo;man-in-the-middle&rdquo;, reading your data, but you think you&rsquo;ve made an encrypted network connection &hellip; you have of course, just not to the intended source!</p>\r\n<p>Incidentally, don&rsquo;t assume that you&rsquo;re safe if you&rsquo;re using a <em>wired</em> network &ndash; such as in a hotel room.&nbsp; A technique with the scary-sounding name of <em>''ARP poisoning''</em> works in much the same way.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>Know the name of the WiFi router you should connect to. If you find more than one similar sounding name, check again.&nbsp; The staff may even be interested to know that some new networks have appeared.</em></p>\r\n<h2>Some solutions - HTTPS and VPN</h2>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s all been doom and gloom so far &ndash; you might start to think that there is no way to use a public internet connection safely.&nbsp; Well, it&rsquo;s not quite that bad and there are some things you can do to mitigate these problems.</p>\r\n<p>The different exploits described above rely on the ability of an attacker to make sense of traffic as it passes by, from your device to the eventual destination.&nbsp; But what if the data is encrypted in some other way, before it even leaves your laptop? And then only decrypted when it reaches the (intended) destination?&nbsp; If your laptop and the destination have established some form of encryption &ndash; privately and unique to this particular session &ndash; the eavesdropper can&rsquo;t make sense of the data.&nbsp; This foils even the MITM attack, as even though the attacker has broken the <em>transport </em>encryption, they still only get to see data in an encrypted form.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>There are 2 techniques to do this &ndash; HTTPS for websites and VPN for accessing your corporate network.</em></p>\r\n<h3>Secure Websites - HTTPS</h3>\r\n<p>Secure websites use HTTPS as the transport protocol, instead of the standard plain HTTP.&nbsp; You can see this in your browser, as the address for the web page will start with https://.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The system relies on certificates which are issued to the website provider.&nbsp; The certificate gives you assurance that the website is genuine and your web browser validates this against a <em>certificate authority</em>.&nbsp; There is some complex mathematics behind this but the certification gives you two things &ndash; an assurance that you&rsquo;re talking to who you think you are and some data which your web browser can use to create a encryption unique key.&nbsp; Each end of the connection then knows enough to encrypt the packets of information in a way that <em>only the other end can decrypt</em>.&nbsp; You can then safely use that website, secure in the knowledge that anyone snooping on your WiFi signal can&rsquo;t read your data<a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a>.</p>\r\n<h3>Virtual Private Networks - VPN</h3>\r\n<p>If you want to access corporate data or attach your laptop to the corporate network from a remote location, a virtual private network is the best solution.&nbsp; This creates a secure connection from your laptop to the corporate network, with the internet just used as a transport system in between.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again, the key is that data is encrypted before it leaves your device and can only be decrypted by the VPN &lsquo;gateway&rsquo; at the corporate network end.&nbsp; This gives you the same protection as HTTPS &ndash; a snooper can see the packets of data, but they&rsquo;re encrypted at source and so can&rsquo;t be read.</p>\r\n<p>VPN is typically set up by your corporate IT department.&nbsp; In fact, your corporate network should never be open to outside access without a VPN being used.</p>\r\n<h2>An aside on prime numbers</h2>\r\n<p>Modern cryptography is based on properties of prime numbers &ndash; numbers which are only divisible by themselves and one.&nbsp; The crucial point is that if you multiply two prime numbers together, it is very hard to work back from the result to figure out what those prime numbers were.&nbsp; This is sometimes likened to &ldquo;secret paint mixing&rdquo; &ndash; it&rsquo;s easy to mix paint colours, but impossible to separate them again.&nbsp; The best currently known algorithms to find prime factors of a large number rely on lots of guessing and the computing power required to do this increases hugely as the numbers get bigger<a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, if two parties know a couple of large prime numbers, they can pass the <em>result of the multiplication</em> between them without worrying that anyone can get back to the original primes.&nbsp; This is the fundamental of what is called <em>public key cryptography</em> and the basis of how two parties can create a secure connection over an unsecure (unknown) link.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Of course, as computing power is ever increasing, the problem of <em>factoring</em> the product of two large primes becomes more vulnerable to a &ldquo;brute force&rdquo; try-every-value attack.&nbsp; So the prime numbers used are big &ndash; really, really big.&nbsp; This is why you see &ldquo;256-bit&rdquo; encryption talked about &ndash; the 256 refers to the number of digits in the binary representation of the values being used.&nbsp; 1024-bit and 2048-bit are becoming increasing common key lengths.</p>\r\n<h2>Some final basic points to remember</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTPS and VPN tools rely on your laptop or device establishing a connection to a network or website and all traffic leaving your laptop being encrypted.&nbsp; But this is no use at all if your laptop is already compromised in some way.&nbsp; (This next bit applies anywhere, not just out-and-about).</p>\r\n<p>The ideal situation for a hacker is to have some software running on your laptop and there are a few ways to achieve this.&nbsp; Firstly, if you don&rsquo;t have a firewall configured, your laptop can be attacked directly whenever it is connected to a public network (you&rsquo;re probably OK on the corporate LAN which will have firewalls already).&nbsp; Fortunately, most computers are now protected by default.&nbsp; The second approach is to get you to run a program which installs a virus, Trojan or other piece of spyware.&nbsp; This is typically done with &ldquo;social exploits&rdquo; &ndash; tricking the user with a fraudulent e-mail or website.</p>\r\n<p>A virus is a program which replicates itself by attaching to other programs on your computer. To get infected, all you need to do is run an infected program.&nbsp; A Trojan is a program which pretends to do something that you&rsquo;d want, but is actually working for the hacker.&nbsp; Spyware is software which runs invisibly on your computer, but allows some form of remote control by the hacker.&nbsp; Once spyware is present, the hacker could do almost anything &ndash; scan your hard-drive, take a screenshot of your desktop or log any keys you press (e.g. as you type in your password for your on-line banking).</p>\r\n<p>You can protect yourself from these threats in two ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Have an up to date virus scanning program.&nbsp;</strong> The up-to-date part is very important, because virus checkers use &ldquo;signatures&rdquo; to detect virus programs &ndash; just like the biological version, a modern virus program mutates and changes its signature.&nbsp; So you need up to date virus detection tools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Simply be careful about which programs you run.</strong>&nbsp; If a website unexpectedly pops up a request to install a program or run a Java applet, be very wary.&nbsp; The most common method of infection is to trick a user into clicking on a link to a false web page which asks the user to download spyware.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><em>Keep these concepts in mind and you massively reduce the chance of a nasty infection and having your data &ndash; or worse - stolen.</em></p>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\n<p>So, in summary, the following are some key points to keep in mind when using public WiFi:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be aware of the potential risks &ndash; both physical and virtual</li>\r\n<li>Only connect to WiFi access points that you know to be genuine</li>\r\n<li>Expect secure websites &ndash; https &ndash; and don&rsquo;t use unsecured websites</li>\r\n<li>Have an up-to-date virus checking program</li>\r\n<li>Don&rsquo;t run programs from an unknown source, no matter how appealing they may&nbsp; sound</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><br /> \r\n<hr size="1" />\r\n<div>\r\n<h6><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a> This is why modern household internet hubs &ndash; such as the latest BT Home Hubs &ndash; dynamically adjust their signal to try to improve reception.&nbsp; Chances are that your neighbours are interfering with the signal, so congested are the airwaves.<a href="#_ftnref2"></a></h6>\r\n<h6><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a> For example, check the properties of the connection by clicking on the system tray icon on your laptop.<a href="#_ftnref3"></a></h6>\r\n<h6><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a> In fact, he has to do this in order to send it on &ndash; your connection might be a bit slower.</h6>\r\n<h6><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a> It&rsquo;s a fact of data security that the landscape is ever changing.&nbsp; There are theoretical/proof-of-concept attacks on HTTPS, such as <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_Layer_Security#BEAST_attack">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_Layer_Security#BEAST_attack</a>. But these are not considered practical at the present time.<a href="#_ftnref5"></a></h6>\r\n<h6><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a> If a fast prime factoring algorithm was to be discovered, the whole field of encryption and cryptography would be turned on its head.&nbsp; This is a big part of the interest in quantum computing, which suggests this <em>might </em>be possible at some point in the future.</h6>\r\n<h3>About Neil Maude</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../assets/articles/113/contained_images/8d9e8419f6d7_180_NeilM_ws.jpg?1359557446" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Electronic Document Management General Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:neilM@arenagroup.net">neilM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Neil joined the Arena Group in 2006 and has almost 20 years of   experience in the electronic document management industry, working with   both private and public sector customers.&nbsp; Neil sits on Arena&rsquo;s board  of  directors and manages the delivery operations of Arena&rsquo;s EDM  business.&nbsp;  His team spend their time developing software, implementing  solutions  for customers and providing after-sales software support  services, both  in the UK and internationally.</p>\r\n<h2>Related Features</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/163">Confidential files left on trains, in the wrong hands, on the move?</a></p>\r\n<a href="../../../articles/113?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank">Compliant Records Management in UK Schools - 6 feature series<br /></a>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store, software for document management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../case_studies?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">Case studies: <strong>m</strong>store in practice</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2013-11-25', 'iStock_000024004901Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 531637, '2013-11-22 11:02:04', 'Cyber Security', '2013-11-21 15:41:17', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'cyber-security-keeping-your-data-safe-outside-of-the-office'),
(174, 'Arena and Agenci offer a one-stop compliance shop for straight-forward information security ', 'Agenci and Arena Group partnership offers end-to-end compliance alignment for BSI0008 in the form of process certification and enablement technology.', '<p class="introduction">Agenci and Arena Group partnership delivers end-to-end compliance alignment for <strong>BS10008</strong> in the form of process certification and enablement technology.</p>\r\n<p>Information security experts, <a href="http://www.theagenci.com/" target="_blank">Agenci</a>, have partnered with Arena Group in support of its <strong>m</strong>store software for electronic document and records management (EDRMS). &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Agenci&rsquo;s Managing Director, Gary Hibberd, comments; &ldquo;following a review of <a href="../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store</a>, we can confirm that it is aligned with BS10008 and, used in accordance with certified policies and processes, it can effectively enable compliance with the standard.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s General Manager, Neil Maude, comments; &ldquo;Ag<img class="image_right" src="../../../assets/articles/174/contained_images/ca1a90bc613b_253_Agenci Information Security - Bw.jpg?1385132929" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" />enci adds value to our offering in that we now have a trusted advisor to whom we can direct customers who are looking for specialist expertise in the area of compliance, and peace of mind that their new policies comply with BS10008.&rdquo; Gary adds; &ldquo;for the first time ever, and with support from Arena, we can deliver a full solution to our customers &ndash; certified procedures and <strong>m</strong>store to enable compliance. This makes the process of executing a new, compliant way of working so much quicker and simpler for the customer.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Agenci has assessed many businesses to reveal what needs to be done in order to meet the requirements of BS10008. Gary comments; &ldquo;In the cases where proposed measures towards certification have been applied the benefits to the client in terms of efficiency improvement and cost reduction have been striking.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Similarly, Arena has found that alignment with the standard is already crucial in the public sector, for example in education, which is subject to increasingly stringent legislation regarding the safeguarding of data pertaining to young and vulnerable people. Neil comments; &ldquo;We have doubled our customer base for <strong>m</strong>store over the past two years and BS10008 is often a key concern for the customers we work with.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>In the New Year, Agenci and Arena plan to host a special workshop event in Leeds city centre to present the requirements of BS10008, and options for compliance. This will feature a special demonstration of <strong>m</strong>store, and case studies from Arena Group customers already benefitting from compliance. If you would be interested in attending, please contact <a href="mailto:marketing@arenagroup.net">marketing@arenagroup.net</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>What is BS10008?</h2>\r\n<p><br />BS10008 is the&nbsp;British Standard&nbsp;for &ldquo;evidential weight and&nbsp;legal admissibility of&nbsp;electronic information.&rdquo; Introduced in 2008, this standard outlines the&nbsp;specific requirements for the implementation&nbsp;and operation of electronic information management systems.</p>\r\n<p>The standard covers&nbsp;the storage and transfer of information, and addresses issues relating to&nbsp;its authenticity and integrity.&nbsp;<em><span class="font_blue">These issues are&nbsp;important where the information might be used as evidence.</span></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>What are the benefits of BS10008 certification?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improved data security</li>\r\n<li>Increased efficiency</li>\r\n<li>Reduced bureaucracy</li>\r\n<li>Reduced operating costs</li>\r\n<li>Reduced reliance on paper</li>\r\n<li>Improved front line services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Reducing your reliance on paper and digitising processes can save ten&rsquo;s of thousands per year and brings a host of other benefits including increased efficiency, better customer service and increased office space - no more filing cabinets! Certification to BS10008 goes further to ensure that your records can still be used as evidence, should the need arise. This is imperative for many sectors including law, insurance, health and education.</p>\r\n<p>Government and business are increasingly looking to achieve the &lsquo;less paper office&rsquo; in order to reduce costs and improve process efficiencies in the face of tough economic times. Furthermore, technology and the way we consume and work with data is rapidly evolving - there is a growing desire for digital information but this makes data protection a priority concern. 2014/15 will see the introduction of new EU wide Data Protection laws, making this standard even more important. In sectors ranging from health, with the introduction of the electronic medical record, to law, as the government pushes for a paperless court system; the controls over data are key to the delivery of a secure service and protecting personal data.</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">More about <strong>m</strong>store</a></p>\r\n<p>More about Agenci: <strong><a href="http://www.theagenci.com/bs10008" target="_blank">http://www.theagenci.com/bs10008</a></strong></p>', '2013-11-22', 'iStock_000015959628Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 174538, '2013-11-22 14:23:52', 'BSi10008', '2013-11-22 14:17:18', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-and-agenci-offer-a-one-stop-compliance-shop-for-straight-forward-information-security'),
(175, 'Meet us at the Nottingham ASBM', 'Arena Group''s Paul Grant will be at the Nottingham Association of School Business Managers Meeting on the 28th of January.', '<p class="introduction">The perfect opportunity to meet our team and chat about all things document management.</p>\r\n<p>The Nottingham ASBM conference takes place at Center Parks, Nottingham on the 28th of January.</p>\r\n<p>We will be showcasing our full range of services; from <a href="../../../articles/112" target="_blank">print control software</a>, our <a href="../../../page/print-the-hidden-costs" target="_blank">Managed Print Service</a> (MPS) to <a href="http://http//www.arenagroup.net/page/edm-for-education" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store for Education</a>. Speak to our experts about how we can help you to improve efficiencies and reduce costs.</p>\r\n<p>The meeting takes a new format, combining with the Nottinghamshire County Council and Nottingham City Council Annual Services to Schools event.</p>\r\n<p>The morning session will be a meeting for all of the members of the Nottingham ASBM.</p>\r\n<p>The afternoon session is an excellent opportunity to come along and meet our team as Head Teachers and other school representitives from Nottinghamshire County and Nottingham City Council will be invited to visit the exhibition.</p>\r\n<p>Every exhibitor place is taken for what is gearing up to be an excellent event.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-01-15', 'Notts ASBM logo.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 179914, '2013-11-28 16:12:00', 'Notts Association of School Business Management Logo', '2013-11-28 15:56:42', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'meet-us-at-the-nottingham-asbm'),
(176, 'Our elves are busy this Christmas!', 'December has arrived and everyone at Arena knows what that means … It’s time for our volunteers to dust off their Christmas hats, dig out their festive jumpers, practice their dance moves and get ready for some festive fun!', '<h1 class="introduction">December has arrived and everyone at Arena knows what that means &hellip; It&rsquo;s time for our volunteers to dust off their Christmas hats, dig out their festive jumpers, practice their dance moves and get ready for some festive fun!</h1>\r\n<h2>The Big Give</h2>\r\n<p>Our volunteers help to wrap presents for underpriviledged children in  Bradford, many of whom probably wouldn''t otherwise receive gifts on  Christmas Day.</p>\r\n<p>The team spent their day putting batteries into toys and dropping them into gift bags. Stickers were added before gathering the gifts together, ready for an event themed around Disney''s ''Fozen'' - which will be hosted for the lucky children closer to Christmas.</p>\r\n<p>Arena''s Lyndsey Standidge attended The Big Give for the 3rd consecutive year and told us why it''s so fulfilling. "Its always nice to be able to offer help and support to others less fortunate, especially around Christmas time. All in all we had a great day, roll on next year!"</p>\r\n<h2>Holbeck Elderly Aid Christmas Party</h2>\r\n<p>A keenly anticipated event on the Arena Group CSR calendar, this year&rsquo;s party was quickly subscribed by volunteers who returned to help ensure that it was a success.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://http//holbeckelderlyaid.org.uk/" target="_blank">Holbeck Elderly Aid</a> helps older people to live independently by providing a range of activities such as lunch clubs, IT classes and shopping trips to the local supermarket. At the annual Christmas party our volunteers help with an array of tasks, from setting tables and serving food and drinks to selling raffle tickets and showcasing a spot of the &lsquo;hokey-cokey&rsquo;!</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s festive meal was followed by a tombola. At the end of the party, our volunteers handed out gifts &ndash; donated by Arena Group colleagues &ndash; to ensure that every attendee left with a present to enjoy.</p>\r\n<p>Arena''s Mike Alsancak commented; &ldquo;it&rsquo;s great fun being there and really satisfying when you see how much the guests enjoy the party.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Leeds Rotary Club Christmas Card Posting</h2>\r\n<p>Our volunteers will be out posting Christmas cards in support of Leeds Rotary Club on December 17th. If you see them, please give them a cheery wave!</p>\r\n<h2>Can our volunteers help you?</h2>\r\n<p>At Arena we are keen to give something back to our local communities so we are always seeking community or charity projects for our volunteers. Whether you have a party to host, a garden to weed, walls to paint or skills to take advantage of, please get in touch to apply for a CSR visit! Simply drop an email to us at <a href="mailto:marketing@arenagroup.net">marketing@arenagroup.net </a></p>', '2014-12-15', 'wrapping 1.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 222650, '2014-12-15 17:15:36', 'Big Give Group', '2013-12-03 15:24:35', '2014-12-15 17:15:37', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'our-elves-are-busy-this-christmas'),
(177, 'Arena Elves wrap gifts for the Big Give', 'The Arena volunteers have visited the Abundant Life Centre in Bradford to support the Big Give’s Christmas gift giveaway.', '<p class="introduction">Many families that attend the Big Give are quite simply unable to afford  gifts for their own children, christmas decorations and christmas  dinner due to other more essential items that need to be paid for such  as food and heating bills.</p>\r\n<p>It culminates in a large giveaway event where Christmas  presents are given to all children attending that are aged 11 and below.  Before that is possible however, a lot of work takes place behind the  scenes.</p>\r\n<p>This is where our volunteer elves come in.</p>\r\n<p>Our  volunteers arrived to be met by a large room full of brilliant toys for  children of all ages. Arena&rsquo;s task was simple; to wrap as many as  possible.</p>\r\n<p>Forming a production line with tasks varying from  cutting paper to finishing it off with bows and ribbon, they finally  marked the gift with the appropriate age sticker to be sure that it  would go to a child that would appreciate it the most.</p>\r\n<p>Claire Mclean enjoyed the day;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s  a really good day that always makes me feel really Christmassy. It&rsquo;s  great to know that our hard work ensures that some less fortunate  children get at least one gift over the Christmas period.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>More information on the Big Give and its importance to to the local community can be read here: <a href="http://secure.thebiggive.org.uk/projects/view/12855/the-big-give" target="_blank">thebiggive.org.uk</a></p>', '2013-12-19', '20131210_114459.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 178730, '2014-01-10 16:42:46', '', '2014-01-10 16:42:49', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-elves-wrap-gifts-for-the-big-give'),
(179, 'INFOGRAPHIC: Paper Vs Programs', 'The completely paperless office is often not achievable but a transition to ''less paper'' has a number of benefits - explored in this infographic.', '<p class="introduction">The completely paperless office is often not achievable but a transition to ''less paper'' has a number of benefits.</p>\r\n<h5><em>Click the image below to enlarge it.</em></h5>\r\n<h3>Related Pages:</h3>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">Electonic Document Management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/75_IG_paper_vs_programmes_final.jpg" target="_blank"><img id="the_img_link" src="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/75_IG_paper_vs_programmes_final.jpg" alt="Paper Vs Programmes" width="600" /></a></p>', '2014-01-15', 'Infographic.png', 'image/png', 1633608, '2014-02-03 09:25:51', '', '2014-01-15 09:14:11', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 1, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'infographic-paper-vs-programs'),
(180, 'A day in the life... Service Apprentice', 'We have been speaking to a few of our apprentices to learn what they do at Arena. First up is a Service Apprentice.', '<p class="introduction">"It&rsquo;s really encouraging to see former apprentices doing well in the  field; I know that, if I work hard, I have a good chance to succeed as  well."</p>\r\n<p><strong>When I finished school I knew that I didn&rsquo;t want to be sitting down behind a desk all day so I did an IT apprenticeship. Whilst I was there, Pete (my manager at Arena) came to give us a talk about the service apprenticeship role at Arena and I realised that it was something I could really enjoy doing.</strong></p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m based at Arena&rsquo;s Garforth workshop with other apprentices. It&rsquo;s a fun environment as we all get on well &mdash; there&rsquo;s lots of banter and we see each other out of work time too. The learning is really hands on; we spend so much time repairing and reconditioning machines that it becomes second nature. If I&rsquo;m struggling I just ask Pete and he explains how the problem has occurred and how to avoid it in the future. Because there are a few of us though, we quite often figure out how to solve faults between us, without Pete&rsquo;s help.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We receive training ranging from IT qualifications at college to learning about new machines on special courses hosted by manufacturers. That&rsquo;s what I like here; we get lots of variety and we&rsquo;re always moving forwards. I&rsquo;ve been on eight training courses since I started here in late 2011.</p>\r\n<p>After a few months you get assigned a mentor. This is a Service <br /> Engineer who started off as an apprentice. Going to visit the customers with my mentor is my favourite part of the job; the challenges are so different to being in the workshop and you never know what to expect.</p>\r\n<p>We also have individual responsibilities; a few of us check second hand machines to decide whether to scrap them for parts, refurbish them or sell them straight on to a reseller. Other apprentices have tasks like preparing parts for engineers in the field.</p>\r\n<p>I recently spent three months working away on a large installation spread over many sites from Southampton to Livingstone. I stayed in hotels through the week, travelling back home on a Friday. I was there with two other apprentices and an engineer; Arena seem to like sending us on the larger installs for the experience of being out in the field, supporting the engineers and wider service team &mdash; Arena&rsquo;s whole ethos is very much &ldquo;in it together&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>Eventually I want to manage my own team of engineers but for now the next step is to become a Service Engineer, out on the road and fixing machines on customer sites. We are awarded points based on our performance and being at the top of the points table when a vacancy comes up gives you a much better chance of getting a position as an engineer. As an added bonus, whoever is top of the table at the end of the year is invited, along with their partner, to join high achievers from throughout the company for the Premier Conference - a long weekend away in a sunny overseas location.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s really encouraging to see former apprentices doing well in the field; I know that, if I work hard, I have a good chance to succeed as well.</p>\r\n<p class="introduction">Tom</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information about our apprenticeship programme, or to see how to apply, view our <a href="../../../page/apprenticeship-programme">Apprenticeship Academy page.</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other articles in this series:</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/181">Administration Apprentice</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/182">IT Apprentice<strong>&nbsp;</strong></a><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-03-03', 'IMG_0192.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 119725, '2014-01-17 15:15:45', '', '2014-01-17 15:15:55', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'a-day-in-the-life-service-apprentice'),
(181, 'A day in the life… Administration Apprentice', 'We have been speaking to a few of our Apprentices to learn what they do at Arena. Hear from our Admin Apprentice.', '<p class="introduction">"My favourite thing about this job is my colleagues - there&rsquo;s a great atmosphere in the office and we all get along."</p>\r\n<p><strong>I was working in a consumer facing role in the financial sector before I came to Arena. I had expected to stay there but a friend told me about the apprenticeship vacancy at Arena. The opportunity to train and earn a qualification whilst working made it an attractive move for me.</strong></p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve never worked in this type of business environment before, so being an apprentice is really good experience. A role like this is all about learning and means that I can get a really good understanding of the way a commercial business operates.</p>\r\n<p>When I first started here I received training from my manager, Sandra; she gave me responsibility for a few tasks and the guidance I needed to get started. Since then my role has really grown.</p>\r\n<p>I make sure that any changes to customer contracts are smoothly administered and I set up new deals on the system. This can be as simple as adding information about a new machine against an existing account or entering details for a brand new customer. I&rsquo;m often contacting leasing companies or customers to ensure that we all have access to up-to-date information.</p>\r\n<p>I also work closely with Arena&rsquo;s Admin Assistant, Debbie, liaising with customers and Arena&rsquo;s Sales and Service teams to collate information in preparation for installations. Debbie is training me to support her during really busy times, and to cover her role when she is away.</p>\r\n<p>Another of my regular tasks is recording customer feedback gathered by our Customer Relationship Management Team (CRMs). The CRMs visit our customers to ensure that they are satisfied with the service they are receiving from Arena, and they gather lots of useful feedback. This all goes into a database and I save individual surveys into <strong>m</strong>store before sending letters to customers to thank them for taking the time to offer us their feedback.</p>\r\n<p>Outside of my day-to-day role I also help with invoices and leases along with binding proposals for the Sales team. I also work on reception when our receptionist is away, manning the switchboard and welcoming guests. I quite enjoy that &ndash; it was quite daunting at first because the switchboard can be incredibly busy, but now I know what I&rsquo;m doing it makes a nice change from being in the office.</p>\r\n<p>The work I do is incredibly varied and the people I work with really make my job enjoyable. I get a lot of support from colleagues in the Finance and Admin teams&ndash; and Sandra is always available if I have any questions. There&rsquo;s a great atmosphere in the office and we all get along; I&rsquo;ve made a lot of good friends and we spend time together in and out of work. The social events have really made me feel part of the team from the very beginning.</p>\r\n<p>Alongside my role I&rsquo;m studying for a Business NVQ at Wakefield College. I have assignments to do outside of work and lecturers from the college also visit Arena to observe the work I&rsquo;m doing.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m not sure about the future but for now I&rsquo;m happy to be in a role that I enjoy whilst getting a qualification and developing skills that I know will be useful in whatever challenge I take on next.</p>\r\n<p class="introduction">Evie</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information about our apprenticeship programme, or to see how to apply, view our <a href="../../../page/apprenticeship-programme">Apprenticeship Academy page.</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Other articles in this series:</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/180">Service Apprentice<br /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/182">IT Apprentice<strong> </strong></a><strong><br /></strong></p>', '2014-03-03', '0803.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 215642, '2014-03-03 10:32:23', '', '2014-01-22 13:38:50', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'a-day-in-the-life…-administration-apprentice'),
(182, 'A day in the life… IT Apprentice', 'We have been speaking to a few of our apprentices to learn what they do at Arena. In our final article, here''s our IT Apprentice.', '<p class="introduction">"I get all sorts of problems to solve through this which provides the  satisfaction in my role. I really enjoy solving a complex problem by  myself."</p>\r\n<p><strong>Before I started at Arena Group I had been looking for roles on an apprenticeship website. I knew that an apprenticeship was the best option for me as I wanted to continue to learn and build on the skills that I had developed whilst studying IT at college.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The training opportunities have been exactly what I hoped for; I&rsquo;m studying for a BTEC and National Diploma in IT as part of my apprenticeship. Also, alongside this, Arena is helping me to gain my Microsoft qualifications.</p>\r\n<p>Although I had previously studied IT at college, IT in the working environment is completely different. I was pretty much a clean slate when I arrived which I think has made it easier for Steve, my manager, to teach me.</p>\r\n<p>There are just the two of us in the IT office. We get on well; working hard but have a laugh as well. Because of the nature of my job I also spend a lot of time with various members of staff around the company. I&rsquo;m often travelling between Arena&rsquo;s various sites; it&rsquo;s good to be out and about, visiting colleagues that I wouldn&rsquo;t otherwise see.</p>\r\n<p>My job is very varied; I&rsquo;m responsible for setting up phones, laptops and door fobs for new employees. I also order new equipment such as software and computer parts, and I provide some support to internal users of MS Dynamics, our sales database.</p>\r\n<p>The main target that I am measured by is the quality of my responses to IT tickets, or queries, from staff - I must respond to at least 80% of these personally. I get all sorts of problems to solve through this which provides the satisfaction in my role. I really enjoy solving a complex problem by myself.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m not looking too far ahead, when my apprenticeship is finished my goal is simple; to get a permanent role here at Arena as an IT Support Technician. Then, I hope to continue to develop my IT skills through my daily experiences and hopefully earn more Microsoft qualifications. I&rsquo;ve learned so much over the last two years and I want to continue to learn once I finish my apprenticeship.</p>\r\n<p class="introduction">Mark</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information about our apprenticeship programme, or to see how to apply, view our <a href="../../../page/apprenticeship-programme">Apprenticeship Academy page.</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Other articles in this series:</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/181">Administration Apprentice</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/182"></a><a href="../../../articles/180">Service Apprentice</a><strong><br /></strong></p>', '2014-03-03', '0926.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 204377, '2014-02-03 11:25:02', '', '2014-01-22 13:42:48', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'a-day-in-the-life…-it-apprentice'),
(183, 'Arena achieves Ricoh''s Gold Standard', 'Arena Group has achieved the Ricoh Gold Standard Certification for delivery of excellence in customer service.', '<p class="introduction">Ricoh state that; <em>&ldquo;Gold Partner Certification is awarded to dealerships with the most advanced levels of technical competence and highly effective service processes in place to manage the installation and maintenance of Ricoh hardware solutions.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>The award focuses on several areas relating to service and support, including technical training, call escalation, staff development and account management. Arena has met the highest standards in all of these areas and an annual audit will ensure that levels are maintained.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mick Harrison, Group Service Manager at Arena comments;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;<em>We&rsquo;re extremely pleased to have been recognised as a Ricoh Gold Partner. This recognition differentiates Arena Group as a leading service provider, acknowledges the dedication of our Service Team and demonstrates Arena&rsquo;s commitment to employee training and development.</em>&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Gold Partner Status gives Arena access to the most up-to-date support and prioritised product training, which means Arena&nbsp; customers can be assured reliable advice and support with even the very latest Ricoh products and the most complex installations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-01-23', 'GOLD customer service logo.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 757149, '2014-01-23 10:39:16', '', '2014-01-23 10:37:37', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-achieves-ricohs-gold-standard');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(184, 'Future-proofing a large document archive', 'Common challenges surrounding the retention of information for a very long time, and the considerations worth making before you digitise a large paper archive.', '<p class="introduction">A look at the challenges surrounding the retention of information for a very long time, and the considerations worth making before you digitise a large paper archive.</p>\r\n<p>Several of our previous articles advise on how to catalogue data and what should &ndash; or should not &ndash; be retained.&nbsp; In some cases, the legal retention period for a document is measured in decades, making a major issue of the decisions you take around storage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are two challenges in keeping information for a very long time.&nbsp; Firstly, it has to be safe from loss or damage.&nbsp; Secondly, it has to be usable if and when you do want to look at it again.</p>\r\n<h2>Paper Challenges</h2>\r\n<p>As a technology company, we are advocates of electronic document records management systems &ndash; <strong>EDRMS</strong> &ndash; in place of paper stores.&nbsp; Usually, EDRM systems are promoted on the grounds of better security, accessibility and efficiency. However, these systems also bring a big advantage over keeping key information in paper format:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Whenever paper files are moved or handled, they are at risk of loss, serious damage or mild degradation. </li>\r\n<li>Paper also degrades in storage - picture dusty yellowed pages held together by rusted paperclips.&nbsp; </li>\r\n<li>Some types of printed or hard copy documents are particularly sensitive, such as thermal print material, which we''ve seen degrade significantly in as little as 5 years &ndash; and become totally illegible within 10 years.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are keeping critical information on paper then you are unlikely to know its condition until you try to retrieve it - and that might be when you need to defend a legal case.</p>\r\n<p>The message here is obviously to carefully plan how you store hard copy documents if you need to archive them for many years. We would always recommend an EDRMS to safeguard your information from damage, degradation and disasters such as floods.</p>\r\n<h2>Electronic Solutions &hellip; and Challenges</h2>\r\n<p>Digitising your paper solves the physical degradation issue but electronic systems require their own considerations.</p>\r\n<p>Firstly, you&rsquo;ll need some software to handle your digital files.&nbsp; If you just go with &ldquo;files on disk&rdquo; then you have some immediate considerations:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Finding what you want, when you want it: </strong>Think carefully about file structure and how you will manage disposal of documents at the end of their retention period.</li>\r\n<li><strong>How to keep sensitive files secure:</strong> This solution won&rsquo;t have granular security or auditing.&nbsp; Someone could delete or replace part of your archive and you won&rsquo;t have automatic assurance against file tampering. </li>\r\n<li><strong>Consider file types: </strong>Currently it can be a challenge to open an AmiPro word processing file or even a Lotus 1-2-3 spreadsheet file &ndash; both common formats 15 years ago. </li>\r\n<li><strong>A robust storage media:</strong> There is a risk that your disc(s) will become corrupted or damaged, making your files inaccessible.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>A good EDRMS addresses these problems, but there are some key questions to ask your provider:</p>\r\n<h3>Some documents must be retained for many years and may outlive your means of opening them (your EDRMS).</h3>\r\n<p>Like any other business purchase, you should consider the solution lifecycle and what you&rsquo;ll do at the end of that useful life. &nbsp;You may also ask about the future plans for your chosen EDRMS.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>So, if your EDRMS does become obsolete, can you extract, open and read the files stored within it - and move them to a new system?</h3>\r\n<p>This is pretty much covered with scanned images &ndash; the formats are well  understood and commonly used.&nbsp; I may live to regret this, but I would  expect to be able to read a CCITT Group4 compressed TIFF file with  standard software 30+ years from now.</p>\r\n<h3>What about older digital formats, such as AmiPro or  Lotus?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Well, you could convert these to Word and Excel but that risks  those products also being out-competed. In this case you would have to  migrate again &hellip; and again.&nbsp; At each conversion, you risk the file  changing &ndash; for example, the fonts used in the original may not be  available and an approximation will have to be made.</p>\r\n<p>The solution may be PDF/A format, a particular version of the Adobe PDF standard which is  designed for archiving. This subset is designed (and defined in  ISO19005-1:2005) to correctly  display the information held in that PDF/A file &ndash; without any external  dependencies.&nbsp; This would include the fonts required in that document,  so the information is always going to look as the author intended it.&nbsp;  The PDF/A specification is bound to also evolve over time and you may  need to perform some migrations, but you can be certain that you&rsquo;re  keeping the original appearance of the document. So use of PDF/A is  another question to be asking your software supplier. Your EDRMS can then provide the access control and traceability, whilst storing files in a form which will be accessible with you need them.</p>\r\n<h3>Hardware</h3>\r\n<p>On the subject of obsolete technology, it&rsquo;s also worth mentioning storage media at this point.&nbsp; Maybe 10 or so years ago, the storage technology of choice for archiving was something called &ldquo;write once optical media&rdquo; &ndash; or WORM drive. These sounded great, because the media was specified to last for at least 50 years - great for long term archiving.</p>\r\n<p>The problem was, the drives clearly weren&rsquo;t going to last that long, and there were compatibility issues with PCs used to control those drives. This mix of compatibility issues left no standard format for the data on disc and we found that customers needed to migrate all their data to new discs every 5 years, so that they knew they could read the data reliably. So much for 50 years of media life ...</p>\r\n<p>Now that the market has moved on, this technology is obsolete and pretty much everyone uses arrays of magnetic storage instead. But this is a hard-won lesson to guard against manufacturer-specific hardware, however well-intentioned the design may be. Your platform choice should allow growth and migration at a sensible cost.</p>\r\n<h2>Summary</h2>\r\n<p>Long term document retention is a matter of planning for the future. It is notoriously difficult to predict future events and requirements but there are a couple of basic rules which can avoid major trouble and expense:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select a solution that supports whatever you put into your archive on the first day, making it usable on the last day &ndash; without degradation or expensive maintenance work.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Plan for the day when the system will need replacement and consider how you will transfer your archived data to the next system. This is going to happen many times as technology advances throughout the lifetime of your information archive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>About Neil Maude</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../assets/articles/113/contained_images/8d9e8419f6d7_180_NeilM_ws.jpg?1359557446" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Electronic Document Management General Manager<br />Tel: 0844 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:neilM@arenagroup.net">neilM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Neil joined the Arena Group in 2006 and has almost 20 years of   experience in the electronic document management industry, working with   both private and public sector customers.&nbsp; Neil sits on Arena&rsquo;s board  of  directors and manages the delivery operations of Arena&rsquo;s EDM  business.&nbsp;  His team spend their time developing software, implementing  solutions  for customers and providing after-sales software support  services, both  in the UK and internationally.</p>\r\n<h2>Related Features</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/163">Confidential files left on trains, in the wrong hands, on the move?</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store, software for document management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../case_studies?service=Electronic+Document+Management" target="_blank">Case studies: <strong>m</strong>store in practice</a></p>', '2014-01-23', 'iStock_000033885734Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 400735, '2014-01-28 09:59:49', 'Document Archive', '2014-01-23 17:20:19', '2015-03-31 14:55:45', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'future-proofing-a-large-document-archive'),
(185, 'Kyocera’s brand new application makes surveys a doddle!', 'Quick, efficient and accurate surveys administered entirely from the touch screen on your Kyocera device.', '<p class="introduction">Kyocera&rsquo;s brand new application transforms a Kyocera Multi-Function Printer into an on-demand questionnaire creating, result gathering, analysis hub for multiple choice questionnaires and surveys.</p>\r\n<p>As the name suggests, <em>Teaching Assistant</em> is ideal for educational facilities to enable on-demand testing; but its application is far from limited to that. With uses ranging from gathering tenant feedback for housing associations to customer questionnaires for travel companies; it is advantageous for any organisation handling high volumes of testing or feedback surveys.</p>\r\n<h2>What does it do?</h2>\r\n<p>Streamlining the task of printing, recording and analysing multiple choice surveys; <em>Teaching Assistant</em> helps to prepare, conduct and report on surveys quickly and accurately.</p>\r\n<p>This application can be installed to many standard Kyocera multi-function devices. It is managed directly from the device&rsquo;s touch screen so does not require any IT resources or support.</p>\r\n<p>The survey can be created directly on the device and printed without the need for expensive, pre-printed media. Once completed, <em>Teaching Assistant</em> automatically collates the data in seconds, helping to eliminate human error and returning accurate results. Comprehensive statistics are automatically generated and compiled into ready-to-use reports.</p>\r\n<p>There is also a Plug-in which enables <em>Teaching Assistant</em> to place survey results into MS Excel; even including a space on your spread sheet against open ended questions requiring further feedback.</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;What are the benefits?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Increased productivity </strong>&ndash; automated collation of multiple-choice questionnaires and surveys, saving time by providing instant feedback.<br /> <br /> </li>\r\n<li><strong>Improved marking accuracy </strong>&ndash; Reducing the possibility of human error.<br /> <br /> </li>\r\n<li><strong>Reduced IT burden </strong>&ndash; no need for complicated IT intervention, dedicated server software or online survey providers.<br /> <br /> </li>\r\n<li><strong>Lower costs</strong> &ndash; Surveys can be printed in-house without the need for expensive, pre-printed media or external suppliers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/185/contained_images/993434ad13ae_259_Teaching Assistant_Infosheet_KDS_Final.jpg?1390906748" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="680" /></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../web/contact_us" target="_blank">Contact us</a> for more information about this new software or any of our services.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>', '2014-01-27', 'ExamPaper_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 128329, '2014-12-11 13:40:14', '', '2014-01-28 10:59:37', '2014-12-11 13:40:14', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'kyocera’s-brand-new-application-makes-surveys-a-doddle'),
(186, 'Arena Group retains Microsoft’s Gold standard', 'Arena has retained the Microsoft Partner Network Gold competency in Application Development along with Silver Midmarket Solution and Silver Server Platform.', '<p class="introduction">To retain the Gold Certification, Arena has met certain standards by proving technological expertise through exams and customer testimonials referencing successful projects.</p>\r\n<p>Microsoft Gold Partners receive a host of support in areas ranging from planning and training, to support. Possibly most exciting is that Arena receives internal licenses for new Microsoft software. This allows Arena&rsquo;s experts to test out Microsoft products and pass on first-hand knowledge and better informed advice to customers.</p>\r\n<p>A dedicated Microsoft contact and unlimited access to Microsoft&rsquo;s Partner Learning Center ensures that Arena can offer the most up-to-date support. This is informed by the latest knowledge and training, along with access to technical resources and developer tools.</p>\r\n<p>All of this means that you can be assured that Arena staff can tackle even the most complex issues, with extensive training and support from Microsoft&rsquo;s experts if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>To retain Microsoft Platform Ready certification, Arena had to provide evidence of customer tested, packaged software solutions, along with participation in the Customer Satisfaction Index. This tested both Arena&rsquo;s technical capability and customer satisfaction levels.</p>\r\n<p>This recognition from Microsoft reflects Arena&rsquo;s commitment to employee development and the extensive testing done to maintain the exceptional quality of Arena&rsquo;s offering and customer support.</p>\r\n<p>Neil Maude, Arena''s Gener Manager, explains how the maintenance of the MS certification benefits users of <a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management"><strong>m</strong>store, Arena''s software for electronic document and records management</a>;</p>\r\n<p>"Our customers rely on <strong>m</strong>store as a critical tool to bring efficiency to their organisations so it is essential that we keep pace with the relentless change in the modern IT environment. This independent certification from Microsoft gives our customers peace of mind that our products continue to operate reliably and securely on the latest IT platforms. We''re proud to retain our product certification on this new level and give assurances to our customers that they will enjoy the significant value of <strong>m</strong>store; now and into the future."</p>', '2014-02-11', 'MSFT_logo_Web.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 61526, '2014-02-20 14:20:32', '', '2014-02-11 16:55:35', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-group-retains-microsoft’s-gold-standard'),
(187, 'Welcoming staff to our brand new North East office', 'With over 60 years’ of experience in document management between them, Ken and Mark bring a raft of knowledge to Arena.', '<p class="introduction">With over 60 years&rsquo; of experience in document management between them, Ken and Mark bring a raft of knowledge to Arena, gleaned from running their own businesses and working with some of the industry&rsquo;s largest players.</p>\r\n<p>Working from Arena&rsquo;s brand new North East office in Durham Tees Business  Centre, both Mark and Ken will be focusing on a variety of sectors for  Arena&rsquo;s North East operation, supporting the expansion of a growing  client base.</p>\r\n<p>Mark&rsquo;s attention was drawn to Arena when he noticed the business taking on new clients in the North East. &nbsp;&ldquo;It was clear to me that Arena was expanding quite fast and I was impressed by what I heard about their high service standards and ethical practices. Arena&rsquo;s reputation gave me such a good feeling, I wanted to be a part of their success.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Ken&rsquo;s motivation was very similar, he also cites Arena&rsquo;s ethical stance as a key influencer; &ldquo;joining Arena was an easy call. I wanted to be with an ethical company, and after meeting with some of the senior management team it was clear that this was the right place for me. It has a really friendly, family feel - what you see is what you get.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;If your business is based in the North East, why not give them a call?</p>\r\n<h5>Pictured: Ken Cross (left) / Mark Williams (right)</h5>', '2014-02-17', '0695.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 171371, '2014-02-12 09:48:49', '', '2014-02-12 09:48:56', '2015-08-06 08:03:10', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'welcoming-staff-to-our-brand-new-north-east-office'),
(188, 'Mobile printing made easier', 'We’ve been taking a look at some of the more recent applications on the market that can help you get a file from your mobile device and onto paper.', '<p class="introduction">Have you ever had the frustrating experience of having a document or web page displayed on your mobile phone or tablet and no quick way of printing it?</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve been taking a look at some of the more recent applications on the market that can help you get a file from your mobile device and onto paper.</p>\r\n<h2>Apple Devices running iOS 4 or later</h2>\r\n<p>The more recent Toshiba and Kyocera devices natively support Apple''s AirPrint feature. AirPrint enables instant printing from iPad, iPhone or iPod touch without the need to install drivers or download software. Simply connect to the same wireless network that the printer is connected to, select the appropriate AirPrint printer on your device and choose print. It''s that simple.</p>\r\n<p>AirPrint offers the user various output settings, allowing you to select the number of copies, double or single-sided pages, and so on - but don&rsquo;t expect advanced features such as stapling and folding to be available.</p>\r\n<h2>Android OS</h2>\r\n<p>When printing from the Android operating system, the appropriate Toshiba or Kyocera printing app must be downloaded from the Google Play Store.</p>\r\n<p>It is worth making the download though as, dependent on the model and configuration of your mobile device and printer; these features may be available when using the app:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Private PIN release printing</li>\r\n<li>Scanning capability </li>\r\n<li>Ability to associate a print job with a department code </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Toshiba&rsquo;s printing app can be downloaded here:</h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.toshiba.dse.ebridge.acme.paid&amp;hl=en_GB">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.toshiba.dse.ebridge.acme.paid&amp;hl=en_GB</a></p>\r\n<h3>Kyocera&rsquo;s printing App can be downloaded here:</h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.kyocera.kyoprint&amp;hl=en_GB">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.kyocera.kyoprint&amp;hl=en_GB</a></p>\r\n<h2>What if I&rsquo;m not on the same network or I need to account for the prints that are being produced?</h2>\r\n<p>No problem, we have solutions that can cope with this requirement. Just give us a call and we can advise on the best way forward.</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="mailto:news@arenagroup.net">Contact us</a> to find out more about printing from mobile devices, monitoring and  controlling print and copy output, digitising your paper-driven  processes or implementing an electronic document management system.</p>\r\n<p>Visit us to see a demonstration of mobile printing and output control in action. <a href="../../../articles/95">Our next open day</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Related articles</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/managing-the-&acirc;??bring-your-own-device&acirc;??-byod-challenge?tag=Expert+News">Tackling the ''Bring your own device'' (BYOD) challenge</a></p>', '2014-11-10', 'iPadSplurge_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 106128, '2014-12-11 13:34:44', '', '2014-02-13 10:23:04', '2015-02-06 16:34:31', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'mobile-printing-made-easier'),
(189, 'Andrew Jones MP visits Arena', 'Ahead of Apprenticeship Week, Arena has had a visit from a VIP guest.', '<p><strong>Andrew Jones, MP for Harrogate and Knaresborough, dropped by  to chat with us and our apprentices. Along with many other roles, he is  the Apprenticeship Ambassador for Parliament.</strong></p>\r\n<p>With many of Arena&rsquo;s former apprentices now in management positions and current apprentices in Service, IT and Admin; Andrew was particularly interested to discuss our apprenticeship programme.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I was keen to hear about Arena&rsquo;s successes; especially hearing how many people have joined through the apprenticeship scheme, what they have achieved and are still achieving.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Arena&rsquo;s expansion to date has been impressive; it is great to see apprentices playing such a key part in the growth of the business.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>I am always looking at the challenges faced within the recruitment system to see how we can make it easier to bring more apprentices into employment.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>Andrew was particularly focussed on how the learning opportunities for apprentices benefit both the candidates themselves, and the company.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Apprenticeships present a proven route towards improving skills in the workforce and give British businesses a real competitive edge. Working with apprentices is mutually beneficial in that the apprentice learns whilst they are employed, and they develop a way of working that is tailored to your company. </em></p>\r\n<p><em>The result of this is a motivated and skilled employee ready to form a valuable part of the team for the future.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>As discussed in the <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/feb/05/twelve-applications-every-apprenticeship-minister-matthew-hancock">Guardian</a>, there has been a sharp increase in the number of apprenticeship vacancies in the UK. However, there has been an even larger increase in applications with an average of 12 applications for every position.</p>\r\n<p>Andrew is visiting companies like Arena as he aims to increase the number of companies taking on apprentices, and the number of people becoming apprentices. The key to this is increasing awareness about the benefits of the scheme.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;The government identified apprenticeships as a key way to fill the nation&rsquo;s skills gap. Apprentice numbers are growing significantly, with a wider range of opportunities and increased financial support from the government.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>The aim is to show more people that apprenticeships could work for them; equally to communicate the benefits to businesses. </em></p>\r\n<p><em>More exposure and publicity can help to make people more aware of the successes of apprenticeships both corporately and personally.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>By improving the brand image of apprenticeships we can encourage greater participation and celebrate the successes.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>Thanks to Andrew for visiting us here at Armitage House, we hope to speak again soon.</p>\r\n<h4>Andrew Jones pictured (L) speaking with Mick Harrison, Arena''s Group Services Manager (R).</h4>\r\n<p>For further information on our apprenticeship scheme, visit our website: <a href="../../page/apprenticeship-programme">http://www.arenagroup.net/page/apprenticeship-programme</a></p>\r\n<p>Link to Guardian article: <a href="http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/feb/05/twelve-applications-every-apprenticeship-minister-matthew-hancock">http://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/feb/05/twelve-applications-every-apprenticeship-minister-matthew-hancock</a></p>', '2014-02-16', '0812.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 203615, '2014-02-17 10:16:44', '', '2014-02-17 10:16:50', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'andrew-jones-mp-visits-arena'),
(190, 'Squeaky-clean future for Morrish Solicitors LLP', 'Over recent years many businesses have been negotiating the economic landscape with stretched profit margins, lean budgets and a keen focus on survival. Investment in the green agenda has, perhaps understandably, taken a back seat for many and its resurgence is surely a sign of recovery. One business making serious strides in this area is Morrish Solicitors LLP. ', '<p class="introduction">Over recent years many businesses have been negotiating the economic landscape with stretched profit margins, lean budgets and a keen focus on survival. Investment in the green agenda has, perhaps understandably, taken a back seat for many and its resurgence is surely a sign of recovery. One business making serious strides in this area is Morrish Solicitors LLP.</p>\r\n<p>An office move by <a href="http://www.morrishsolicitors.com/" target="_blank">Morrish Solicitors LLP</a> saw the introduction of low energy lighting, recycling of old hardware from the previous site and company policies refreshed to acknowledge the environment. Perhaps the biggest move towards a greener operation though, is evident in the practice&rsquo;s print and copy strategy.</p>\r\n<p>Morrish renewed a contract with Arena Group Ltd to replace its printers and copiers with upgraded machines. New Toshiba models were chosen for their low energy consumption and for the fact that they are carbon offset. This means that the CO2 produced in their manufacture and transport, and the estimated print and copy output for the contract period, has been offset with a contribution towards a carbon reduction initiative. In this case, it funds energy efficient cooking stoves in Africa under a scheme coordinated by carbon offsetting expert, co2balance. Through this process the emissions are balanced to become "Carbon Zero" with no detrimental effect on the environment. Morrish went a step further, purchasing additional credits from co2balance to carbon neutralise its Kyocera machines under the same scheme.</p>\r\n<p>Paul Scholey, Partner at Morrish Solicitors, comments; &ldquo;every business has a responsibility to keep its carbon footprint to a minimum.&nbsp;To really walk the walk you need to look at all of your buying decisions with that in mind &ndash; it&rsquo;s an approach we&rsquo;re trying to adopt across the board, and we&rsquo;re sure that our clients approve.&nbsp; It doesn&rsquo;t have to cost an arm and a leg to be proactive with your CSR policies.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The output of the machines has also been considered from an environmental perspective. Defaults on the printers are set to reduce wasteful and unnecessary print practices, limiting colour output and one-sided pages. This minimises paper consumption and ensures economic use of toner whilst preventing Morrish&rsquo;s recycling bins from over-flowing. This is not only environmentally aware but has a positive impact on the financial cost of running the machines.</p>\r\n<p>Jaime Lockwood, IT Manager at Morrish adds; &ldquo;In today&rsquo;s economic and environmental climate, just being good at what we do is not enough.&nbsp;It&rsquo;s our social responsibility to ensure that we are also as environmentally aware as possible. Our clients understand that everyone needs to try that little bit harder and they want to work with firms that are also looking to make a difference. Fortunately, Arena is like-minded and through working with them we have managed to deliver a solution that provides the best of <em>all </em>worlds - a fast and efficient quality print solution that is also carbon neutral.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Looking to the future, Paul Scholey tells us that Morrish is currently considering an environmental audit of its entire operation with a view to reducing its carbon footprint even further. Watch this space!</p>\r\n<h2>Related Articles</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/print-control">Putting the brakes on wasteful and unnecessary printing</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/160">Erasable printing is here!</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/47">Getting greener with Arena</a></p>\r\n<h5>PICTURED: Jaime Lockwood, IT Manager (L) and Paul Scholey, Partner (R) - Morrish Solicitors LLP<strong>&nbsp;</strong></h5>', '2014-02-20', 'Green appeal 006.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 133947, '2014-02-20 17:06:12', 'Morrish Solicitors LLP', '2014-02-20 17:06:21', '2014-10-27 08:29:40', 3, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'squeaky-clean-future-for-morrish-solicitors-llp'),
(194, 'Kids in Leeds are making ready to get snappy!', 'Up to 1,500 big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of Leeds in May to take on a free fun run challenge in aid of charity. They will be taking part in the annual Arena Group Leeds Junior and Mini Run, which is organised by Jane Tomlinson’s Run For All and takes place on the same day as the Leeds Half Marathon.', '<p class="introduction">Up to 1,500 big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of Leeds in May to take on a free fun run challenge in aid of charity. They will be taking part in the annual Arena Group Leeds Junior and Mini Run, which is organised by Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s Run For All and takes place on the same day as the Leeds Half Marathon.</p>\r\n<p>The mini and junior run is now in its sixth year and, Arena Group''s sponsorship makes it the biggest free mass participation children&rsquo;s event in Yorkshire.</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s run is being held on <strong>Sunday 11<sup>th </sup>May</strong>. There are two distances &ndash; 2.5km for youngsters aged 9-14 and 1.5km for children 3-8, with both routes finishing alongside the city&rsquo;s landmark Millennium Square. All finishers receive a medal.</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part are encouraged to raise a small amount of money for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal or another charity of their choice. This year the appeal is supporting Leeds-based charity <a href="http://www.snaps-vol.org.uk/index.html" target="_blank">SNAPS</a>, which helps children with special needs and their families. It currently supports over 350 families each year.</p>\r\n<p>The charity provides practical help and advice for families and stages hydrotherapy and drop-in sessions at the Penny Field School in Meanwood.</p>\r\n<p>SNAPS general manager Angela Furminger said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re thrilled to have been chosen as the benefitting charity for this year&rsquo;s Arena Group Mini and Junior Run. Whatever the youngsters raise &ndash; big or small &ndash; will make a huge difference to our families.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, Arena''s MD, says: &ldquo;We are delighted to continue our sponsorship of such a great event. It''s gratifying that our support allows children to enter for free. It is always heartening to see so many youngsters taking on a challenge to help others and we hope SNAPS receives a big boost from the event to help it with its excellent work.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Mini and Junior Run event lead Lynne Preston said: &ldquo;The mini and junior runs are a brilliant way for kids to get actively involved on half-marathon day and enjoy the thrill of being cheered on by crowds of spectators.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Both runs attract youngsters of all abilities and all those who take part should be very proud that local good causes benefit thanks to their efforts.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To enter the Arena Group Leeds Mini and Junior Run please go to <a href="http://www.runforall.com">www.runforall.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/articles/194/contained_images/147f3954b371_260_Junior_RFA_Leeds.jpg?1393939701" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2014-03-05', 'Launch Pic SNAPS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 49755, '2014-03-05 14:22:33', '', '2014-03-04 13:28:20', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'kids-in-leeds-are-making-ready-to-get-snappy'),
(195, 'Arena crowned Employer of the Year for the second time!', 'Arena has once again been announced as an ‘Employer of the Year’ at this year''s Leeds Apprenticeship Awards. This is the second year in succession that we have won this award in the category for medium sized businesses.', '<p class="introduction">Arena has once again been announced as an &lsquo;Employer of the Year&rsquo; at this year''s Leeds Apprenticeship Awards. This is the second year in succession that we have won this award in the category for medium sized businesses.</p>\r\n<p>The judges were particularly impressed with the quality of training provided, making favourable comments regarding the skills that are transferred to our apprentices and the career development paths that are available to them.</p>\r\n<p>Martin Wright, Group HR Manager at Arena commented;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;the award is testimony to the quality of all our apprentices (past and present) and the staff who work to develop them.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>This is another pleasing accolade for Arena &ndash; let&rsquo;s see if we can get the hat-trick next year!</p>\r\n<h2>Related features:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/181"><strong>Evie: </strong>Admin apprentice</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/182"><strong>Mark: </strong>IT apprentice</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/180"><strong>Tom: </strong>Service apprentice</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/apprenticeship-programme">Arena''s Apprenticeship Academy</a></p>', '2014-03-05', 'IMG_0249.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 119384, '2014-03-05 10:53:16', '', '2014-03-05 10:53:25', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-crowned-employer-of-the-year-for-the-second-time'),
(196, 'Meet our Customer Relationship Managers', 'You may have recently received a visit from one of our Customer Relationship Managers (CRMs). Tasked with traveling around our existing client base, our CRMs are there to speedily handle any queries and make sure that your business is getting maximum value in return for your investment in Arena.', '<h2><strong>Why does Arena have the CRM team?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>As our business continues to grow we want to make sure that our existing clients get the attention and high level of service that they are used to. Our service team and account managers are willing and happy to respond to customer queries but the CRM role is dedicated to servicing our customers proactively through face-to-face visits.</p>\r\n<p>We have found that our clients appreciate the time a CRM can offer to them to make sure the service we are providing is up-to-scratch.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Meet our customer relationship managers</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://thewire.arenagroup.net/uploads/user/image/397/show_0011_small.jpg" alt="Show_0011_small" /></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Claire Mclean</strong></h2>\r\n<p><br /> Claire manages the CRM team. She joined Arena in January 2011 and has since made an average of 400 annual client visits. Claire joined Arena from a sales background and loves her customer facing service role, commenting;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I&rsquo;m proud to lead the CRM team, top class service has always been a priority for Arena and this team plays a key part in that. I think our customers appreciate that we are constantly looking to learn about the challenges they face and find ways to improve the service they receive from Arena.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://thewire.arenagroup.net/uploads/user/image/325/show_John_20Clark.jpg" alt="Show_john_20clark" /></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>John Clark</strong></h2>\r\n<p>John is an experienced member of the CRM team, having joined in August 2011. He has been with Arena since 2005, previously working as an account manager. John enjoys hearing how Arena is helping our customers, saying;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I enjoy visiting clients purely with customer service in mind. The feedback they offer helps us to understand how to make improvements to the service we provide. I am here to listen to them, to find out the challenges they are facing as a business and in their industry so that we may improve our value to them.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong><strong><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../../assets/articles/196/contained_images/4f004c31779b_278_Laura Edwards Apr 15 crop.jpg?1430140060" alt="Show_lauraedwards" width="227" height="270" /></strong></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Laura Edwards</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Although the newest member of the CRM team, Laura has worked in the document industry since 2009 in various customer-facing roles. Laura enjoys building long-term relationships with customers, commenting;</p>\r\n<p><em>"I am passionate about delivering high standards of customer service to our clients. I constantly build a relationship with customers to have a clear understanding of their needs and expectations. This helps us to improve the customer service they receive from Arena - and to allow their businesses to continue to thrive."</em></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Would you like to request a CRM visit?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Our CRMs are constantly moving around our customer base but maybe you&rsquo;d like to see them soon, in which case please give us a call on 0844 863 8000 or email <a href="mailto:marketing@arenagroup.net">marketing@arenagroup.net</a>.</p>', '2015-04-28', '87_CRM_Pic.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 269879, '2015-04-27 13:13:21', '', '2014-03-26 16:25:20', '2015-04-28 14:47:49', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'meet-our-customer-relationship-managers--2'),
(197, 'Visit us at the ACE Credit Union Services Conference', 'Arena will be at the ACE Credit Union Services Conference in Newport on 9-10th May. Visit us to see our mstore for Credit Unions software.', '<p class="introduction">Meet the Arena team next month at the ACE Credit Union Services Conference&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will be showcasing our copy and print devices along with Arena''s Electronic Document and Records Management software (EDRMS): <strong>m</strong>store for Credit Unions.</p>\r\n<p>Speak with our team about cutting costs and increasing efficiencies in the area of print, copy. We can also show you how to reduce your reliance on paper, whilst ensuring legal compliance using <strong>m</strong>store.</p>\r\n<p>A presentation from our document management experts, Tim Lancelot and Dan Lancaster, will also feature on the conference agenda.</p>\r\n<h2>Visit our stand for your chance to win&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>We will be offering visitors a chance to win a set of Kyocera ceramic knives!</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<h3>Venue:</h3>\r\n<p>Hilton Hotel, Newport</p>\r\n<h3>Date:</h3>\r\n<p>9th May: 2-5pm | 10th May: 9am-2.45pm.</p>\r\n<p><strong></strong><a href="../../../page/arena-in-credit-unions">About <strong>m</strong>store for Credit Unions</a><a href="../../../page/arena-in-credit-unions"></a></p>\r\n<h2>Downloads</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/91_ARENA_mstoreCUNIONS.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>m</strong>store for Credit Unions leaflet</a></p>', '2014-04-27', 'conference-speaker.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 171423, '2014-04-23 15:36:08', '', '2014-03-31 10:45:33', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'visit-us-at-the-ace-credit-union-services-conference'),
(198, 'Meet us at PfH Live/ CIH Housing 2014 - Stand P66', 'Did you know that Arena is PfH’s number 1 nominated supplier for the provision of Photocopiers, Printers, Multi-Functional Devices (MFDs) and Office Based Managed Print Services (MPS)? Meet us on stand P66 at PfH Live 2014, Manchester Central on 24-26th June.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group is PfH&rsquo;s number 1 nominated  supplier for the provision   of  Photocopiers, Printers, Multi-Functional  Devices (MFDs) and Office    Based Managed Print Services (MPS). Meet us at PfH Live!</p>\r\n<p>We will be showcasing our hardware and software for print management  and our managed print service (MPS). Meet us at PfH Live on <strong>24th - 26th June, Manchester Central, stand P66</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Arena staff will be on hand to  discuss electronic document management and how consumers can combine  technology to reduce costs, drive efficiency and improve  sustainability.</p>\r\n<p>We''ll also be demonstrating mobile printing - visit our stand and we''ll show you how to print from a tablet or your mobile phone.</p>\r\n<h2>Visit us on stand P66 to enter our prize draw</h2>\r\n<p>On our stand we will be offering visitors the chance to win Toshiba tablets and ceramic knives from Kyocera!</p>\r\n<h2>Register for your FREE delegate pass:</h2>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.speeddata.co.uk/ExhibitorGuests/Housing.aspx?EGRef=PFH35P65" target="_blank">http://www.speeddata.co.uk/ExhibitorGuests/Housing.aspx?EGRef=PFH35P65</a></h3>\r\n<h2>Arena''s No. 1 position on the PfH Framework</h2>\r\n<p>PfH specialises in improving procurement practice for over 800 social housing providers throughout the UK.</p>\r\n<p>Arena  is PfH&rsquo;s number 1 nominated supplier for the provision of   Photocopiers,  Printers, Multi-Functional Devices (MFDs) and Office   Based Managed  Print Services (MPS). To win this position Arena was put through a  stringent tender process that compared us with a long list of our competitors. This process scrutinised many criteria including our prices, service performance and quality, product and service portfolio and value for money.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue">Our no. 1 position confirms that our  products and services are of   the highest standard and we offer  exceptional value to our clients.</p>\r\n<h2>About the show<strong><br /></strong></h2>\r\n<p>The  Chartered Institute of Housing&rsquo;s Annual Exhibition is the UK&rsquo;s  ultimate housing experience focusing on the provision of affordable  housing and the development of sustainable communities. For the&nbsp;third  year running, Procurement For Housing has partnered with CIH to host PfH  Live under the same roof.</p>\r\n<p>Arena will be exhibiting alongside over  300 of the sector&rsquo;s leading providers, partners and suppliers as they  showcase the latest products and services in the housing and  regeneration sector. Free seminars will give delegates an opportunity to  share best practice and solutions to current and future sector  challenges.</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.procurementforhousing.co.uk/insight-and-opinion/pfh-live-2014/">www.procurementforhousing.co.uk</a></p>\r\n<h2>Join the discussion</h2>\r\n<p>Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/ArenaGroup" target="_blank">@ArenaGroup</a> / <a href="http://twitter.com/PfHLive2014" target="_blank">@PfHLive2014</a></p>', '2014-03-31', 'pfhlive2014.gif', 'image/gif', 12656, '2014-03-31 12:40:54', '', '2014-03-31 12:40:54', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'meet-us-at-pfh-live-cih-housing-2014-stand-p66'),
(199, 'Caring kids get set to tackle Arena Group York Mini and Junior Run', 'Hundreds of big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of York in August to take on a free fun run challenge in aid of charity.', '<p class="introduction">Hundreds of big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of York in August to take on a free fun run challenge in aid of charity.</p>\r\n<p>They will be taking part in the annual Arena Group York Mini and Junior Run, which is organised by Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s Run For All for children of all abilities.</p>\r\n<p>Arena is proud to be sponsoring the Mini and Junior Run for the fifth  year, once again funding entry fees for every participant. The event has become a popular fixture in the sporting calendar  for thousands of children and families and is a great family day out in  support of a very worthy cause. The mini and junior run is one of the biggest races of its kind in the region and entry is free for all.</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s run will be held at 11.45am on Sunday August 3rd. There are two distances &ndash; 2.5km for youngsters aged 9-14 and 1.5km for children aged 3-8 &ndash; with both routes finishing on Knavesmire Road near the racecourse. Mini run participants must be accompanied around the route by an adult.</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part are encouraged to raise a small amount of money for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal or another charity of their choice. This year the appeal is supporting <a href="http://www.yorkcarerscentre.co.uk/content/young-carers" target="_blank">York Carers Centre&rsquo;s Young Carers&rsquo; Service,</a> which supports children aged between 8 and 18 who help care for a parent or sibling with either a physical or mental illness.</p>\r\n<p>The service also provides excursions, often the only break the children get from the daily pressures of being a young carer.</p>\r\n<p>Senior young carer worker Liz Langwade said: &ldquo;While we get some core funding, all our activities are paid for by fundraising and donations. To have been chosen to benefit from the Mini and Junior Run is brilliant and will make such a difference to the lives of young carers in York.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mini and Junior Run event lead Keith Taylor said: &ldquo;Both runs attract youngsters of all abilities and all those who take part should be very proud that local good causes benefit thanks to their efforts.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To enter the York Mini and Junior run visit <a href="http://www.runforall.com" target="_blank">www.runforall.com</a></p>', '2014-04-09', 'York Launch Photo York Young Carers Apr14.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 42567, '2014-04-09 12:15:26', 'York Young Carers', '2014-04-09 12:15:27', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'caring-kids-get-set-to-tackle-arena-group-york-mini-and-junior-run');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(200, 'How secure is your toner?', 'You may have spotted some recent cases in the news about unscrupulous employees fraudulently ordering and selling printer consumables for personal gain. Arena Group’s Professional Services Manager, Ian Fox, shares his advice on how best to keep track of your organisation’s supplies whilst safeguarding your budgets.', '<p class="introduction">A few high profile court cases have recently made the headlines, following fraud convictions against individuals ordering excess amounts of printer toner and ink &ndash; in one case, even buying supplies for printers their employer did not own &ndash; and selling it online. This activity went on for several years, earning the culprit an estimated &pound;90k before a small mistake prompted suspicion and uncovered the fraud.</p>\r\n<p>Although this is unlikely to be a widespread issue, many businesses have no way of tracking their consumption of such items, so it can be easy for corrupt behaviour to go on undetected. This is especially the case for businesses stocking large amounts of toner in an effort to ensure they never run out.</p>\r\n<h2>Do you have a store room full of toner and consumables?</h2>\r\n<p>Toner is expensive, often costing several hundred pounds to fully stock one printer or multi-function device (that&rsquo;s the big printer, scanner, copier and fax machine sitting in your office). If you own inkjet printers you&rsquo;ll find cartridges are even more expensive; it&rsquo;s a little known fact - although perhaps not surprising; that <a href="../../../articles/107">inkjet ink is more expensive than Dom Perignon champagne</a>!</p>\r\n<p>You might have a stock room full of the stuff, so it&rsquo;s a good basic step to keep an itinerary that details how much is ordered. This will help you to track your consumption and forecast spending. It can also evidence that the right products are purchased and that they are used appropriately.</p>\r\n<h2>Who looks after your printers?</h2>\r\n<p>If you buy your own printers and manage maintenance and related consumables in-house then you are more at risk from underhand behaviour. However, if your printers are leased and managed under a service contract then you benefit from third party protection. This is because you will be ordering consumables from your provider, who will notice if you are requesting more than you need &ndash; and will only supply the appropriate products for your printers. A good provider will endeavour to avoid over-supplying in an effort to manage their own costs.</p>\r\n<h2>Considered a Managed Print Service (MPS)?</h2>\r\n<p>This is the ultimate weapon in your armoury against over-spending on print and copy. Your printers will be managed by a service provider who will bundle your machines, consumables and service together into one, agreed, regular bill. So, - no more surprises!</p>\r\n<p>Even better, your machine will send an automatic alert to your provider when it is running low on toner &ndash; and you&rsquo;ll receive a new cartridge &lsquo;just in time&rsquo;. This means there is no need for anyone to spend time sourcing and ordering your consumables, and you don&rsquo;t need to keep a big stock on-site.</p>\r\n<p>Taking this a step further, installing print control software on your machines will afford you an even greater degree of transparency and control. This lets you report on exactly what is printed, by whom and at what cost, and gives you additional tools to control user activity. <a href="../../../articles/112">Read more about print control in my related article</a>.</p>\r\n<p>So, regardless of the size of your business or the way you manage your printers, there are ways to manage your stock and spending on consumables.</p>\r\n<h3>About Ian Fox</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../..//assets/articles/200/contained_images/21ef27b5b1bc_276_Ian Fox Jan15 large.jpg?1422352750" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="131" height="131" align="LEFT" />Professional Services Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:ianF@arenagroup.net"></a><a href="mailto:ianf@arenagroup.net">IanF@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Ian Fox joined the Arena Group as a Systems Engineer in 1995. During his time at Arena he has gained a wealth of experience in helping organisations with their document related workflows. He now heads up the Professional Services department, which was formed in January 2011 with the aim of ensuring that existing and future Arena clients receive the best possible advice, solutions and support to enable them to manage and control their documents effectively.</p>\r\n<h2>Related articles</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../112"></a><a href="../../../articles/112">Putting the brakes on wasteful print and copy</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../133"></a><a href="../../../articles/133">VIDEO: BBC Watchdog on shrinking inkjet cartridges</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../130"></a><a href="../../../articles/130">INFOGRAPHIC: the process behind Arena&rsquo;s Managed Print Service</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../107"></a><a href="../../../articles/107">Printer ink pricier than champagne</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../81"></a><a href="../../../articles/81">Top tips for selecting a managed print service provider</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-04-22', 'PoliceLine_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 100842, '2014-12-11 15:32:02', '', '2014-04-22 15:31:02', '2015-02-02 10:22:37', 3, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'how-secure-is-your-toner'),
(201, 'Raising a cheer for the Leeds Arena Group Junior & Mini Runs', 'Sunday 11th May saw hundreds of youngsters take to the streets of Leeds to raise cash for local children''s charity SNAPS.', '<p class="introduction">Around 1500 youngsters got involved in this year''s Arena Group Junior and Mini Runs in Leeds.</p>\r\n<p>The mini and junior run is now in its sixth year. Arena Group''s  sponsorship makes it the biggest free mass participation children&rsquo;s  event in Yorkshire.</p>\r\n<p>This year''s event supports Leeds-based charity, <a href="http://www.snaps-vol.org.uk/index.html" target="_blank">SNAPS</a>, which helps children with special needs, and their families.</p>\r\n<h2>Congratulations to our winners!</h2>\r\n<p>The winner of the boys&rsquo; Junior Run &ndash; for 9 to 14 year olds &ndash; was Alex Wyke-Ulliott, 14, with Harvey Norden, 11, in 2<sup>nd</sup> and Keiran Roebuck, 13, in 3<sup>rd</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>Top of the tree for the girls&rsquo; was Alisha Laidler, 13, with Megan Driscoll, 13, in 2<sup>nd</sup> and Megan Wyke-Ulliott, 11, in 3<sup>rd</sup>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Congratulations also go to the winners of our Schools Team Challenge. First place in the Mini Run went to St Margaret''s C of E Primary School in Horsforth, whilst the Junior race was won by Cockburn School.</p>\r\n<p>Arena Group Managing Director Adrian Fitzpatrick said: &ldquo;It was great to see so many children taking part in the Leeds Mini and Junior Run. We are delighted that our sponsorship allows youngsters to run for free.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&ldquo;They all should be applauded for the great effort they have made and it is particularly pleasing to know that event has raised lots of money to support the excellent work of SNAPS.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>York Junior and Mini Runs - August 3rd</h2>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s York runs will be held at 11.45am on Sunday August 3rd. There  are two distances &ndash; 2.5km for youngsters aged 9-14 and 1.5km for  children aged 3-8 &ndash; with both routes finishing on Knavesmire Road near  the racecourse. Mini run participants must be accompanied around the  route by an adult. All finishers receive a medal.</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part are encouraged to raise a small amount of money  for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal or another charity of their choice. This  year the Appeal is supporting <a href="http://www.yorkcarerscentre.co.uk/content/young-carers" target="_blank">York Carers Centre&rsquo;s Young Carers&rsquo; Service,</a> which supports children aged between 8 and 18 who help care for a parent or sibling with either a physical or mental illness.</p>\r\n<h2>About Run For All</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Run For All is part of Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s lasting legacy. Jane Tomlinson CBE raised &pound;1.85m for children&rsquo;s and cancer charities before her untimely death from cancer aged just 43 in 2007. She made headlines across the world by competing in a series of epic endurance challenges from the London Marathon, ironman and triathlon competitions, to a 4,200 mile cycle ride across the width of the USA &ndash; despite being diagnosed with incurable cancer.</p>\r\n<p>Her family are now on course to take that total to &pound;5m in her memory.</p>', '2014-05-12', 'Photo_finish_1.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 112250, '2014-05-13 09:45:57', '', '2014-05-13 09:20:38', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'raising-a-cheer-for-the-leeds-arena-group-junior-mini-runs'),
(204, 'Is there a demon in your office?', 'Demon Printers are wreaking havoc in offices across the land! They come in many guises and can be tricky to spot. But don’t panic - help is at hand.', '<p class="introduction">Demon Printers are wreaking havoc in offices across the land! They come in many guises and can be tricky to spot. But don&rsquo;t panic - help is at hand.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ll start by showing you how to identify a problem printer, and then we&rsquo;ll help you to get rid of them for good.</p>\r\n<p>But first of all we&rsquo;d like you to <a href="../../demons">watch our video</a>, so you can see these demonic devices in action.</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../demons"><img src="../../..//assets/articles/204/contained_images/d0c37c03d129_264_ArenaGroup_DemonPrinters_Email_VideoPlayer-01.jpg?1401648445" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-05-30', 'ArenaGroup_DemonPrinters_Email_Eyes-01.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 100839, '2014-06-01 18:48:47', '', '2014-06-01 18:38:07', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'is-there-a-demon-in-your-office'),
(205, 'Arena Group makes tracks at Herd Farm', 'Arena has been back to Herd Farm. This time the volunteers took on work from flower arranging to laying a bike track.', '<p class="introduction">Arena has been back to Herd Farm. This time the volunteers took on work from flower arranging to laying a bike track.</p>\r\n<p>Educational resource centre, <a href="http://www.herdfarm.co.uk/" target="_blank">Herd Farm</a>, offers activities for young people including those at risk and with disabilities. The council run centre relies on help from volunteers to carry out some of the maintenance work.</p>\r\n<p>Arena frequently visit the centre to help out and, in our first visit of the year, the volunteers were kept busy as usual.</p>\r\n<p>To say the weather could have been better is an understatement. Right from the start it was pouring with rain so initially, the Herd Farm staff found tasks to do indoors.</p>\r\n<p>The day began with some good old fashioned housework. Schools stay overnight on visits and then the centre staff have a very short time frame to get the facilities ship shape, ready for the next school&rsquo;s arrival.</p>\r\n<p>Usually a daunting task for just one man, with all of the Arena volunteers hard at work, the buildings were sparkling in next to no time.&nbsp; The team, brushed, vacuumed, and mopped them into submission with only one tea break required!</p>\r\n<p>Our volunteers are a hardy bunch so the next step was outside to face the elements. Some prepared and planted hanging baskets whilst the others started on the bike path.</p>\r\n<p>The baskets were soon finished. They were prepared, filled with soil and then the flowers carefully arranged. Now the team were all united, working on the bike track.</p>\r\n<p>The track involved filling wheelbarrows and trundling down a windy path before pouring it on the roughly dug out track. Then it was spread and finally compressed using a buffer plate. The path was a challenge but nothing compared to the steep, muddy slope as Debs found out to the amusement of everyone else!</p>\r\n<p>All in all, a lot of hard but fulfilling work, and also a lot of fun &ndash; there were certainly a few aches around the Arena offices the next day!</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Do you need our CSR support?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>If you are a charity or community group in need of similar assistance, please contact Arena&rsquo;s CSR Coordinator, Debbie Burnell, on 0844 863 8000 or email <a href="mailto:DebbieB@arenagroup.net">DebbieB@arenagroup.net</a>.</p>\r\n<h3><strong><em>Pictured (L &ndash; R): Debbie Burnell, Ben Lockwood , Becki Oxtoby, Jess Jones, Billy Loxton, Mike Alsancak, John Speight.</em></strong></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>To learn more about Herd Farm, visit their website: <a href="http://www.herdfarm.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.herdfarm.co.uk/</a></em></p>', '2014-06-11', 'IMG_0318.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 142164, '2014-06-12 10:29:20', '', '2014-06-12 10:29:30', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-group-makes-tracks-at-herd-farm'),
(207, 'The top 6 reasons to outsource your print and copy management', 'Outsourcing is contracting a business function to an external party. Arena''s Gary Putson takes a look at the benefits of outsourcing your print and copy management. ', '<p class="introduction">Outsourcing is contracting a business function to an external party. Arena''s <strong>Gary Putson</strong> takes a look at the benefits of outsourcing your print and copy management.</p>\r\n<h2>Source expert support and resources</h2>\r\n<p>A specialist company will have the latest information on new software and hardware at its fingertips, offering you assurance that you will always have access to the best equipment to drive down costs and increase efficiencies in your business.</p>\r\n<p>Your provider&rsquo;s specialist team will be able to pass on the benefits from the latest training in both machine care and software, without the expense or time out needed for your staff to do any learning or research themselves.</p>\r\n<h2>Shine a light on areas for improvement and cost reduction</h2>\r\n<p>At the outset, an external company will assess your workforce&rsquo;s print and copy behaviour to report on costs and any inefficiencies that they can address. This initial investigation is without obligation to purchase anything. The provider will look at a broad array of things including which machines are most heavily used, associated energy consumption, the types of documents printed and so on, in addition to considering how to improve the maintenance of your devices, increase efficiency and cut costs. A comprehensive report is delivered to you with a proposed plan of action.</p>\r\n<h2>From installation, to support and maintenance &ndash; everything is taken care of</h2>\r\n<p>After installing a new system for you, consumables for your printers can be managed by your provider. Remote monitoring software means the end of ordering replacement toner as a new cartridge is despatched just as a current one is running out. This also means you no-longer need to store a supply of toner in your office.</p>\r\n<p>The machines themselves can also be monitored remotely so that engineers can arrive at your premises having already gathered information about the problem &ndash; leading to a quicker fix. Taking up a managed print service (MPS) means simplified billing too &ndash; as maintenance, consumables and printing are covered in one, regular, fixed cost.</p>\r\n<h2>Focus on your Core Business</h2>\r\n<p>Every business has finite resources and every employee has limited time. Outsourcing your print and copy management allows employees to stay focussed on core business needs rather than having their time taken up elsewhere.</p>\r\n<h2>Quickly Implement New Technology</h2>\r\n<p>Most managers will be able to give you a list of projects that they believe would greatly add value but will take significant resources, time and energy to implement. Often, a review of print and copy infrastructure falls into this category &ndash; we know it can deliver cost savings and efficiency benefits but the project itself can seem daunting. Outsourcing is a way to access the resources and expertise to make this innovation happen, removing the time consuming tasks of planning and implementation, hiring new people, or training existing staff by bringing in a qualified and experienced external team.</p>\r\n<h2>Improve performance</h2>\r\n<p>With one expert to oversee all of your print and copy requirements and resources, you can be certain that your infrastructure will be managed efficiently. At the outset your provider will audit your current situation and implement a plan to suit your business needs. Going forward their guidance and a dedicated service team will ensure that machines are kept well maintained and up to date, minimising down time.</p>\r\n<p>Often the alternative can involve different departments managing their own needs &ndash; which leads to uncontrolled costs, or an internal IT team that is run off its feet and unable to spend time on innovation.</p>\r\n<h3>About Gary Putson</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/207/contained_images/c03ee1fdd368_266_Gary Putson 0613.JPG?1404137254" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Group Sales Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:garyP@arenagroup.net">garyP@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Gary has worked with Arena for 8 years and has a long background in  sales, originating in the telecoms sector. Gary sits on Arena&rsquo;s board of  directors and manages Arena&rsquo;s growing Sales team of over thirty account  managers and telesellers. His team members spend their days consulting  with businesses across the country to deliver cost reduction, efficiency  savings and sustainability in all areas of document management.</p>', '2014-07-21', 'BrokenPrinterMan_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 93885, '2014-12-11 13:28:07', '', '2014-06-19 15:00:31', '2014-12-11 13:28:07', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'the-top-6-reasons-to-outsource-your-print-and-copy-management'),
(208, 'Growth in Grantham for Arena Group', 'Now that we have moved into our smart new Grantham offices, we''re on the lookout for local talent for our sales and service teams.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group has confirmed the creation of yet more new jobs to keep pace with its rapid and ongoing expansion in Grantham which saw it relocate into larger premises on Swinegate earlier this year.</p>\r\n<p>The company, which currently employs 17 people in Grantham, is now looking to strengthen the team with additional sales people and service engineers.</p>\r\n<p>Gary Putson, Group Sales Director, said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;ve been in Grantham for 3 years and we continue to go from strength to strength. The expansion of the team is a positive sign that we&rsquo;re heading in the right direction in line with our plans.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;By continuing to recruit local people, we&rsquo;re sending a very clear message that we&rsquo;re here, we&rsquo;re hungry for new business and we&rsquo;re committed to Grantham and investing in our business. We have a good, experienced team and want to add to it to continue to achieve our ambitious growth strategy.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s Grantham jobs boost comes following a number of important milestones for the firm so far this year. In February, it announced it was launching into the North East with the opening of a brand new regional office in Stockton-on-Tees, its sixth in the UK.</p>\r\n<p>In April, it was awarded Employer of the Year at the Leeds Apprenticeship Awards for the second year running, in recognition of its continued investment in the training of apprentices. Half of all service engineers currently employed by Arena have completed an apprenticeship programme while working at the company.</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, Managing Director at Arena Group, said: &ldquo;Our growth makes us better placed than ever to tender for larger projects and our reputation depends on being able to deliver a professional service whatever the size or location of the client. Our site in Grantham enables us to service Lincolnshire and the surrounding area, and we&rsquo;re committed to growing the regional team in order to continue to look after existing clients whilst securing new business. It&rsquo;s an exciting time for the entire team.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>', '2014-05-13', 'DSC_3456.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 317009, '2014-06-30 09:02:30', '', '2014-06-30 09:02:31', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'growth-in-grantham-for-arena-group'),
(209, 'The Arena team gets sporty', 'Arena had a team at the Gordons LLP 5-a-side tournament to raise money for The Friends of Alfie Martin.', '<p class="introduction">On a warm, tropical day in Leeds, the Arena Group 5-a-side team could be forgiven for thinking they were in Brazil.</p>\r\n<p>There were no thoughts of playing like England however, as our team marauded through the group stage to qualify for the knockout rounds.</p>\r\n<p>The tournament in question was the Gordons LLP 5-a-side &ldquo;World Cup&rdquo;. With 18 teams present and only the top two in each group progressing, the pressure was on the team to get out of the group.</p>\r\n<p>But they did exactly that, winning all of the games in the group and the quarter final. The lads went from unknowns to become a tournament favourite.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, the journey came to an end in the semi-finals. Despite fighting back from 2-0 down, the team were powerless to stop eventual winners, BDO, from scoring the late goal that took them through to the final.</p>\r\n<p>The disappointment was short lived however, as Gordons had put on a free BBQ and bar which was a huge help in softening the blow of elimination.</p>\r\n<p>Pete Bond, an Arena player commented; <em>&ldquo;It was played in good spirit with a carnival atmosphere -although it was highly competitive with no team giving an inch. It was disappointing not to make the final but that did mean we could get a head-start on the burgers!&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>The Team (L-R) Back row: Ben Lockwood, Tony Schofield, Dave Wagstaff, Pete Bond, Shaun Manuel. Front Row: Ravi Limbechaya, Jack Peacock, Richard Green.</h3>', '2014-07-04', 'Arena Group.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 165091, '2014-07-04 12:57:43', '', '2014-07-04 12:57:52', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 7, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'the-arena-team-gets-sporty'),
(210, 'Winning effort in region’s biggest children’s run', 'Youngsters at two Leeds schools are celebrating victory in a charity run that saw hundreds of big-hearted children take to the city’s streets.', '<p class="introduction">Pupils from St Margaret&rsquo;s in Horsforth carried off the primary school prize in the Arena Group Leeds Mini and Junior Run, organised by Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s Run For All. Cockburn High School in Beeston, meanwhile, took the honours in the secondary school category.</p>\r\n<p>Winner of the boys&rsquo; junior run for 9-14-year-olds was Alex Wyke-Ulliott. Harvey Norden, 11, took second place with 13-year-old Keiran Rowbuck third.</p>\r\n<p>First girl across the line was Alisha Laidler, 13, followed by Megan Driscoll, 13, in second place and 11-year-old Megan Wyke-Ulliott came third.</p>\r\n<p>Our Marketing Manager, Lisa Butterworth (pictured), visited both schools to present each of them with a Toshiba camcorder. She commented; "both schools have picked up the prize several times over the years. We''re always so impressed by the effort that all of the youngsters make on the day, not only in terms of the race but also the fundraising they do for charity."</p>\r\n<p>Arena has sponsored the Mini and Junior run series since it launched six years ago. Our sponsorship covers entry fees, making the race the biggest free mass participation children&rsquo;s event in Yorkshire.</p>\r\n<p>Youngsters who took part were encouraged to raise a small amount of money for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal or another charity of their choice. This year the appeal supported Leeds-based charity <a href="http://www.snaps-vol.org.uk/meettheteam.html" target="_blank">SNAPS</a>, which helps children with special needs and their families. It currently supports over 350 families a year.</p>\r\n<p>The charity provides practical help and advice for families and stages hydrotherapy and drop-in sessions at the Penny Field School in Meanwood.</p>\r\n<p>Mini and Junior Run event lead Lynne Preston said: &ldquo;Once again the mini and junior runs were enormously popular and it was wonderful to see so many children running for such good causes. They should all be very proud of themselves. We are extremely grateful to everyone who took part and for the invaluable support of the Arena Group."</p>', '2014-07-18', 'WebPicStMags_072014.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 102781, '2014-07-15 13:00:12', '', '2014-07-15 10:05:22', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'winning-effort-in-region’s-biggest-children’s-run'),
(211, '10 reasons to curb your paper addiction', 'At Arena, we often still come across organisations that are so heavily reliant on paper that they seem to defy the digital age we now live in. When we ask them why, we tend to hear a common set of reasons for clinging on to heavily paper-driven processes. This article summarises the top 10 excuses and the reasons why they need to be fed through the shredder.', '<p><span class="introduction">At Arena, we often still come across organisations that are so heavily reliant on paper that they seem to defy the digital age we now live in. When we ask them why, we tend to hear a common set of reasons for clinging on to heavily paper-driven processes. This article summarises the top 10 excuses and the reasons why they need to be fed through the shredder.</span></p>\r\n<h2>1. We&rsquo;ve always used paper records &ndash; what&rsquo;s the problem?</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>This is, without doubt, the most frequently voiced reason we hear for clinging to paper. Change can seem daunting and it&rsquo;s often painful and challenging. It&rsquo;s always easier to stay put but sticking with broken and outdated processes is a recipe for failure. Such an unwillingness to consider change inevitably leads to an exponential rise in paper usage, storage needs and costs.</p>\r\n<h2>2. I don&rsquo;t trust computers</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve all heard the horror stories about losing important documents when a computer is infected by a virus. No one likes that sinking feeling when a file is lost or corrupted but that is exactly where remote backup tapes, removable hard drives, &lsquo;the cloud&rsquo; or a remote server come in.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>3. Paper is easy to use</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Paper is easy to use when you&rsquo;re working on a particular document, but then what? That document is likely to be added to an ever-expanding paper archive, presenting you with a potential time-consuming challenge the next time you need to retrieve it &ndash; which might be in several years&rsquo; time. The longer you hoard paper, the more documents you&rsquo;ll accrue and the more difficulty you will face in complying with ever-evolving Data Protection guidelines.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>4. We can control security more easily with paper records</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>You may lock your sensitive documents away and grant access only to authorised employees. However, can you evidence that only they have accessed those files and that they have not tampered with them or shared them? Human nature dictates that at some point, that document store might be left unlocked and forgotten &ndash; can you prove that has never happened?</p>\r\n<p>An electronic document management system requires users to log in. This lets you control and audit which members of staff can access sensitive information, and prevent them from seeing anything that they are not authorised to view. Good software will gift you a host of security features to track user activity, prevent deletion of files and ensure your documents are protected.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>5. We know where all of our paper records are</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>You may be able to keep track today, but as the number of documents stored continues to rise, this will get more and more difficult. Misfiling, malicious activity or, worse still, document loss (through degradation or human error), may go undetected and cause you huge problems.</p>\r\n<p>All it could take to bring your carefully memorised system to its knees could be a crisis, such as a fire or flood - or even some dropped and scattered paperwork. An electronic document management system will prevent the permanent loss of documents whilst indexing and searching functionality places even a misfiled record at your fingertips within a few mouse clicks.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>6. We can&rsquo;t digitise every process for every team, it&rsquo;s impossible</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>We hear you! Rome wasn&rsquo;t built in a day and the concept of digitising all of your paper-led processes can seem daunting. It can be done step-by-step, though, very effectively. We often start with a look at just one of your functions &ndash; like finance, or pupil/customer records. Once that&rsquo;s worked out we move on through a pre-defined plan at a pace that suits you.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s also a good idea to also review the way you print and copy documents at the outset. This is an area where clever technology and a wise infrastructure can reduce paper consumption, address costs and simplify maintenance.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>7. My job will be replaced by a computer</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>You may be worried that robots will take over the world &ndash; but that day has not yet arrived. Don&rsquo;t think of an electronic records management as doing your job, rather, think of it as a tool to help you with your job. It can ease and improve the management of digitised records by making it easier to index and find documents, monitor retention and disposal periods and keep information safe through increased security and remote back-ups.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>8. Our paper document archive is not likely to be lost in a crisis &ndash; the risk of a fire, flood or similar is so low that we are willing to take it.</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>We have heard this a few times and, I kid you not, at least one of those businesses returned to us some time later having suffered just such a crisis. Bad things do happen, and it&rsquo;s best to protect your critical documents and be prepared.</p>\r\n<h2>9. It&rsquo;s too expensive to go digital</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p class="p1">Working with paper also incurs large costs, it&rsquo;s just that they are seeping into your bottom line daily, in the form of overheads such as running printers, and purchasing paper. They are also there in the form of inefficient practices that cost you time. For example, you might need to call back customers after retrieving information from paper files in order to answer their queries. You might spend hours searching for a document, filing and retrieving records &ndash; or undertaking your annual archiving process. Even storing a paper document archive incurs costs, and increasingly stringent legislation in some sectors will only frustrate this issue as document retention requirements expand. All of these costs are present, but they are tougher to spot and control &ndash; and they can all be addressed by digitising your processes.</p>\r\n<h2>10.&nbsp; We have to use paper in order to comply with legislation</h2>\r\n<p>This excuse is about as old as a paper filing system. You can make almost every kind of transaction from buying a home to filing taxes without ever signing a physical document. Laws have changed that allow typed and digital signatures; this is now a standard practice and looks like it is here to stay.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-07-25', 'iStock_000028693036Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 340176, '2014-07-25 07:49:36', 'in tray', '2014-07-25 07:49:38', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, '10-reasons-to-curb-your-paper-addiction'),
(212, 'Hundreds line up for the Arena Group York Mini and Junior Runs', 'Earlier this month we were in beautiful York, cheering on hundreds of youngsters who took part in the Arena Group Mini and Junior Runs. ', '<p class="introduction">Earlier this month we were in beautiful York, cheering on hundreds of youngsters who took part in the Arena Group Mini and Junior Runs. Runners were encouraged to support local and national charities including the Jane Tomlinson Appeal.</p>\r\n<p>Our Francis Fitzpatrick, Finance Director, and Lisa Butterworth, Marketing Manager, were on hand to start the race, cheer on the runners and watch them cross the finish line. &nbsp;Francis commented; &ldquo;what a superb event! It&rsquo;s fun for all the family and a fabulous way to spend a few hours on a Sunday morning in support of so many worthy causes. It&rsquo;s great to see so many children taking part.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Lisa added; &ldquo;these events just go from strength to strength, more children take part every year and it&rsquo;s a great way to get them doing something sporty in support of charity. It seems like only yesterday we were launching the first Arena Group runs in York!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">The appeal is this year supporting York Carers Centre&rsquo;s Young Carers Service, which supports youngsters aged 8-18 who help care for a parent or sibling with either a physical or mental disability.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Arena&rsquo;s Corporate Challenge team were also pounding pavements, running the Asda Foundation 10k, which always proves to be a popular event in the Arena team&rsquo;s sporting calendar.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><img src="../../../assets/articles/212/contained_images/c55515f38429_269_SDP2663-2127.jpg?1408533175" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="500" align="middle" /></p>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: left;">Pictured Top: Arena''s Francis Fitzpatrick and Lisa Butterworth with the winners of the Arena Group Junior Run. Pictured above: Runners crossing the finish line.</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-08-04', 'Group_Pic_Website.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 126938, '2014-08-20 11:06:58', '', '2014-08-20 11:06:59', '2014-10-08 11:56:30', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'hundreds-line-up-for-the-arena-group-york-mini-and-junior-runs'),
(213, 'New pastures for Arena’s electronic document management (EDM) team', 'This month our EDM Team moved into Arena Group’s Wakefield-based head office, Armitage House. The move brings our Sales, Support and Development teams together under one roof, for improved collaboration and team-working. ', '<p class="introduction">The move brings our Sales, Support and Development teams together under one roof, for improved collaboration and team-working.</p>\r\n<p>General Manager Neil Maude comments; &ldquo;the move is hugely beneficial in terms of understanding and responding to customer needs. We are already noticing the value in being able to get our specialists together, face-to-face and at short notice. This collaborative approach comes into its own when we are designing more complex document management systems which combine elements of print, copy and electronic document management.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Our teams work together comprehensive audits to understand the way documents are produced, processed, stored and destroyed by client organisations. This presents a detailed picture of the document workflows present, how and why they exist and various resulting outcomes in terms of efficiency, costs (finance, space, time etc) and environmental impact.</p>\r\n<p>With this understanding the teams collaborate on designing a new and improved infrastructure to leverage savings and improvements. Considered technology includes new print and copy hardware, strategically placed, and software to control and monitor print output, user activity, costs and consumables such as toner. Alongside this, electronic document management software may digitize processes and paper document archives to reduce the organisation&rsquo;s overall reliance on paper &ndash; a practice which has multiple clear and proven benefits.</p>\r\n<p>Neil comments; &ldquo;This holistic methodology often revolutionizes the way an organization works with documents, as can be seen in our clients Reed Boardall, Bradford Grammar School and Leeds Building Society.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Before the team moved in, Armitage House underwent an additional phase of refurbishment to create a brand new &lsquo;Professional Services and Support wing.&rsquo; This has placed all of our technical teams in neighbouring offices with plush new fixtures and fittings to match the other refurbished parts of the building.</p>\r\n<p>Neil adds; &ldquo;those &lsquo;water cooler&rsquo; chats that happen naturally when everyone shares a building, give our teams a more enriched knowledge of our existing customers as well as the markets we are looking to grow Arena&rsquo;s presence in. This is fairly subtle but it can have a very powerful role in developing the services we provide.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll find that our customer support telephone number and email address remain the same, and the same team is in place to respond to queries &ndash; they&rsquo;re simply in a smart new office.</p>\r\n<h2>Winter open day</h2>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;d love to welcome you to Armitage House to meet our team and check out their new surroundings. The site is home to our state-of-the-art showroom which combines the latest technology in document management. <a href="../../../articles/95">Why not join us for our winter open event on October 2<sup>nd</sup></a>, or get in touch to arrange a meeting at your own convenience?</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/print-the-hidden-costs">Our Managed Print Service</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">Electronic Document Management</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/combined-document-service">Consultancy</a></p>', '2014-08-15', 'EDM_Team_Aug14.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 54606, '2014-08-28 08:58:02', 'Arena Group''s EDM Team', '2014-08-20 15:03:29', '2014-10-08 11:56:31', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'new-pastures-for-arena’s-electronic-document-management-edm-team'),
(214, 'Charity Champions!', 'This month, two Arena Group employees have been out and about raising funds for military-related charities. Read about Gareth''s impressive endurance challenge and Karen''s emotional journey through time to the battlefields of WW1.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group has always match-funded any charitable fundraising efforts undertaken by its employees, and during the past month we have seen some particularly interesting activities.</p>\r\n<h2>An emotional journey for Karen Bowley</h2>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/214/contained_images/7c3f0fa9e33d_271_Karen Wenches in Trenches WS.jpg?1411474342" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></p>\r\n<p>Our Facilities Manager, Karen Bowley, tells us; &ldquo;my son is a soldier so I&rsquo;m very passionate about fundraising for anything connected to the military &ndash; both past and present.&rdquo; Since her time working with Arena, Karen has encouraged colleagues to support various charitable campaigns including coordinating a collection of Christmas parcels sent to serving soldiers by local charity &lsquo;Save Our Soldiers&rsquo; (SOS).</p>\r\n<p>On September 12<sup>th</sup> Karen joined &lsquo;<a href="http://www.wenchesintrenches.co.uk/">Wenches in Trenches</a>&rsquo; on their annual walk on the former Western Front. This year&rsquo;s walk took place in Ypres, Begium; in memory of nurses and voluntary aid detachments (VADs) who served in The Great War. Karen explains; &ldquo;I represented a nurse from Wakefield called Nellie Spindler. We all walked in WW1 nurses uniforms to Menin Gate, where we laid wreathes and took some time to reflect and say a few words together in remembrance of those who sacrificed so much for the things we often take for granted today.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>To date, Karen has raised just under &pound;1000. This will be used to fund memorial benches and plaques that will be placed in cemeteries and gardens in memory of the nurses and voluntary nurses who served on the front line during WW1.</p>\r\n<p>If you would like to find out more about this casue, or to make a donation, please visit <a href="http://www.wenchesintrenches.co.uk">www.wenchesintrenches.co.uk</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Impressive endurance challenge by Gareth Crane</h2>\r\n<p>This month Gareth Crane, together with some fellow fundraisers, walked 20 miles along Hadrian&rsquo;s Wall in support of <a href="http://www.helpforheroes.org.uk/">Help for Heroes</a> and the <a href="http://www.pwh.org.uk/">Prince of Wales Hospice</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thus far, the team has raised &pound;600 having completed the &lsquo;Hadrian&rsquo;s Wall Trek&rsquo;. This will contribute towards the enduring network of support that Help For Heores provides for wounded military personnel and their families; and towards vital end-of-life care and services delivered by the Prince of Wales Hospice.</p>\r\n<p>Gareth comments; &ldquo;Help For Heroes is a charity we have supported for some time and the work it does for serving and injured troops is incredible. The Prince of Wales Hospice is also close to our hearts after they recently did an amazing job looking after Sally Beardsmore, a close friend of ours, in her last few weeks. Raising money goes a small way to say thanks to the charity and their staff who helped make Sally comfortable in her last few weeks. Both charities rely heavily on donations, so the cash we&rsquo;ve received from our supporters will be hugely appreciated.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To donate to these worthy causes please visit <a href="http://www.virginmoneygiving.com/team/mattjimgazpaul">www.virginmoneygiving.com/team/mattjimgazpaul</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Did you know about Arena Group''s CSR Days?</h2>\r\n<p>Every Arena employee is encouraged to take 2 annual days away from their usual role to support a local chartity or community project.</p>\r\n<p>We get involved with all kinds of initiatives from gardening to DIY and hosting events for vulnerable community Groups.</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/83">Find out more about how we could help you.</a></p>', '2014-09-29', 'iStock_000034926076XLarge.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 370402, '2014-12-10 17:16:11', '', '2014-09-23 12:13:01', '2014-12-10 17:16:13', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'charity-champions'),
(215, 'Arena''s Grantham welcomes Carl Ewen', 'Arena Group’s Grantham site - Fovia (Innovation) Ltd - recently moved into smart new offices on Swinegate. Account Manager, Carl Ewen, has joined the expanding team and is busy introducing himself to existing clients in the area, whilst also supporting the continued expansion of the regional customer-base.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group&rsquo;s Grantham site - Fovia (Innovation) Ltd - recently moved into smart new offices on Swinegate. The team has welcomed Account Manager, Carl Ewen, who is busy introducing himself to existing clients in the area, whilst also supporting the continued expansion of the regional customer-base.</p>\r\n<p>Our Grantham site boasts a rich and comprehensive portfolio; Carl will be happy to hear from you if you would like to discuss any of the products and services detailed below.</p>\r\n<h2>Copy and Print</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The latest hardware from leading manufacturers including Toshiba, Kyocera and Ricoh.</li>\r\n<li>Software for print control that enables you to track and report on output, user activity and costs.</li>\r\n<li>Our <a href="../../page/print-the-hidden-costs">Managed Print Service</a>:      \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>a free audit of your current print and copy situation </li>\r\n<li>brand new machines placed just where you need them</li>\r\n<li>regular, fixed invoices to cover all of your machine maintenance and imaging costs</li>\r\n<li>toner delivered &lsquo;just in time&rsquo; - when your machines run low. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Electronic Document Management - mstore</h2>\r\n<p>Our EDRMS system, <strong><a href="../../page/electronic-document-management">mstore</a></strong>, helps businesses to scan, organise, store and retrieve documents electronically. It easily integrates with bespoke and industry-specific software including common packages for accounting, legal case management, HR and student records.</p>\r\n<h2>mstore delivers the following benefits;</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improved customer service response - all your documents at your fingertips</li>\r\n<li>Increased efficiency - no more time spent searching for paper files</li>\r\n<li>Reduced workload surrounding audits and inspections</li>\r\n<li>Continuity planning - protection from fire, flood, theft or loss</li>\r\n<li>Document security - controlled access to sensitive data</li>\r\n<li>Reduced storage demands and costs - reduced reliance on paper</li>\r\n<li>Simplified and comprehensive regulatory compliance</li>\r\n<li>Remote access, 24/7 - from anywhere with an internet connection (optional).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Laptops, PCs, Servers and Software</h2>\r\n<p>We are partnered with leading hardware and software vendors to produce working solutions first time. As an accredited Microsoft Certified Partner, we have the in-house skill set to devise, implement and maintain IT systems.</p>\r\n<p>We also have in depth experience of supporting software. Whether your requirements are simply to extend the functionality of software packages such as Excel, Word or full mission/business critical applications, we have both the knowledge and experience to deliver on time and within budget.</p>\r\n<p>The way we communicate in business today is critical to any organisation''s success. Following a review of your existing communications infrastructure, we are able to identify areas where improvements in productivity can be gained together with a possible reduction in costs. Whether it be a fixed cable network or a secure wireless network, Fovia will provide the right solution for your business with cutting edge equipment for all your telephony requirements.</p>\r\n<h2>IT Support</h2>\r\n<p>IT can often be unpredictable and produce undesirable effects on your business; this is where we can step in. We offer all the benefits of a dedicated IT department to small and medium-sized businesses within the Lincolnshire area.</p>\r\n<p>We can work behind the scenes monitoring your systems to prevent failures, and we are just a phone call away if anything does go wrong. If you are looking for a complete IT solution or need additional help to complement your existing skills and resources, we can deliver.</p>\r\n<h2>Here are just some of our current support services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Server solutions for file and email storage</li>\r\n<li>Remote and onsite fault diagnostics</li>\r\n<li>Email security and antivirus solutions.</li>\r\n<li>Data backup services</li>\r\n<li>Broadband and Internet Solutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Keep in touch</h2>\r\n<p>Subscribe to our <a href="../">e-newsletter</a> to keep up-to-speed with our latest news and offers. We also have an active <a href="https://twitter.com/ArenaGroup">Twitter</a> feed and <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/company/arena-group">LinkedIN</a> page where you can check-out the latest goings-on.</p>\r\n<h2>Contact our Grantham Team at Fovia (Innovation) Ltd</h2>\r\n<p>5 Swinegate<br />Grantham<br />Lincolnshire<br />NG31 6RJ</p>\r\n<p>Tel: 0844 863 8000</p>', '2014-08-13', 'DSC_3456.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 317009, '2014-09-23 16:05:49', 'Grantham Team', '2014-09-23 16:05:50', '2014-10-08 11:56:31', 3, NULL, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arenas-grantham-welcomes-carl-ewen');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(216, 'Looking back: 6 Key Changes in Business ', 'Three of Arena’s longest serving staff members tell us how changes in the workplace over the last twenty years have affected them, and the service that Arena provides:', '<h1 class="introduction">Three of Arena&rsquo;s longest serving staff members tell us how changes in the workplace over the last twenty years have affected them, and the service that Arena provides:</h1>\r\n<h2><strong>Improved communication</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Account Manager, John Wall, recalls; &ldquo;We would send thousands of faxes and post promotional leaflets through letter boxes to share information.&rdquo; Email means people can now be contacted almost instantly from anywhere with an internet connection.</p>\r\n<p>Mobile phones have also had a huge effect; &ldquo;When we were out of the office we used pre-pay phone cards in phone boxes. Sometimes I would borrow the customer&rsquo;s phone or head office would call the customer to speak with me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Remote working</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Mobile phones, tablets and laptops make remote working easy. Arena&rsquo;s Neil Maude comments; &ldquo;With our <strong>m</strong>store system for electronic document management we can even access shared files and collaborate with colleagues whilst we&rsquo;re out of the office &ndash; no more dusty and insecure filing cabinets.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Head of HR, Martin Wright, notes that business is now 24/7; &ldquo;In 1991 we had discrete working hours but with email and business mobile phones, we are always available. Some people even reply to emails when they are on holiday!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Print and copy technology</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The modern MFD is a catch-all for the office and far removed from the stand-alone devices of the early 90s. Logistics Director, Harry Wells, explains; &ldquo;The devices can do everything from printing and scanning, to fax and email.&rdquo; With some clever software we can even connect to them remotely, so individual machines alert us when toner is running low and we can sometimes diagnose mechanical problems from afar. &ldquo;We can efficiently keep machines up-and-running, which is convenient for the customer and straight-forward for us.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Printers have progressed from black and white Dot Matrix machines to laser and Harry is glad of this change; &ldquo;They used to use coated paper which was hard to write on and they&rsquo;d jam every few hundred prints. Now it&rsquo;s all a clean process with no messy inks&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Improved safety is not to be underestimated either. Harry recalls; &ldquo;Some had extinguishers next to them for when they set on fire!&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>24/7 service</strong></h2>\r\n<p>John highlights increasing automation; &ldquo;We used to get our meter readings and service requests by phone. With clever software, requests come in automatically. Errors are reduced as we know exactly which toner or part is needed.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Website requests for service and toner may yet take precedence over phone calls &ndash; although many of our customers tell us that they like to chat with our Call Control team. However, the 24-hour presence of the website is beneficial for those who like to get their requests to us out of normal working hours. Martin explains; &ldquo;Customers can send us service calls and toner requests at midnight if they want to, knowing we will pick them up first thing the next day.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Smart new technology also enables Arena&rsquo;s Call Control team to monitor the precise location of our engineers out on the road, meaning that allocating engineers to service calls is more efficient, quicker and easier than ever. Engineers receive jobs remotely on their phone or laptop, and simply get on with their visits.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>The rise and rise of the &lsquo;less paper office&rsquo;</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Internal document processes have evolved through the use of Arena&rsquo;s own products as Martin explains; &ldquo;With our <strong>m</strong>store software, documents are accessible at the touch of a button. Working digitally is extremely efficient, more secure than paper and we always have an accurate audit trail.&rdquo; Previously processes were much slower, documents often got lost and we needed much more storage for all of that paper.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Improved customer relationships</strong></h2>\r\n<p>With a well-managed Customer Relationship Management system, managing communication with customers is much simpler. Client information is held centrally and is shared across our teams, which is vital as our business continues to grow.</p>\r\n<p>John recalls the early 90&rsquo;s. &ldquo;I kept all of my leads in a rolodex that just contained contact details; I had to remember a lot about each customer and it was all in my own head &ndash; not shared with colleagues. Although it&rsquo;s really important to maintain those personal relationships with customers, maintaining a database helps the wider Arena Team to operate in a much more &lsquo;joined up&rsquo; and informed fashion.&rdquo;</p>', '2014-11-05', 'bigstock-Ideas-Technology-in-the-hands-34484432.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 183213, '2014-09-29 11:03:51', '', '2014-09-29 11:03:55', '2014-11-05 09:54:20', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'looking-back-6-key-changes-in-business'),
(217, 'Sweet prizes up for grabs for new e-newsletter subscribers!', 'We''re giving away retro sweet hampers to one lucky e-newsletter subscriber every quarter!', '<p class="introduction">We''re giving away a retro sweet hamper to one lucky e-newsletter subscriber every quarter!</p>\r\n<p>Simply complete the form below to subscribe to our e-newsletter or confirm your email address.</p>\r\n<p>Receive the newsletter for at least one quarter and you could be in with a chance of picking up the sweet treat of a prize.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Sign Me Up!</h1>\r\n<!-- Start of signup -->\r\n<script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[\r\nfunction validate_signup(frm) {\r\n	var emailAddress = frm.Email.value;\r\n	var errorString = '''';\r\n	if (emailAddress == '''' || emailAddress.indexOf(''@'') == -1) {\r\n		errorString = ''Please enter your email address'';\r\n	}\r\n\r\n    \r\nvar els = frm.getElementsByTagName(''input'');\r\nfor (var i = 0; i < els.length; i++)\r\n{\r\n    if (els[i].className == ''text'' || els[i].className == ''date'' || els[i].className == ''number'')\r\n    {\r\n        if (els[i].value == '''')\r\n            errorString = ''Please complete all required fields.'';\r\n    }\r\n    else if (els[i].className == ''radio'')\r\n    {\r\n        var toCheck = document.getElementsByName(els[i].name);\r\n        var radioChecked = false;\r\n        for (var j = 0; j < toCheck.length; j++)\r\n        {\r\n            if (toCheck[j].name == els[i].name && toCheck[j].checked)\r\n                radioChecked = true;\r\n        }\r\n        if (!radioChecked)\r\n            errorString = ''Please complete all required fields.'';\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	var isError = false;\r\n    if (errorString.length > 0)\r\n        isError = true;\r\n\r\n    if (isError)\r\n        alert(errorString);\r\n	return !isError;\r\n}\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n<form id="signup" action="http://dmtrk.com/signup.ashx" method="post"> <input name="addressbookid" type="hidden" value="1875815" /> <!-- UserID - required field, do not remove --> <input name="userid" type="hidden" value="22588" /> <!-- ReturnURL - when the user hits submit, they''ll get sent here --> <input name="ReturnURL" type="hidden" value="http://www.arenagroup.net" /> <!-- Email - the user''s email address --> \r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Email</td>\r\n<td><input name="Email" type="text" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>COMPANYNAME</td>\r\n<td><input class="text" name="cd_COMPANYNAME" type="text" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>FIRSTNAME</td>\r\n<td><input class="text" name="cd_FIRSTNAME" type="text" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>LASTNAME</td>\r\n<td><input class="text" name="cd_LASTNAME" type="text" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<input name="Submit" type="Submit" value="Subscribe" /> </form> <!-- End of signup -->\r\n<h4><a href="../../assets/stored_documents/original/40_Competition Terms and Conditions Arena Group.pdf" target="_blank">Terms and Conditions</a></h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-10-06', 'bigstock-traditional-striped-peppermint-44986603.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 305506, '2014-12-10 17:55:25', '', '2014-09-29 16:08:16', '2015-02-19 10:25:11', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'sweet-prizes-up-for-grabs-for-new-e-newsletter-subscribers'),
(218, 'Arena Group joins the Legal Support Network', 'Arena Group has recently joined the Legal Support Network (LSN) as an official Network Partner. The LSN acts as a common vehicle through which to collaborate and share our experience and knowledge with a view to supporting legal sector organisations.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group has recently joined the Legal Support Network (LSN) as an official Network Partner.</p>\r\n<p>Becoming a <em>networkpartner</em> places Arena into a community comprising of thousands of professionals across a variety of business sectors, all serving the legal sector. The LSN acts as a common vehicle through which to collaborate and share our experience and knowledge with a view to supporting legal sector organisations.</p>\r\n<p>As part of this community, Arena will attend events and conferences hosted by LSN, which will feature our articles and insights about document management to the readership of the LSN&rsquo;s weekly newsletter.</p>\r\n<p>Arena Group&rsquo;s Head of Marketing, Lisa Butterworth, comments; <em>&ldquo;our clients operating within the legal sector have been very highly praising of the LSN, regarding it as a credible &lsquo;go-to&rsquo; source of expertise and advice for the legal community. We are always looking for ways to improve our customer offering and, as a partner of LSN we look forward to increasing our knowledge and understanding of the sector, as well as our customer base.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>LSN&rsquo;s Head of client services, Sarah Cox added; <em>&ldquo;LSN is delighted to welcome Arena Group to the fold as our newest networkpartner. The affiliation gives Arena access to LSN&rsquo;s well established and highly engaged audience of law firm support and business service decision-makers and influencers both online (<a href="http://t.signauxtrois.com/e1t/c/5/f18dQhb0S7lC8dDMPbW2n0x6l2B9nMJW7t5XYg4Xb25WW3M2cJx5vws-6W1q0JJx56dNXVf7pMYfb02?t=http%3a%2f%2fwww.lsn.co.uk&amp;si=6167166809276416&amp;pi=8ce0bd5c676a4e518a7076ab5a68e0e0">www.lsn.co.uk</a>) and in person at our events.&nbsp; They have already hit the ground running with lots of interesting content on the website and are attending our Leeds law firm forum on 21<sup>st</sup> October so we look forward to continuing this partnership long into the future.&rdquo;</em></p>', '2014-10-15', 'iStock_000015959628Medium.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 174918, '2014-12-10 17:43:05', '', '2014-10-15 09:33:32', '2014-12-10 17:43:06', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-group-joins-the-legal-support-network'),
(219, 'Arena dresses up for charity', 'Arena has recently been raising money for the Bolton Society for Blind People. Read how wearing bright colours, a bake sale and a charity run in fancy dress turned into money to support weekly volunteer visits to vulnerable people in Bolton.', '<p class="introduction">Arena has been making a special effort to raise money for Bolton Society for Blind People (BSBP).</p>\r\n<p><strong>With over 7000 people in Bolton affected by sight loss and at risk of isolation, money raised will be used for the BSBP Befriending Service. This offers blind adults relief from social isolation through weekly volunteer visits. </strong></p>\r\n<p>Arena staff have been ''wearing it bright'' to work in aid of the cause.  On October 10th, staff were seen in all kinds of bright colours, and there was also a bake sale of tasty treats kindly baked by Arena colleagues.</p>\r\n<p>It was a successful day with over <strong>&pound;110</strong> raised. Thanks to all for their generosity!</p>\r\n<p>In November a team of staff donned Santa suits to take part in the BSBP Santa Dash at Leverhulme Park in Bolton. The 5km course was exclusively run by people dressed in Santa outfits anjd the Arena team raised around <strong>&pound;100</strong> for their efforts</p>\r\n<p>As with all employee fundraising efforts, Arena has match-funded the cash donation, bringing our total contribution over &pound;400!</p>\r\n<p>Arena''s Managing Director, Adrian Fitzpatrick, comments; "it''s a pleasure to support such a worthy cause - especially for BSBP, which has been a loyal customer to Arena for several years now. I know the team certianly had a lot of fun raising the cash too!"</p>\r\n<p>To read more about the great work that the society do, see their website here: <a href="http://bsbp.org.uk/" target="_blank">http://bsbp.org.uk/</a></p>', '2014-10-16', 'Santa Dashers 2014 BSBP.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 157515, '2014-11-28 14:20:56', 'BSPB Santa Dash Team 2014', '2014-10-16 10:52:41', '2014-11-28 14:25:57', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-dresses-up-for-charity'),
(220, 'Scary in pink!', 'As it''s Halloween, so there have been a couple of spookier interpretations to today''s ''wear it pink'' fundraiser in support of Breast Cancer Care.', '<p class="introduction">We''ve been wearing it spookily pink for <a href="http://www.wearitpink.org/" target="_blank">Breast Cancer Care </a>at Arena Group today.</p>\r\n<p>With 1000 women still dying from breast cancer in the UK every month,  the fight is far from over.</p>\r\n<p>Employees have been paying &pound;1 to wear pink or fancy dress to work, and there are also cakes kindly brought in and baked available to buy in support of the charity.</p>\r\n<p>Any excuse to dress up and raise money for charity!</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p>Click here to see ways to donate: <a href="http://secure.breastcancercampaign.org/appeal/wip_oneoff/?__utma=216891145.7173247.1414756502.1414756502.1414756502.1&amp;__utmb=216891145.0.10.1414756502&amp;__utmc=216891145&amp;__utmx=-&amp;__utmz=216891145.1414756502.1.1.utmcsr=google|utmccn=(organic)|utmcmd=organic|utmctr=(not provided)&amp;__utmv=-&amp;__utmk=205540944" target="_blank">www.wearitpink.org</a></p>\r\n<p>Or follow the campaign on Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/BCCampaign" target="_blank">@BBCampaign</a> and <a href="http://twitter.com/search?q=#wearitpink&amp;src=typd" target="_blank">#wearitpink</a></p>', '2014-10-31', 'IMG_0419.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 115267, '2014-10-31 11:59:55', 'Wear it Pink', '2014-10-31 11:59:59', '2014-10-31 16:21:59', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'scary-in-pink'),
(221, 'Children of LINCOLN take their marks for new charity event', 'Youngsters aged between 9 and 14 will be encouraged to pull on their trainers to take part in the Arena Group City of Lincoln Mini and Junior Runs, which take place on Saturday 21st March.', '<h1 class="introduction">Former England football manager Graham Taylor was back on home turf as he officially launched the new-look Asda Foundation City of Lincoln 10K and Arena Group Lincoln Mini and Junior Runs.</h1>\r\n<p>Youngsters aged between 9 and 14 will be encouraged to pull on their trainers to take part in the Arena Group City of Lincoln Mini and Junior Runs, which take place on Saturday 21st March.</p>\r\n<p>Graham Taylor commented; &ldquo;I&rsquo;m sure there will be a brilliant atmosphere on the day. The runners will get great support and, along with the achievement of crossing the finish line, they will have the satisfaction of helping some really deserving charities.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>The official partner charity of the Arena Group Mini and Junior Run is <a href="http://www.standrewshospice.com" target="_blank">St Andrew&rsquo;s Children&rsquo;s Hospice</a>, with all young runners encouraged to raise a small amount in sponsorship to support its Lincolnshire centre.  St Andrew&rsquo;s is the only children&rsquo;s hospice in Lincolnshire and provides care for children and young adults, who have a life limiting illness, from across the county.</p>\r\n<p>The Hospice provides specialist respite care on an in-patient and day-care basis, pain and symptom control and end of life care. As importantly, the Hospice also provides care and support for the patient&rsquo;s family, including practical and emotional support, special care for siblings and bereavement support. The service costs &pound;1.8m a year to run &ndash; with only a tiny 3 per cent of it coming from Government funding.</p>\r\n<p>Angela Greenfield, Events Co-ordinator at St Andrew&rsquo;s said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re really pleased to have been chosen as the official charity of the Arena Group Mini and Junior Run. We support around 90 children or young people and their families each year, all of them are going through the toughest experience you can imagine.  &ldquo;The work the hospice does, not only in its care, but also in supporting the siblings and families of patients, really is invaluable and just doesn&rsquo;t exist elsewhere. We hope as many young people as possible who take part in the runs will consider raising a small amount for us &ndash; every penny will help to support the hospice and the young people it cares for.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, managing director of the Arena Group, whose support will allow every child to take part in the Mini and Junior Runs for free, said: &ldquo;We are absolutely delighted to support the Lincoln mini and junior runs and St Andrew''s Children''s Hospice. Our involvement with Run For All&rsquo;s children&rsquo;s runs in Leeds and York has been hugely enjoyable and we are very much looking forward to seeing hundreds of youngsters running through Lincoln next year.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p>For more information and to enter the Arena Group Mini or Junior Run go to <a href="http://www.runforall.com" target="_blank">www.runforall.com</a>. Runners who sign up quickly can currently take advantage of an early bird offer.</p>', '2014-11-06', 'image.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 168591, '2014-11-06 21:13:35', 'Lincoln Arena Group Run For All', '2014-11-06 21:13:56', '2014-11-28 14:52:09', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'children-of-lincoln-take-their-marks-for-new-charity-event'),
(222, 'Join us at PfH Live', 'We''re back at PfH Live in Manchester Central in on 23rd-25th June. Meet us on stand P57.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group is PfH&rsquo;s number 1 nominated   supplier for the provision   of  Photocopiers, Printers,  Multi-Functional  Devices (MFDs) and Office    Based Managed Print  Services (MPS). Meet us at PfH Live!</p>\r\n<p>We will be showcasing our hardware and software for print management   and our managed print service (MPS). Meet us at PfH Live on <strong>23rd - 25th June, Manchester Central, stand P57</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Arena staff will be on hand to  discuss electronic document  management and how consumers can combine  technology to reduce costs,  drive efficiency and improve  sustainability.</p>\r\n<h2>Visit us on stand P57 to enter our prize draw</h2>\r\n<h2>Arena''s No. 1 position on the PfH Framework</h2>\r\n<p>PfH specialises in improving procurement practice for over 800 social housing providers throughout the UK.</p>\r\n<p>Arena  is PfH&rsquo;s number 1 nominated supplier for the provision of    Photocopiers,  Printers, Multi-Functional Devices (MFDs) and Office    Based Managed  Print Services (MPS). To win this position Arena was put  through a  stringent tender process that compared us with a long list of  our competitors. This process scrutinised many criteria including our  prices, service performance and quality, product and service portfolio  and value for money.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue">Our no. 1 position confirms that our  products and  services are of   the highest standard and we offer  exceptional value  to our clients.</p>\r\n<h2>About the show<strong><br /></strong></h2>\r\n<p>The  Chartered Institute of Housing&rsquo;s Annual Exhibition is the UK&rsquo;s   ultimate housing experience focusing on the provision of affordable   housing and the development of sustainable communities. For the fourth   year running, Procurement For Housing has partnered with CIH to host PfH   Live under the same roof.</p>\r\n<p>Arena will be exhibiting alongside over  300 of the sector&rsquo;s leading  providers, partners and suppliers as they  showcase the latest products  and services in the housing and  regeneration sector. Free seminars will  give delegates an opportunity to  share best practice and solutions to  current and future sector  challenges.</p>\r\n<h2>Further information</h2>\r\n<p>Coming soon!</p>\r\n<h2>Join the discussion</h2>\r\n<p>Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/ArenaGroup" target="_blank">@ArenaGroup</a></p>', '2014-11-05', 'pfhlive.gif', 'image/gif', 6488, '2014-11-17 14:32:46', '', '2014-11-10 14:36:31', '2014-11-17 14:35:50', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'join-us-at-pfh-live'),
(223, 'Brand new Junior and Mini Run For All arrives in SHEFFIELD!', 'Former England cricket captain Michael Vaughan today [Wednesday 19th November] officially launched the first Plusnet Yorkshire Half Marathon-Sheffield and Arena Group Sheffield Mini and Junior Run. ', '<p class="introduction">Youngsters will have the opportunity to sign-up for the Arena Group Sheffield Mini and Junior Runs, which will take place in the city center on <strong>April 12th 2015</strong>. Arena''s sponsorship makes the children&rsquo;s races entirely free to enter.</p>\r\n<p>The mini course covers a distance of 1.5K and is for children aged 3-8, while the 2.5K junior run is for youngsters aged 9-14.</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, Arena Group managing director, said: &ldquo;We are proud to be sponsoring the Mini and Junior runs at the first Yorkshire Half Marathon - Sheffield. The event is a superb addition to the Leeds and York Mini and Junior events, which we have supported since 2010. It is always a delight to see youngsters of all abilities taking on a challenge and raising money for a host of very worthy charities. I am sure all the young runners who take part in Sheffield will enjoy a really memorable day.&rdquo;<br /><br />Sara Birkinshaw, of Run For All, said: &ldquo;We are really looking forward to bringing this new event to Sheffield next spring in partnership with the City Council. With its triple challenge, scenic route and city centre start and finish, we are sure we can create a colourful event with a great atmosphere and one of which Sheffield can be proud.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Young runners can take part in the new events for fun, for a personal challenge or to raise funds for a charity of their choice. To enter the children&rsquo;s runs please visit <a href="http://eee.runforall.com" target="_blank">www.runforall.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part in the Mini and Junior Runs are encouraged to raise a small amount of money to help a local cause. They can choose any charity of their choice or run on behalf of the Jane Tomlinson Appeal, which is supporting Sheffield-based <a href="http://safeatlast.org.uk" target="_blank">Safe@Last</a>, a charity working with and on behalf of young people at risk through running away from home.</p>\r\n<p>Clare Sherratt, Head of Communications and Funding, said: &ldquo;SAFE@LAST is delighted to be the official charity partner of the Arena Group Sheffield Junior and Mini Fun Run events in the Yorkshire Half Marathon 2015.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re sure that the races will be great fun for children and their families and would encourage everyone to consider entering.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re looking forward to cheering the runners on in April.&nbsp; The funds raised through these events will help us to continue to keep vulnerable children in South Yorkshire safe from harm when they feel they have no choice but to run away.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Siobhan Curtis, Jane Tomlinson Appeal Legacy Manager, said: &ldquo;There&rsquo;s a  great buzz around this new event and we are delighted to be involved.  Many excellent charities will benefit from the efforts of the thousands  of runners who will take part. Money raised for the Jane Tomlinson  Appeal will be used to support children&rsquo;s and cancer charities and we  are immensely grateful to everyone running on our behalf.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p>To enter the children&rsquo;s runs please visit <a href="http://eee.runforall.com" target="_blank">www.runforall.com</a></p>\r\n<p>More about our event benefactor: <a href="http://safeatlast.org.uk" target="_blank">Safe@Last</a></p>\r\n<h6>Pictured: Michael Vaughan with representatives from Safe@Last and Lisa Butterworth of Arena Group</h6>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-11-19', 'Arena Sheffield launch 2015.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 50455, '2014-11-19 15:44:45', 'RFA Launch Sheffield', '2014-11-19 15:44:46', '2014-11-19 15:48:28', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'brand-new-junior-and-mini-run-for-all-arrives-in-sheffield'),
(224, 'Software for easy-peesy printer management !', 'Many of our customers utilise leading edge technology that plays a key part in making their print and copy strategy much more efficient, transparent and easy to manage. Our Professional Services Manager, Ian Fox, takes a brief look at the key benefits.', '<p class="introduction">When you are busy juggling a plethora of important tasks the last thing you need to worry about is submitting a printer meter reading or sourcing more toner to keep your machine up and running.</p>\r\n<p>Many of our customers utilise leading edge technology that plays a key part in making their print and copy strategy much more efficient, transparent and easy to manage. Our Professional Services Manager, Ian Fox, takes a brief look at the key benefits.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Ship-shape print and copy infrastructure </strong></h2>\r\n<p>The software enables you to analyse the activity of machines on your network to see, for example, the print volumes produced by each device. Knowing which machines handle the highest volumes, what percentage of colour is being produced, and where they are located enables us to suggest ways to tweak your infrastructure to gain maximum efficiency. We can even check on the health of your machines and diagnose any mechanical problems remotely. This can all potentially reduce your costs and helps to keep your printers in good working order.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Automated meter readings</strong></h2>\r\n<p>This clever technology takes care of meter readings automatically, sending your provider an accurate reading every 5 hours &ndash; so you don&rsquo;t have to do a thing.</p>\r\n<p><em>"[The software] certainly gives me a better billing experience. In a previous role,&nbsp;monthly readings needed to be submitted,&nbsp;an invoice would arrive and photocopies that were monitored via a spreadsheet would then need to be checked. This was time consuming and subject to errors. Now I am confident that my invoice is correct without any of that hassle."&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Rachel Finlay, Brain Tumour Research and Support Across Yorkshire</em></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Simplified toner management</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Toner levels are monitored by the hour. When a device reaches a pre-defined toner level, Arena dispatches a replacement to you.</p>\r\n<p>This means you don&rsquo;t need to store spare toner cartridges or spend time sourcing the best deal - and there&rsquo;s no risk of your printers ever running dry.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;We always had to store a lot of spare toner for our printers and we would have one person managing each printer and another storing the toner. The new system has taken out a few layers of administration and management of the printers - freeing people up to focus on their jobs." <br /><br /></em>Jaime Lockwood, Morrish Solicitors</p>\r\n<h3>About Ian Fox</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../..//assets/articles/224/contained_images/93ca34f4a755_276_Ian Fox Jan15 large.jpg?1422352750" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="127" height="127" align="LEFT" />Professional Services Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:ianf@arenagroup.net">IanF@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Ian Fox joined the Arena Group as a Systems Engineer in 1995. During  his time at Arena he has gained a wealth of experience in helping  organisations with their document related workflows. He now heads up the  Professional Services department, which was formed in January 2011 with  the aim of ensuring that existing and future Arena clients receive the  best possible advice, solutions and support to enable them to manage and  control their documents effectively.</p>', '2014-11-28', 'iStock_000037897768_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 82782, '2014-11-28 13:54:25', '', '2014-11-28 13:51:35', '2015-02-02 10:23:59', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'software-for-easy-peesy-printer-management'),
(225, 'This Year''s Top Blog Posts', 'As 2014 draws to a festive close we thought it would be nice to take a stroll through some of our best read blog posts of the year. From paper saving tips to toner fraud prevention - it''s well worth a look!', '<p class="introduction">As 2014 draws to a festive close we thought it would be nice to take a stroll through some of our best read blog posts of the year. From paper saving tips to toner fraud prevention - it''s well worth a look!</p>\r\n<h2>The top 6 reasons to outsource your print and copy management</h2>\r\n<p>From expert support to increasing efficiencies, Gary Putson takes a look at the benefits of outsourcing your print and copy management.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://bit.ly/OutSce" target="_blank">Read this article</a></p>\r\n<h2>10 reasons to curb your paper addiction</h2>\r\n<p>We often come across companies that are still clinging to heavily paper-driven processes. This article summarises the top excuses and the reasons why they need to be fed through the scanner.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://bit.ly/PaperAddict" target="_blank">Read this article</a></p>\r\n<h2>Software for easy-peesy printer management!</h2>\r\n<p>Ian Fox takes a brief look at the key benefits to using leading edge technology to make print and copy strategy much more efficient, transparent and easy to manage. The last thing you need to be doing is submitting meter readings or sourcing replacement toner.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://bit.ly/PrintMgr" target="_blank">Read this article</a></p>\r\n<h2>7 Small Steps Towards Big Savings in the Housing Sector</h2>\r\n<p>Arena recognises that many housing associations (and other businesses in fact) must focus on the efficiencies that they can influence in order to deliver cost savings. Sean McGuigan outlined 7 simple steps that can lead to significant savings.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://bit.ly/SaveHse" target="_blank">Read this article</a></p>\r\n<h2>Paper vs Programs Infographic</h2>\r\n<p>Finally, a feast for the eyes in the form of our infographic comparing the benefits of paper documents Vs electronic.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://bit.ly/PaperVsProgrammes" target="_blank">Read this article</a></p>', '2014-12-15', 'AnnualReview_WS.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 131762, '2014-12-15 17:29:52', '', '2014-12-15 17:29:52', '2014-12-22 11:59:50', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'this-years-top-blog-posts'),
(227, 'Is your printer data secure?', 'MFP’s (Multi Function Printers) are often overlooked in an organisation''s security policy. This can be a risk if sensitive data is processed through the machine, but there are solutions available to ensure that private data remains private. Arena’s Ian Fox explains:', '<p class="introduction">From securing IT networks to locking filing cabinets or shredding files when they are no longer required, many businesses are conscious of the importance of document security. Most companies have procedures and regulations in place to ensure that sensitive information does not get into the wrong hands.</p>\r\n<p>When you use your Multi Function Printer(MFP), temporary files may be created on its internal hard disk drive as it caches print, or collates copied or scanned pages. Unfortunately some well publicised cases have made the headlines, where end of life MFP&rsquo;s have been resold and subsequently targeted for the extraction of sensitive data.</p>\r\n<p>Fear not! There are solutions available to ensure that private data remains  private. Below, Arena&rsquo;s Head of Professional Services, Ian Fox,  explains.</p>\r\n<p>We don&rsquo;t need to explain the problem of leaked data reaching the hands of competitors. This alone should provide enough motivation to ensure security but if it doesn&rsquo;t, the Information Commisoner''s Office (ICO) is always on hand to impose financial penalties or prosecute any companies acting in breach of its rules.</p>\r\n<p class="font_blue" style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>The ICO can give fines of up to &pound;500,000 for failure to comply with the Data Protection Act.</em></strong></p>\r\n<h2>How to be sure that your MFP data is secure:</h2>\r\n<p>Scans and print jobs are temporarily stored on the MFP&rsquo;s hard drive before being drawn from it to print. In the past, instant overwriting or encryption of data was the only way to address this, often leading to a loss of device performance. The other option was a manual process at the end of the device&rsquo;s life to invalidate the data, either by removing the drive and physically destroying it or by using one of the many utilities / services available for secure erase. Both of these are extremely time consuming processes.</p>\r\n<p>Many modern machines now come with secure hard disk technology as standard. The data on these disks is encrypted using an AES 256-bit key to comply with ISO/IEC15408 standards. The decryption key is known only by the corresponding MFD and, in the event of the disk being connected to any other system, the data is immediately rendered unreadable.</p>\r\n<p>With this type of technology in place it&rsquo;s also possible for an authorised service engineer to enter specific security codes into the device that can instigate destruction of all data held on the disk without the need for removing the disk from the machine. This saves time and ensures security when dealing with your MFP at the end of its contract.</p>\r\n<h3>About Ian Fox</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/227/contained_images/1af28acae326_276_Ian Fox Jan15 large.jpg?1422352750" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="148" height="148" align="LEFT" /></p>\r\n<p>Professional Services Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:ianF@arenagroup.net">ianF@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Ian Fox joined the Arena Group as a Systems Engineer in 1995. During  his time at Arena he has gained a wealth of experience in helping  organisations with their document related workflows. He now heads up the  Professional Services department, which was formed in January 2011 with  the aim of ensuring that existing and future Arena clients receive the  best possible advice, solutions and support to enable them to manage and  control their documents effectively.</p>\r\n<h2>More information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../web/contact_us" target="_blank">Contact us</a> to find out more about monitoring and controlling print, printing from mobile devices, digitising your paper-driven processes or implementing an electronic document management system.</p>', '2015-01-20', 'bigstock-Concept-Of-Data-Protection-39198535.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 172503, '2015-01-20 15:13:22', '', '2015-01-20 15:13:26', '2015-01-28 16:54:35', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'is-your-printer-data-secure');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(228, 'MPs call for a ban on long email disclaimers', 'Sir Alan Duncan, MP, recently called for a ban on long email disclaimers, citing the wasteful print practices that they encourage. Arena''s Ian Fox explains why such drastic action is not necessary and outlines the ways in which many organisations are already tackling the problem.', '<p class="introduction">A <a href="http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/mps-push-for-ban-on-long-email-disclaimers-9965802.html?origin=internalSearch">recent article in the Independent</a> included a quote from Sir Alan Duncan, (MP for Rutland and Melton, and a Minister of State in the Department for International Development). He asserts that long disclaimers at the bottom of emails waste &ldquo;forests&rsquo; worth of paper&rdquo; and declares his belief that such disclaimers should be replaced by a simple and short link.</p>\r\n<p>The article makes a very valid point; &ldquo;Printing out emails often means accidentally printing all of the disclaimer at the bottom, which can add up to a number of pages&hellip; Short emails become 2 page documents, longer emails &ndash; and chains &ndash; start to run over multiple sheets. All of which adds to the size of the paper files. So signatures add not only cost in print, but also in long term filing and archiving costs.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s Neil Maude agrees, stating; &ldquo;We run a scanning bureau to digitise paper files; we have frequently found that up to 25% of the file content consists of email signatures.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>An alternative solution (without even touching your disclaimer)</h2>\r\n<p>You may not realise it, but the tools to address this problem already exist and are working within many businesses. Arena&rsquo;s Ian Fox outlines some features of commonly used software that can prevent the accidental printing of email disclaimers and help to reduce the number of pages printed.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>Educate users with alerts</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Much of this wasteful output is produced accidentally. A user goes to print an email, without realising that the email contains many replies and forwards from previous communications. Before they know it several pages are streaming out of their printer, most of which are destined for the recycle bin!</p>\r\n<p>With effective use of print control software, it is possible to generate a pop-up alert to a user, informing them of the number of pages that will be printed and, if required, even the cost to the business of printing the document. These alerts can be configured to your requirements and will of course work with other applications. Once this technology is in place we usually see a substantial reduction in accidental page printing.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>Set appropriate defaults</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Further to alerts, rules-based printing can be used to select more economical defaults. Printing can be set to black and white or greyscale as standard (colour prints are typically ten times more expensive than mono.) You might also default to duplex printing - a sheet of paper costs around half a penny - you&rsquo;ve paid for two sides so why not use them? Printing on both sides of the page can also help reduce your storage and shredding costs.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>Helpful monitoring, duplicate detection and print quotas</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Do you ever mistakenly print the same document twice? Software can enable duplicate detection and deletion, and print quotas can be set. These defaults are commonly used in settings such as education, where they can be applied to specific user groups. For example, students may be restricted from printing in colour or even have a quota set on how much they can print, whilst staff rules can be much more in line with departmental requirements and budgets.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>Secure or &lsquo;Find-Me&rsquo; printing</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Further savings and process improvements can be made through the use of secure, or &lsquo;Find-Me&rsquo; printing. This technology allows you to print to a virtual print queue. Nothing actually is printed until a user decides to collect their pages. They simply walk up to a device of their choice (this could be on another floor or even in a different building) and logon to the machine using either a PIN, password, proximity card or even finger print. Once logged in, the user can see their print jobs and the associated costs, before they decide to print or delete them. Jobs that haven&rsquo;t been collected after a certain time period can be deleted automatically if required.</p>\r\n<p>This greatly improves document security as it prevents sensitive documents from being left uncollected on printer output trays. Your paper recycling bins will have never been so empty!</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>Monitor &amp; Report</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Print control software can put you back in control of your companies&rsquo; expenditure on printing. If you can&rsquo;t analyse it, then you can&rsquo;t manage it. But with an effective print control solution you can use powerful management reporting to challenge user print behaviours. We often find that when users know that their print activity is being monitored, staff behaviour changes. Unnecessary colour printing reduces, more double-sided printing is utilised and the outcome is that costs tumble - it&rsquo;s better for the environment too.</p>\r\n<p>To find out more about how to tackle the burden of wasteful print practices in your business, give us a call on 0844 863 8000.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>About Ian Fox</h3>\r\n<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="" align="LEFT" />Professional Services Manager<br /> Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:ianF@arenagroup.net">ianF@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Ian Fox joined the Arena Group as a Systems Engineer in 1995. During his time at Arena he has gained a wealth of experience in helping organisations with their document related workflows. He now heads up the Professional Services department, which was formed in January 2011 with the aim of ensuring that existing and future Arena clients receive the best possible advice, solutions and support to enable them to manage and control their documents effectively.</p>\r\n<h2>More information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../web/contact_us" target="_blank">Contact us</a> to find out more about monitoring and controlling print, printing from mobile devices, digitising your paper-driven processes or implementing an electronic document management system.</p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/95" target="_blank">Visit us</a> to see a demonstration of our super-clean carbon zero printers and MFDs, mobile printing and print control in action.</p>\r\n<h2>Related articles</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/putting-the-brakes-on-wasteful-printing?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank">Putting the brakes on wasteful printing practices</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/software-for-easy-peesy-printer-management?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank">Automatic meter readings and more - software for easy-peesy printer management</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/10-reasons-to-curb-your-paper-addiction?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank">10 reasons to curb your paper addition</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/steps-towards-the-less-paper-dream?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank">Steps towards the less paper dream</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-01-22', 'HiRes.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 126453, '2015-01-27 10:20:10', '', '2015-01-22 14:31:56', '2015-01-27 10:20:12', 3, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'mps-call-for-a-ban-on-long-email-disclaimers');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(229, 'Printing in a new dimension', '3D printing has really gathered pace in the past few years. We discuss some of the uses devised to take advantage of this technology.', '<p class="introduction">3D printing has really gathered pace in the past few years. From once being in the domain of science fiction, the machines are now available on the high street and resulting in more and more uses being devised for them.</p>\r\n<h2>So, how does it work?</h2>\r\n<p>The 3D printing journey starts with a computer file. A Computer Aided Design (CAD) file is created to tell the printer what pattern to print. The design is sliced by the software into hundreds or thousands of horizontal layers to enable the printer to create it, one layer at a time and from a growing variety of materials including plastics and even edible substances. The object is built up rather than chipping away at a large block, resulting in a more efficient process without waste.</p>\r\n<p>The potential is exciting, here are a few of the most innovative uses that we&rsquo;ve seen yet.</p>\r\n<h2>Commercial design and product development</h2>\r\n<p>Product development can now be done for a fraction of the cost, producing prototypes in a matter of hours. Nike works in this way to create <a href="http://www.digitaltrends.com/sports/need-a-size-9-nike-and-adidas-can-3d-print-that-for-you-if-youre-an-nfl-player/">multiple, improved prototypes</a> in the space of one day.</p>\r\n<p>Other design-led applications such as architecture have seen a gradual shift from drawings on paper, to CAD models created on a computer and accompanied by models painstakingly built by hand using materials like card and foam. Now a 3D model can be printed to speed and simplify the process.</p>\r\n<h2>3D printing in space</h2>\r\n<p>When an astronaut needed a wrench, the usual practise was a costly one &ndash; to send one up on another craft. Following the development of a 3D printer that works in space, <a href="http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/station/research/news/3Dratchet_wrench/">NASA simply emailed a design</a> to the International Space Station - saving a huge amount of time and money.</p>\r\n<p>Medical marvels</p>\r\n<p>From a <a href="http://news.yahoo.com/3d-printed-legs-help-disabled-dog-run-for-the-first-time-225649913.html">dog with 3D printed legs</a> to <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/11202016/3D-printed-drugs-could-revolutionise-prescriptions.html">3D printed medication</a>, the medical industry is one that may be transformed by the technology. Printing a body part to practise on before an operation is becoming increasingly common, and there have already been cases of 3D printed medical implants. For example, <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/3d-printing-can-create-replacement-bones-2014-8">replacement vertebrae</a> for a 12 year old boy. Perhaps even more impressively, a tiny splint was created for a <a href="http://www.livescience.com/34613-3d-printing-airway-splint.html">baby&rsquo;s airway to assist breathing</a>; this was designed to grow with the boy over three years, before finally dissolving without a trace as the tissue grows over it.</p>\r\n<h2>Food</h2>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://edition.cnn.com/2014/11/06/tech/innovation/foodini-machine-print-food/">Foodini</a> is a 3D printer designed to print food. Currently in its infancy, the device can print complex desserts or foods such as pizza and pasta. It has already prompted ideas about use in the military and for elderly people.</p>\r\n<p>Hershey recently hosted a <a href="http://uk.businessinsider.com/hershey-chocolate-3d-printer-2014-12">3D chocolate printing exhibit</a> using the printer to produce chocolate shapes. They could design much more complex designs than usual, some even had moving parts!</p>\r\n<h2>What&rsquo;s the future for 3D printing?</h2>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s still early days for the mainstream 3D printer industry but it doesn&rsquo;t seem like it&rsquo;ll be long before the machines are widespread and used for a plethora of applications. Driven by open source communities, more and more complex things are being printed in 3D &ndash; you can even print a 3D printer with a 3D printer.</p>\r\n<p>(Image is the Arena logo printed as a 3D keyring)</p>', '2015-02-16', 'photo (3) edit.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 110782, '2015-02-17 10:29:54', 'The Arena logo printed as a 3D keyring', '2015-02-16 13:59:27', '2015-02-17 16:00:22', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'printing-in-a-new-dimension'),
(230, 'Google Vice President Vint Cerf: Print digital files, or risk losing them', 'The Telegraph reported on internet pioneer Vint Cerf’s warning that it is time to start preserving vast quantities of digital data before they are lost forever. ', '<p class="introduction">Speaking at a conference in San Jose, California, Vint Cerf cited a huge problem with our ability to preserve and run software over long periods of time. He said he felt a &lsquo;great burden&rsquo; to find a way to create digital formats which can still be accessed in thousands of years. For now, he advised the printing of treasured photos to ensure they are always to hand.</p>\r\n<p>This leads us to consider legal retention periods for business information &ndash; which sometimes span decades. Printing reams of documentation is not a practical solution and this makes a major issue of the decisions you take around storage.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, what can you do to ensure that those business critical documents you want to store for many years will remain accessible? Here are our top considerations concerning this issue.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>1. Take care if you choose to store &lsquo;hard copy&rsquo; files</h2>\r\n<p>Whenever paper files are moved or handled they are at risk of loss, serious damage or mild degradation. Long-term storage in itself is also a risk - picture dusty yellowed pages held together by rusted paperclips.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s Neil Maude comments; &ldquo;Some types of printed or hard copy documents are particularly sensitive, such as thermal print material, which we''ve seen degrade significantly in as little as 5 years &ndash; and become totally illegible within 10 years.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Carefully plan how you store hard copy documents. We would always recommend an electronic document and records management system (EDRMS) to safeguard your information from damage, degradation and disasters such as floods.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>2. Beware of simply saving files onto a disk</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>To reiterate Mr Cerf&rsquo;s good point, it can currently be a challenge to open an AmiPro word processing file, or even a Lotus 1-2-3 spreadsheet file - both common formats 15 years ago.</p>\r\n<p>Consider file structure - how will you find the file you want, when you want it - and how will you manage the disposal of documents at the end of their retention period?</p>\r\n<p>Add to this the risk of corrupted media and security concerns surrounding the flagging and prevention of file tampering or accidental file deletion and you face quite a challenge.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>3. Opt for scanned images and PDF/A files</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>We would expect that a scanned image file (eg; a CCITT Group4 compressed TIFF file) is likely to last for in excess of 30+ years as these formats are well understood and commonly used. Also look out for PDF/A files, which are specifically designed for archiving and defined in ISO19005-1:2005.</p>\r\n<p>Crucially, select a storage solution that supports whatever you put into it on the first day, making it usable on the last day &ndash; without degradation or expensive maintenance work.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>4. Establish the long-term development plan for your digital storage solution</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Always ask vendors about the future plans of any chosen EDRMS. If the system becomes obsolete, will you be able to extract, open and read the files stored within it &ndash; or move them to a new system?</p>\r\n<p>Plan for the day when the system will need replacement and consider how you will transfer your archived data to the next system. This will happen repeatedly as technology advances throughout the lifetime of your data archive.</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p>Article in The Telegraph: <a href="http://t.co/KNKastu8NV">http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/science-news/11410506/Print-out-digital-photos-or-risk-losing-them-Google-boss-warns.html&nbsp;&hellip;</a></p>\r\n<h2>Related articles</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../future-proofing-a-large-document-archive?tag=Expert+News" target="_blank"></a><a href="../../../articles/future-proofing-a-large-document-archive">Future-proofing a large document archive</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/confidential-files-left-on-trains-in-the-wrong-hands-or-just-on-the-move">Confidential files left on trains, in the wrong hands or on the move?</a></p>', '2015-02-17', 'bigstock-Technology-Frustration--31425881.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 153643, '2015-02-17 11:17:03', '', '2015-02-17 11:17:07', '2015-02-19 14:41:46', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'google-vice-president-vint-cerf-print-digital-files-or-risk-losing-them'),
(231, 'Leeds Legal Sector Breakfast Meeting', 'Going digital - turning paper into process\r\n\r\nAn event hosted by the Legal Support Network (LSN), in partnership with Arena Group\r\n\r\nDate: Wednesday 25 March 2015\r\nTime: 8am-9.30am', '<p><span class="introduction">An event hosted by the Legal Support Network (LSN), in partnership with Arena Group</span><strong>. <br /></strong></p>\r\n<h2>Going digital - turning paper into process</h2>\r\n<h3>Date: Wednesday 25 March 2015<br /> Time: 8am-9.30am<br />Location: Aspire, Infirmary Street, Leeds, LS1 2JP</h3>\r\n<p>Join our breakfast roundtable meeting to network with representatives from the operational side of local legal practices. Hear perspectives from the coal face in SME legal business about cutting the cost of producing and managing documents. Our chairperson will be editor-in-chief of Legal Practice Management magazine, Rupert Collins-White; he will facilitate an informal discussion on the topics outlined below.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Can firm go paper-less or paper-light? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Is a paperless legal business possible - or desirable? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mobility and remote working / document and data security / privacy </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cloud storage </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Information governance and legal compliance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Please contact Giles Gobey to register<strong>:<br /></strong></h2>\r\n<h3>If you would like to attend, please contact Giles Gobey using the details below.</h3>\r\n<h3>Tel: 0113 2135635 | Email: <a href="mailto:gilesg@arenagroup.net">GilesG@arenagroup.net</a><strong><br /></strong></h3>', '2015-02-23', 'lsn.jpeg', 'image/jpeg', 28968, '2015-02-23 16:10:37', '', '2015-02-23 16:10:38', '2015-03-06 12:23:25', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'leeds-legal-sector-breakfast-meeting'),
(232, 'Carbon Zero Heroes', 'Getting greener with Arena has never been easier since the launch of the Toshiba TEC Carbon Zero Scheme in 2009. We''ve been monitoring the positive outcomes of the initiative and come up with some superb facts about the impacts seen in 2014.', '<p class="introduction">Getting greener with Arena has never been easier since the launch of the Toshiba TEC Carbon Zero Scheme in 2009. We''ve been monitoring the positive outcomes of machines purchased by Arena Group customers during 2014, with superb results.</p>\r\n<p>The Toshiba TEC Carbon Zero Scheme ensures that every Toshiba&nbsp;Multi-Function Printer (MFP)&nbsp;is both helping the environment and making a positive contribution to local communities.</p>\r\n<p>Carbon offsetting allows for investment in projects that save the emission of, or absorb, an equivalent amount of CO<sub>2</sub> to that of the manufacture and&nbsp;shipment of each Carbon Zero MFP.</p>\r\n<p>Here''s our summary of the positive impacts related to the Toshiba Carbon Zero MFPs that were purchased by Arena Group customers in 2014.</p>\r\n<h2>Click the image below to enlarge it.</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/120_Carbon Zero Heroes 2014 Infographic.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/articles/232/contained_images/591df2a7b9f5_277_Carbon Zero Heroes 2014 Infographic.jpg?1425648291" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/119_Arena Group Carbon Zero Hero Review 2014.pdf" target="_blank">Download the full report.</a></p>', '2015-03-06', 'photo.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 94178, '2015-03-06 14:05:24', 'CarbonZero sticker', '2015-03-06 12:15:43', '2015-03-06 14:09:10', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'carbon-zero-heroes'),
(233, 'Arena Group Mini and Junior Run For All - Free places', 'Arena Group funds free places for children and young people taking part in the annual Jane Tomlinson Arena Group Mini and Junior Fun Run series.', '<p class="introduction">Arena Group funds free places for children and young people taking part in the annual Jane Tomlinson Arena Group Junior and Mini Fun Run series.</p>\r\n<p>The series has now been extended to include Leeds, York, Lincoln, and Sheffield. Our sponsorship covers all of the mini and junior runs.</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, managing director of Arena, said &ldquo;Mike Tomlinson  has created a lasting legacy to his wife Jane with these runs for the  whole family and we are proud to be part of that team.&nbsp; Supporting the  runs is a natural fit for Arena as many of our voluntary and charitable  activities focus on helping and supporting children and young people as a  way of giving back to local communities.&rdquo;<br />&nbsp;<br />The Junior and Mini  fun runs, part of the Jane Tomlinson Run for All, are expected to raise  thousands of pounds for local charities. This year children and schools  taking part will be encouraged to fundraise either for their own school  or for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal.</p>\r\n<h2>For more information, including how to enter the runs, visit:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><span><span>Lincoln: </span></span><a href="http://www.runforall.com/junior/lincoln/" target="_blank"><span><span>http://www.runforall.com/junior/lincoln/</span></span></a><br /><span><span> Leeds: </span></span><a href="http://www.runforall.com/junior/leeds/" target="_blank"><span><span>http://www.runforall.com/junior/leeds/</span></span></a><br /><span><span> Sheffield: </span></span><a href="http://www.runforall.com/junior/sheffield/" target="_blank"><span><span>http://www.runforall.com/junior/sheffield/</span></span></a><br /><span><span> York: </span></span><a href="http://www.runforall.com/junior/york/" target="_blank"><span><span>http://www.runforall.com/junior/york/</span></span></a></p>', '2015-03-12', 'SDP2232-1690.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 179545, '2015-03-12 15:45:25', '', '2015-03-12 15:45:27', '2015-03-19 08:45:16', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-group-mini-and-junior-run-for-all-free-places'),
(234, 'Biometrics: document security is at your fingertips ', 'As biometric security becomes more popular, we are seeing increased usage at the point of print.  Arena’s Head of Professional Services, Ian Fox, takes a look at the reasons why, outlining the rationale and benefits behind biometric authentication technology.', '<p class="introduction">As biometric security becomes more popular, we are seeing increased usage at the point of print. Arena&rsquo;s Head of Professional Services, Ian Fox, takes a look at the reasons why, and offers his top tips for implementation.</p>\r\n<p>An increased focus on document security has resulted in many organisations implementing print control solutions that have Find-Me capable print queues. This technology requires users to submit print jobs to a virtual queue where they are held until the user visits a printer of their choice to authenticate and release the jobs that they wish to print. The security benefit here lies in preventing confidential information from being left uncollected on printer output trays. <a href="../../../articles/putting-the-brakes-on-wasteful-printing" target="_blank">More info here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>There are a number of ways of authenticating (i.e identifying yourself) at the device in order to release your printed pages from the virtual queue. Typically these are PIN, username and password login, or some form of proximity technology such as key fobs or oyster style cards. However, all of these can potentially be lost, stolen or lent &ndash; not so secure.</p>\r\n<h2>Introducing biometrics</h2>\r\n<p>Biometric authentication has become increasingly popular over recent years. The most common device for printers is a fingerprint scanner but other forms exist, including retina and facial scanners.</p>\r\n<p>Unlike a card, PIN or fob, biometric data cannot be lost, lent or stolen - so only users that should have access to their documents can actually release them.</p>\r\n<p>There is also no more danger of forgetting your card or fob &ndash; it&rsquo;s unlikely that users will forget their fingers! Once biometric data is recorded, it is held centrally and cannot be lost.</p>\r\n<p>There are also a cost and efficiency benefits in that the need to buy cards and fobs or to set-up, provide and replace those items is removed.</p>\r\n<h2>Implementing biometric security &ndash; 4 simple steps</h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>1. Notify employees of the intention to use a biometric system &ndash; and who they should speak to if they have any concerns.</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s worth noting here that change in business is often met with reluctance, especially when that change involves the security of personal data such as fingerprints. For this reason it&rsquo;s wise to try anticipating some likely concerns and queries so that you can be prepared.</p>\r\n<p>For example: Users can be assured that only an encrypted mathematical representation of their fingerprint is stored, rather than an image of their fingerprint. In fact, it&rsquo;s virtually impossible to create an image from the mathematical representation that is stored in the database.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>2. Be prepared for challenges to the system based on any area that is protected by the law - such as religion or disability.</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Consider making allowances and providing alternatives for those who raise any legally justifiable objection to compliance with a biometric scanning policy. There have been cases of employers getting into hot water when challenged by employees who were physically unable to use such devices or who held strong religious objections to using them.</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>3. Check current legislation surrounding biometric security, and prepare policies to ensure the safety of all biometric data.</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol> <ol> </ol>\r\n<h3>4. Communicate clearly at every stage of implementation to reassure staff and deal with any concerns as early in the process as possible.</h3>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<h2>The future</h2>\r\n<p>Although it&rsquo;s relatively early days for biometric security in the workplace, it is now accepted and expected in areas such as airports which employ facial recognition software and iris scanners.</p>\r\n<p>There is a huge potential for the use of biometrics in business. If the technology is implemented correctly and accepted, soon you could be clocking in, authorising documents and making purchases all using biometrics.</p>\r\n<h2>For more information:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/join-us-for-our-spring-open-day" target="_blank">Visit us at our next open day </a>to see biometric devices and &lsquo;follow me&rsquo; print technology in action.</p>\r\n<h2>Related articles:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/views-from-the-top-coping-with-change" target="_blank">Views from the top: Managing Change</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/is-your-printer-data-secure" target="_blank">Is your printer data secure?</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/putting-the-brakes-on-wasteful-printing" target="_blank">Putting the brakes on wasteful and unnecessary printing</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h3>About Ian Fox</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/224/contained_images/93ca34f4a755_276_Ian Fox Jan15 large.jpg?1422352750" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="127" height="127" align="LEFT" />Professional Services Manager<br /> Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:ianF@arenagroup.net">ianF@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Ian Fox joined the Arena Group as a Systems Engineer in 1995. During his time at Arena he has gained a wealth of experience in helping organisations with their document related workflows. He now heads up the Professional Services department, which was formed in January 2011 with the aim of ensuring that existing and future Arena clients receive the best possible advice, solutions and support to enable them to manage and control their documents effectively.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-03-23', 'bigstock-Close-up-of-woman-eye-in-proce-82624028.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 299403, '2015-03-23 11:53:21', 'Biometrics', '2015-03-23 11:53:24', '2015-03-27 15:02:32', 7, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'biometrics-document-security-is-at-your-fingertips'),
(235, 'City of Lincoln sees a cracking start to the Arena Group Mini and Junior Run For All Series ', 'Hundreds of youngsters braved chilly temperatures to take part in the first ever Arena Group City of Lincoln Mini and Junior Run For All last weekend.', '<p class="introduction">Hundreds of youngsters braved chilly temperatures to take part in the first ever Arena Group City of Lincoln Mini and Junior Run For All last weekend.</p>\r\n<p>The fun got underway on Saturday when crowds turned out to cheer on children aged from 3-14 years who ran to raise money for a variety of charities, including the official partner charity, St Andrew&rsquo;s Hospice. &nbsp;All the youngsters crossing the finish line received a goody bag, T-shirt and medal to go with their sense of achievement.</p>\r\n<p>First boy across the finish line in the 2.8km mini run was Harry Denton followed by Ed Parry in second and William Webb in third. Emily Crookes won the girls mini run, Eleanor Clarkson was second and Molly Warburton came third.</p>\r\n<p>The 5K boys junior run was won by Harrison Wood who finished ahead of Jack Stocks in second with Jordon Blight taking third place. The girls junior run was won by Lucy Thornton, Rachel Nealon came second and Ellanor Brown took third place.</p>\r\n<p>Cllr Donald Nannestad, Portfolio Holder for Recreational Services and Health at the City of Lincoln Council, who took part in the event, said: &ldquo;A beautiful city like Lincoln lends itself to events such as this. The spectators helped generate a great atmosphere which I&rsquo;m sure all the runners appreciated.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, Arena Group managing director, said: &ldquo;Our first involvement with the City of Lincoln mini and junior runs has gone really well and we are delighted. It was fantastic to see so many children running and raising money for charity.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part in the Mini &amp; Junior Runs are encouraged to raise a small amount of money to help a local cause. They can choose any charity &ndash; or support the official partner charity. In 2015, the run will be supporting St Andrew&rsquo;s Childrens&rsquo; Hospice.</p>\r\n<p>St Andrew&rsquo;s Hospice is the only children&rsquo;s hospice in Lincolnshire and provides care for children and young adults who have a life limiting illness across the county. The Hospice provides specialist respite care on an in-patient and day-care basis, pain and symptom control and end of life care. The Hospice also provides care and support for the patient&rsquo;s family, including practical and emotional support, special care for siblings and bereavement support. The service costs &pound;1.8m a year to run &ndash; with only a tiny 3% of it coming from Government funding.</p>\r\n<p>Angela Greenfield, Events Co-Ordinator for St Andrews Hospice, commented; &ldquo;We&rsquo;re really pleased to have been chosen as the official charity of the Arena Group Mini &amp; Junior Run For All. We support around 90 children or young people and their families each year, who are all going through the toughest experience you can imagine.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-03-23', 'Start_Runners.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 145946, '2015-03-24 15:50:10', 'Lincoln RFA 2015', '2015-03-24 15:50:11', '2015-03-24 15:51:46', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'city-of-lincoln-sees-a-cracking-start-to-the-arena-group-mini-and-junior-run-for-all-series'),
(236, 'Youngsters from York get ready to run for charity!', 'Hundreds of big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of York on August 2nd to take on a free charity fun run challenge.', '<p class="introduction">Hundreds of big-hearted youngsters will hit the streets of York in August to take on a free fun run challenge in aid of charity.</p>\r\n<p>They will be taking part in the annual Arena Group York Mini and Junior Run, which is organised by Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s Run For All. The event is for children of all abilities, aged 3-14 years.</p>\r\n<p>The mini and junior run is one of the biggest races of its kind in the region and entry is free. York is just one of 4 locations this year, to find out more about events in Leeds, Sheffield and Lincoln, <a href="../../../articles/arena-group-mini-and-junior-run-for-all-free-places">click here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>This year&rsquo;s York runs will be held at 11.45am on <strong>Sunday August 2nd</strong>. There are two distances &ndash; 2.5km for youngsters aged 9-14 and 1.5km for children aged 3-8 &ndash; with both routes finishing on Knavesmire Road near the racecourse. (Mini run participants must be accompanied around the route by an adult.)</p>\r\n<p>Children taking part are encouraged to raise a small amount of money for the Jane Tomlinson Appeal or another charity of their choice but especially to support the official partner charity. This year that is The Family Fund, a UK-wide charity based in York, which for 40 years has been giving grants to low-income families&nbsp;raising a disabled or seriously ill child aged 17 and under.</p>\r\n<p>Family Fund Chief Executive Cheryl Ward said &ldquo;We are delighted to have been selected as Jane Tomlinson&rsquo;s charity partner for these runs and look forward to raising money to help even more families.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Adrian Fitzpatrick, managing director of Arena Group said: &ldquo;We are proud to be supporting the York Mini and Junior Run for the seventh year. The event has become a popular fixture in the sporting calendar for thousands of children and families. It&rsquo;s a great family day out and supports a very worthy local cause.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Mini and Junior Run event lead Keith Taylor said: &ldquo;The mini and junior runs are a brilliant way for kids to get actively involved on 10K day and enjoy the thrill of being cheered on by crowds of spectators. Both runs attract youngsters of all abilities and all those who take part should be very proud that local good causes benefit thanks to their efforts.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<h2>Further Information</h2>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.runforall.com/junior/york/" target="_blank">Register for the York Mini and Junior event</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/arena-group-mini-and-junior-run-for-all-free-places">About the Mini &amp; Junior Series - Lincoln, Leeds, Sheffield, York</a></p>', '2015-03-24', 'York_Launch_2015.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 144197, '2015-03-25 09:24:51', 'York RFA Launch 2015', '2015-03-25 09:24:52', '2015-03-26 14:01:47', 3, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'youngsters-from-york-get-ready-to-run-for-charity'),
(237, 'A busy month for Arena', 'April has been a great month for the Arena team, with an open day and Annual Conference!', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span class="introduction">April has been a great month for the Arena team<span class="introduction"> as we had both an open day and Annual Conference</span>. With the conference for Arena staff and the open day for you to visit, here''s an insight into both.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Open Day</h2>\r\n<p>We were delighted to welcome many of you to our open day in Wakefield on April 23<sup>rd</sup>.  It was a pleasure to have Armitage House full of guests, seeing what  Arena has to offer &ndash; both our services and the food and drinks that we  put on were well received!</p>\r\n<p>As is becoming a tradition at these events, one lucky guest will win a  hamper full of goodies, if you entered, the winner will be announced in  the coming week!</p>\r\n<p>Our clients typically feedback how informative the day is, seeing devices and software in action. They also enjoy the opportunity to network with other similarly minded business people and meeting the Arena team.</p>\r\n<p>We hope to welcome many more of you to Armitage House in the future - or to our next open day in October.</p>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Annual Conference</h2>\r\n<p>Our Annual Conference is a real highlight on the Arena Group calendar. This year it took place at Forest Pines  Hotel &amp; Golf Resort in North Lincolnshire.</p>\r\n<p>There was a brief business update, including a pre-recorded speech from Martin the Group HR Manager as he was en route to the London Marathon. Awards were handed out to employees for reaching 10 years'' service, and four who achieved 25 years'' service.</p>\r\n<p>Continued service excellence was the key theme of the talks.</p>\r\n<p>Following this, the audience was entertained by international  keynote speaker,  children&rsquo;s authorand comedian, Gavin Oattes.</p>\r\n<p>Gavin reminded the staff of the importance of having fun at work, his many ideas all illustrated with entertaining anecdotes.</p>\r\n<p>Armed with an understanding of the business''s plans and bags of inspiration, the Arena team are ready for the year ahead!</p>\r\n<p><img style="float: left;" src="../../assets/articles/237/contained_images/57a3f55ec668_280_CDM0SesXIAAqZBK.jpg?1430218057" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="172" height="307" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="../../assets/articles/237/contained_images/385c6bd56d90_279_Conference2015-14-redu.jpg?1430217957" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="250" /></p>', '2015-04-28', 'Conference2015-13.JPG', 'image/jpeg', 200609, '2015-04-28 10:49:27', '', '2015-04-28 10:49:31', '2015-04-28 14:19:43', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'a-busy-month-for-arena'),
(238, 'Jeremy Vine talks print', 'Jeremy was discussing printers with BBC’s technology consultant.\r\n\r\nWhile they were speaking about issues for home users, many of the points rang true for business as well.', '<p class="introduction">At Arena, we&rsquo;re always interested when people start to talk print. The recent Jeremy Vine show on BBC Radio 2 was no different. Jeremy was discussing printers with BBC&rsquo;s technology consultant.</p>\r\n<p>While they were speaking about issues for home users, many of the points rang true for business as well.</p>\r\n<h2>Jeremy guessed the top three printer problems as:</h2>\r\n<p>Jamming <br />Lack of connection with the PC <br />Supplies and toner related</p>\r\n<p><br />After plenty of chat about the complexity of printers and some of the difficulties experienced, one caller rang in to say he was delighted. He pays a monthly fee which pays for all of his ink.</p>\r\n<p>Further to that, he doesn&rsquo;t even have to order it; the printer sends a message when ink is low and his new one arrives ready. Jeremy and Zoe agreed that this sounded brilliant.</p>\r\n<p>This sounds remarkably similar to a service that Arena can provide for your business: a Managed Print Service (MPS). An MPS covers all of Jeremy&rsquo;s concerns.</p>\r\n<h2>No more jamming</h2>\r\n<p>With a specialist service team to come rushing to your aid, there will be someone to help fix any problems that you may have. And, with the expert care and attention that your machine gets if you do call the Arena team, you can be optimistic that you won&rsquo;t need us as often as you may expect.</p>\r\n<h2>Prompt communication</h2>\r\n<p>Arena has a large Professional Services team who are there to ensure that your devices are set up properly and working on your network. They are available on the phone or in person if any problems do arise.</p>\r\n<h2>No more toner issues</h2>\r\n<p>No more running out of toner or time spend looking for the cheapest shop. An MPS can automate the delivery of toner to you &ndash; despatched every time your ink drops below a certain level.  No more worrying about the cost either, ink and service can be covered with a predictable, regular bill.</p>\r\n<p><em>If you want to be as delighted as the caller to Jeremy&rsquo;s show, contact Arena Group to hear how a Managed Print Service can help you to save up to 30% on your print and copy costs.</em></p>', '2015-05-22', 'iStock_000012103102XLarge.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 335467, '2015-05-22 10:43:14', '', '2015-05-22 10:43:19', '2015-05-22 10:45:45', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'jeremy-vine-talks-print'),
(239, 'Change your office culture with a Managed Print Service', 'By working with the right print and copy provider you can realise significant savings, whilst also increasing the security of printed documentation. But where do you start?', '<h3><strong class="introduction">&ldquo;We have reduced paper consumption by 40% and our colour usage has reduced from 75% to around 25%.&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />Julie Greenland, ICT Project Manager, Liverpool Mutual Homes</h3>\r\n<p>Today, businesses of all shapes and sizes are looking to reduce waste and gain efficiencies. Reviewing operations in all areas is key to keeping your organisation competitive, but one element that often gets overlooked is printing.</p>\r\n<p>By working with the right provider you can realise significant savings, whilst also increasing the security of printed documentation. But where do you start?</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Here are our recommended steps for improving print and copy practices:</strong></h2>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Identifying the quick wins. Do you see any of the following in your organisation:</p>\r\n<ol> </ol> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Recycle bins overflowing with unclaimed prints</li>\r\n<li>Single side printing</li>\r\n<li>Unnecessary colour printing </li>\r\n<li>Accidental printing of excessive pages </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br />Create a print policy and raise awareness:</p>\r\n<ol> </ol> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Print policies can be implemented without the need for user interaction for certain types of document, e.g. set-up printing of emails in mono and double sided. </li>\r\n<li>Alternatively you can inform users about pending print jobs by displaying a popup that details the number of pages, how much colour is being used and even what the cost of the printing the document would be. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Communicate:</p>\r\n<ol> </ol> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Let the business know what you want and how it will benefit them. Clear communication is key to getting everyone on board.&nbsp; </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p>Training:</p>\r\n<ol> </ol> \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Choose your provider wisely and ensure that everyone has the necessary training and knowledge to implement the changes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When trying to implement a change it is always useful to contact an expert: Arena can help. Here are some of the ways that our print management software can help you print more efficiently. Don&rsquo;t just take our word for it though, read what our customers have to say.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Reduce wasteful print</strong></h2>\r\n<p>With follow me print, users can no longer send jobs to the printer and then forget about them.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I used to walk through the office and see a stack of uncollected paper on every printer. We&rsquo;ve already made a noticeable improvement and we expect to make significant financial savings just from reduced output.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href="../../../case_studies/community-integrated-care?service=Copy+and+Print">Case study: Community Integrated Care</a><br /></em></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Make economical printing the first thought</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Setting economical defaults means people have to actively choose if they want to print colour for example. You can even go a step further with rules so they do not have the option at all.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We are seeing a change in behaviour as our staff become more aware of what they are printing. Previously many of them simply didn&rsquo;t know how to change the settings so automating everything has really helped.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><em></em><a href="../../../case_studies/liverpool-mutual-homes?service=Copy+and+Print"><em>Case Study: Liverpool Mutual Homes</em></a></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Document safety at the front of mind</strong></h2>\r\n<p>No more pressing print and then running to the nearest machine to be sure that no one has seen your confidential documents. With a fob, card, fingerprint or password required to release documents, you can press print safe in the knowledge that the document will not be released without you being there.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I run payroll and other confidential documents; I like that I can send them to the printer safe in the knowledge that they will not print out until I go there to release them.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href="../../../case_studies/age-uk-scarborough-district?service=Copy+and+Print">Case Study: Age UK Scarborough and District</a><br /></em></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Use the most economical device for each print job</strong></h2>\r\n<p>As an audit is conducted before an MPS solution is installed, this ensures that there is the right mix of printers and copiers to meet your needs whilst minimising costs &ndash; as much as 30%!</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;We are seeing reduced colour printing - only when it&rsquo;s needed - and they are generally using the most economical device for the print job &ndash; even the head teacher no longer has a printer in his office.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href="../../../case_studies/ashville-college">Case Study: Ashville College</a><br /></em></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Then you can see the results of your changing office culture with predictable billing</strong></h2>\r\n<p>With MPS you can receive a single monthly invoice &ndash; no surprise bills. You also have access to reports to view activity by department or user so see where the greatest costs are.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;We&rsquo;re able to generate more detailed reports than before, which means we can more reliably calculate the true cost of each course. We also have more control over activity and forecasting is expected to become more accurate.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em><a href="../../../case_studies/middlesbrough-college">Case Study: Middlesbrough College</a></em><strong> <br /></strong></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Further Information</strong></h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/130">Check out our infographic: MPS in pictures!</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/7_MPS from Arena Group.pdf">Case studies: MPS customer stories</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/98_24_final MPS brochure for email.pdf">MPS Brochure</a></p>', '2015-05-28', 'bigstock-Businessman-with-Note-About-Cu-73539232 - small.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 127746, '2015-05-28 15:03:48', '', '2015-05-28 15:03:49', '2015-05-29 07:31:16', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'change-your-office-culture-with-a-managed-print-service'),
(240, 'How do you value your data?', 'The IRMS conference is Europe’s premier event for the records management profession and, whilst much of the content is technical and specific, it’s also a great way to get an overview of trends and themes in information management. Neil Maude shares his thoughts on the event.', '<p class="introduction">In mid-May this year, I spent a very pleasant couple of days at the annual IRMS conference.The IRMS conference is Europe&rsquo;s premier event for the records management profession and, whilst much of the content is technical and specific, it&rsquo;s also a great way to get an overview of trends and themes in information management. These days, it&rsquo;s hard to imagine an organisation which isn&rsquo;t dependent on its information &ndash; in all the forms that may include &ndash; to be successful.  So these themes are relevant for everyone.  Here are some of the key points that I took away from this year&rsquo;s conference.</p>\r\n<h2>Information as Currency</h2>\r\n<p>The stated theme for the conference was &ldquo;information as currency&rdquo;.  To me, this makes perfect sense &ndash; information can be a store of value, in the same way that money is a store of value.  In the same way, it&rsquo;s not much use unless you&rsquo;re actually doing something with it. Several of the conference presentations showed how organisations are unlocking the value of their information, making use of data and not just locking away records as evidence of what happened in the past.</p>\r\n<p>Digitisation of paper records was a common activity to these initiatives, which is unsurprising given that digital information is so much more easily shared around and sharing is clearly a vital step to unlocking value.  But much of our organisational information is still created in paper, for convenience and ease of use.  This paper is expensive to store and share, hence the need for digitisation.  Scanning may also seem to be an expensive process, but the take-away statistic was that it&rsquo;s been cheaper to store information digitally since 1996 &ndash; and the longer you have to store the information, the better it is to have it digital.</p>\r\n<h2>Data is Outliving Systems</h2>\r\n<p>Interestingly, the lifetime of information is typically longer than the usable life of the systems we use to store it.  For example, you may want to store &ndash; or be compelled to store &ndash; a digital document for 25 years.  But the typical life of an electronic document management system is 5 years &ndash; and I can&rsquo;t imagine using an EDMS from 25 years ago!  This mismatch is causing problems for Records and IT managers, who are faced with getting critical information out of obsolete systems and into new ones.  And there were a couple of real scare stories about the cost of doing so, especially in the context of public sector outsource arrangements!</p>\r\n<p>Of course, there is a straightforward solution for this.  When setting up a contract, make sure that your supplier is using open standards and that access to your information is possible.  Ideally, create a decommissioning plan at the outset of a contract, even if only in outline.  That way, you&rsquo;ll know what you&rsquo;re up against when your chosen solution needs replacement.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s also worth thinking about file formats at this point.  Wide adoption of PDF as a document storage standard &ndash; including the self-contained PDF/A archiving standard &ndash; gives a good method to ensure you&rsquo;ll be able to read a document in a future system.  PDF has always been associated with Adobe Systems, who were the original author.  But Adobe did the world of information management a great service by giving away the rights and now PDF is an ISO standard &ndash; it&rsquo;s not going to change any time soon, it&rsquo;ll be backwards compatible and anyone can use it.</p>\r\n<p>But don&rsquo;t forget about &ldquo;metadata&rdquo; &ndash; the information about the document, such as indexing data or usage history.  It can be very useful to know who created a document, who has looked at it or modified it to a new version &ndash; all of which counts towards legal admissibility, should you need it.  Unfortunately, whilst there are standards for this &ldquo;data about data&rdquo;, they&rsquo;re by no means widely adopted by records management software systems.  According to The National Archives (TNA), most electronic document record management systems are not designed to allow an easy export of data.  But you should still ask how you&rsquo;ll get back your audit trails and indexing data, when you move to a new system.  At Arena, we&rsquo;ve worked on projects where customers had the images from a previous system, but had to re-process all of them to get back to a well-ordered and useable structure (we OCR&rsquo;d the documents for them, recreating the indexes) because the outgoing vendor wouldn&rsquo;t release the index data from the previous system &ndash; an expensive problem that is best avoided at the outset.</p>\r\n<h2>Cloud is Everywhere</h2>\r\n<p>A third recurrent theme was the wide adoption of cloud computing and open source solutions.  I found this striking, given the type of information &ndash; key organisational data &ndash; being discussed.  Jurisdiction remains a crucial concern, however, as it&rsquo;s clearly more appropriate to keep some classes of data with the boundaries of your own network.  However, the increasing adoption of mobile working is an accelerating driver towards cloud computing.  An often-aired view was that the only way to avoid unauthorised use of consumer cloud services, such as free DropBox accounts, is for the organisation to provide a credible alternative.  Credible means usability &ndash; at least as nice to use as the free alternatives &ndash; as well as enterprise-grade security and other technical features.  There&rsquo;s a strong message for IT departments right there!</p>\r\n<p>The risk of open source was also a strong trend, driven by presentation to users via web and mobile &ndash; this move away from desktop computing means that Microsoft is no longer the only game in town.  Examples of this were wide ranging, including Department of Business Innovation and Skill and the US Navy &ndash; both of whom presented their open-source solution programmes at the conference.  Considerable cost savings were a big driver here.</p>\r\n<h2>Value</h2>\r\n<p>This brings me back to a question which I took away from the conference &ndash; just how do you put a value on your information?   A couple of presentations talked about valuing information in line with the investment made in creating the information.  For me, that&rsquo;s going to be misleading, if not plain wrong.  I view that as &ldquo;sunk cost&rdquo; which I can&rsquo;t recover and it&rsquo;s unlikely to be a true reflection of the value I can get from that information in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Some other metrics for information value include the cost to recreate or replace the information if it was lost and the impact of not having it (including potential fines). However, my favourite valuation is to estimate the opportunity value available within that information.  A trivial example is to imagine you have 2 complimentary products, A and B.  You have some customers who have bought one but not the other and you know there&rsquo;s a 50% chance of a purchase if you approach the customer with the additional product &ndash; armed with this knowledge you can easily put a value on your customer purchase records.</p>\r\n<p>But, in the end, it&rsquo;s clear that the value of organisational information is dependent on the context.  Realising that value is going to depend on IT, records managers (or whoever has ownership of the data) and business users all working together constructively.  That too, was a common discussion point throughout the IRMS conference!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>About Neil Maude</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/113/contained_images/8d9e8419f6d7_180_NeilM_ws.jpg?1359557446" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Electronic Document Management General Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:neilM@arenagroup.net">neilM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Neil joined the Arena Group in 2006 and has almost 20 years of    experience in the electronic document management industry, working with    both private and public sector customers.&nbsp; Neil sits on Arena&rsquo;s board   of  directors and manages the delivery operations of Arena&rsquo;s EDM   business.&nbsp;  His team spend their time developing software, implementing   solutions  for customers and providing after-sales software support   services, both  in the UK and internationally.</p>', '2015-06-15', 'bigstock-Stacks-Of-Coins-On-Graphs-And-68048935.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 251830, '2015-06-19 10:17:29', '', '2015-06-15 10:13:40', '2015-06-19 10:18:07', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'how-do-you-value-your-data');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `headline`, `summary`, `main_content`, `date`, `image_file_name`, `image_content_type`, `image_file_size`, `image_updated_at`, `image_alt`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`, `recycled`, `recycled_at`, `display`, `position`, `highlight`, `cached_slug`) VALUES
(241, 'Join us for our Stockton-on-Tees open day', 'We are preparing to host guests at our Stockton-upon-Tees office on Thursday August 13th. Guests will be in with a chance of winning a prize in our exclusive draw, hearing and seeing the latest technology in document management and grabbing a bite to eat with our team. Who''d miss it?', '<p class="introduction">Arena invites you to join us in our <strong>Stockton-on-Tees</strong> office<strong> on&nbsp;Thursday August 13th</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Grab a bite to eat with our team and enter the prize draw. We will be hosting sessions to demonstrate;</p>\r\n<h2 class="font_blue">Printing from mobile devices whilst controlling output:</h2>\r\n<p>See how to print documents wirelessly from android tablets and phones, or Apple iOS devices such as the iPad and iPhone. We will also show you how to control output volumes, set print <br /> defaults and monitor activity to manage the related costs.</p>\r\n<h2 class="font_blue">How you could save 30% on print and copy:</h2>\r\n<p>See how our print audit process can reveal areas for cost saving, efficiency building and productivity growth. Watch a typical managed print system in action and hear about our clients who are already benefiting.</p>\r\n<h2 class="font_blue">How to reduce your reliance on paper and work smarter:</h2>\r\n<p>How combining paper with electronic document management can transform your organisation and save you thousands. See our mstore software which is already proving invaluable to many businesses for managing archiving and processes such as accounts payable.</p>\r\n<h2 class="font_blue">How to control print and copy and reach your sustainability goals:</h2>\r\n<p>See the newest tools for monitoring and controlling print and copy output and check out the latest super-clean, carbon neutral devices.</p>\r\n<p>Download: <a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/125_Flyer_Aug 15.pdf" target="_blank">our Open Day Flyer</a></p>\r\n<h1>Exclusive Prize Draw</h1>\r\n<p>To enter simply book an open day appointment, and sign in on arrival.*</p>\r\n<h1><br />Book your place:</h1>\r\n<p>To ensure we maintain our high service levels on what is expected to  be a busy event, we are asking guests to pre-book appointments.</p>\r\n<p>Please speak to your Arena account manager, RSVP via phone: <strong>0344 863 8000</strong> or email <a href="mailto:marketing@arenagroup.net">marketing@arenagroup.net</a> to book your visit.</p>\r\n<h2>Venue:</h2>\r\n<p>Durham Tees Valley Business Centre, Primrose Hill Industrial Estate, Orde Wingate Way, Stockton-on-Tees, TS19 0GA</p>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><a href="../../assets/stored_documents/original/38_Competition Terms and Conditions Arena Group.pdf" target="_blank">*Terms and conditions apply.</a></h4>', '2015-06-30', 'bigstock-Welcome-Mat-3835957.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 323812, '2015-06-30 13:48:45', '', '2015-06-30 12:53:59', '2015-08-24 08:23:37', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'join-us-for-our-stockton-on-tees-open-day'),
(242, 'Arena is on the ESPO framework', 'Arena is delighted to have been awarded a place on the ESPO Document Scanning framework (860). This framework provides access to a range of document scanning solutions including the scanning, storage and disposal of documents, the supply of software, and consultancy services. Arena is in lot 3, provision of scanning software.', '<p class="introduction">Arena is delighted to have been awarded a place on the ESPO Document Scanning framework (860). This framework provides access to a range of document scanning solutions including the scanning, storage and disposal of documents, the supply of software, and consultancy services. Arena is in lot 3, provision of scanning software.</p>\r\n<h2>What this means for you:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>There is no need to run a full EU procurement process; ESPO has done the work for you. The framework is free to access and is compliant with UK/EU procurement legislation.</li>\r\n<li>Secure knowledge that the innovative solutions and products on offer have been independently validated as providing best-in-class value for money.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You      can be confident in Arena as we have been vetted and comply with a range      of accreditations, standards and legislation including BS10008 for      Evidential Weight and Legal Admissibility.</li>\r\n<li>Pre-agreed      terms &amp; conditions to underpin all orders so no need to worry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Who is it for?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Schools &amp; Academies</li>\r\n<li>Local Authority Establishments</li>\r\n<li>Police &amp; Emergency Services</li>\r\n<li>NHS &amp; HSC Bodies</li>\r\n<li>Central Government Departments &amp; their      agencies</li>\r\n<li>Registered Charities</li>\r\n<li>Registered Social Landlords</li>\r\n<li>And many more&hellip;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>About ESPO</h2>\r\n<p>ESPO is a local authority owned purchasing and supply consortium with over 30 years&rsquo; experience in public sector procurement. ESPO is a not for profit, self-funded organisation.</p>\r\n<p>All ESPO frameworks are let in full compliance with UK procurement regulations (and the EU procurement directive). The specialist buying teams have extensive experience of providing high quality procurement solutions to the public sector on a nationwide basis.</p>\r\n<h2>About Arena&rsquo;s electronic document management software, mstore</h2>\r\n<p>With many hundreds of clients within the UK and globally, Arena&rsquo;s <strong>m</strong>store software brings the tools and capabilities necessary to bring electronic document management to your organisation, allowing you to achieve your goals of process efficiency, cost reduction and business transformation.&nbsp; By providing a proven document processing platform, <strong>m</strong>store allows you to also implement security and governance best practices, including meeting the requirements of BS10008, the code of practice for legal admissibility of electronic documents. Working with Arena offers assured value for money for the customer throughout the entire application lifecycle as we manage the design, delivery and updates.</p>\r\n<p><strong>m</strong>store is independently audited by Microsoft, achieving both Windows 7 and 8 logo certification.&nbsp; The solution is deployed on Microsoft servers, making implementation straightforward with the most common IT platform and can be delivered either on-premise or in a cloud deployment. The web client is compatible with IE 8, 9, 10 and 11, Google Chrome, Firefox, Opera, Safari on OSx, iMac, iPad and Android, providing maximum compatibility your current and future infrastructure.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>More information:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://www.espo.org/Frameworks/Buildings-Facilities-Management/390-Document-Scanning-Services">https://www.espo.org/Frameworks/Buildings-Facilities-Management/390-Document-Scanning-Services</a></p>', '2015-07-27', 'ESPO-logo-2014-PMSGreen-HighRes.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 140223, '2015-07-27 10:17:57', '', '2015-07-27 10:17:58', '2015-08-03 15:05:58', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'arena-is-on-the-espo-framework'),
(243, 'Is your school compliant with document retention requirements?', 'With retention periods for pupil records ranging from days to decades, how do you ensure that you are compliant? Although the examples are for school documents, the advice applies to all sectors.', '<p>Here is a small selection of the records that your school should be keeping &ndash; and how long for.</p>\r\n<p>For a full list, view the <a href="http://www.irms.org.uk/images/resources/infoguides/records_management_toolkit_for_schools_version_4_may_2012.pdf">Information Records Management Toolkit.</a></p>\r\n<p><em>Child protection files - DOB +25 years<br /> Complaints files &ndash; Date of resolution of complaint +6 years<br /> Attendance registers &ndash; Date of register +3 years<br /> Pupil files in secondary schools &ndash; Pupil&rsquo;s DOB +25 years<br /> Correspondence relating to authorised absence and issues &ndash; date of absence +2 years<br /> Examination results &ndash; year of examination +6 years (external), +5 years (internal)<br /> Advice and information to parents regarding educational needs &ndash; Closure +12 years<br /> Parental permission slips for school trips where there has been a major incident &ndash; DOB of the pupil involved +25 years (slips for all pupils on the trip must be retained)<br /> Record of homework set &ndash; current year +1 year<br /> </em></p>\r\n<p>Arena&rsquo;s General Manager, Neil Maude, takes us through the difficulties that can be caused by keeping all of these documents &ndash; and offers a solution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Storing your paper documents<br /> </strong>After viewing the above list &ndash; which is just a fraction of the full requirements - we wouldn&rsquo;t blame you for worrying about storage space, finding documents for a Freedom of Information (FOI) request, disposing of documents when you are legally required to, or simply keeping a complete record of them.</p>\r\n<p>Further to this, the Data Protection Act 1998 states that records should be kept for no longer than necessary. Even if you have lots of space, you cannot just fill it with documents as you may need to access them for a Freedom of Information request, or destroy them at the end of their retention periods.&nbsp; Managing the different requirements can be very labour intensive.</p>\r\n<p>If you add to this the fact that the FOI act 2000 states that the school must maintain a list of records that have been destroyed, and who authorised their destruction, there is a lot to have covered in your records management policy.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>An alternative solution</strong></p>\r\n<p>Space issues can be addressed by scanning paper files and storing them electronically. Provided you have a system that enables compliance with BS10008 (a standard and code of practice which ensures the evidential weight of documents stored electronically), you can destroy the original paper documents and still have a legally admissible record should you need it.<br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p>A good electronic document and records management system (EDRMS) will apply retention rules to each part of a classification of documents stored in the system. Documents are stored against the appropriate classification (e.g.; attendance, admission, parental permission forms, SEN statements). The system can then apply rules to dispose of documents or present them for review on a set date &ndash;possibly with reference to pupil specific information, such as date of birth.&nbsp; Those documents with a fixed disposal date can be automatically weeded from the files, keeping you compliant with your policies. This approach dramatically reduces the management time associated with retention and completely eliminates the issues associated with large physical paper archives.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For further information on how Electronic Document Management can help ensure your school is compliant, contact Arena Group at <a href="mailto:info@arenagroup.net">info@arenagroup.net</a> or 0344 863 8000.</p>\r\n<h3>About Neil Maude</h3>\r\n<p><img src="../../../assets/articles/113/contained_images/8d9e8419f6d7_180_NeilM_ws.jpg?1359557446" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="100" align="left" /></p>\r\n<p>Electronic Document Management General Manager<br />Tel: 0800 863 8000 | Email: <a href="mailto:neilM@arenagroup.net">neilM@arenagroup.net</a></p>\r\n<p>Neil joined the Arena Group in 2006 and has almost 20 years of    experience in the electronic document management industry, working with    both private and public sector customers.&nbsp; Neil sits on Arena&rsquo;s board   of  directors and manages the delivery operations of Arena&rsquo;s EDM   business.&nbsp;  His team spend their time developing software, implementing   solutions  for customers and providing after-sales software support   services, both  in the UK and internationally.</p>', '2015-08-26', 'iStock_000015150766Small.jpg', 'image/jpeg', 289546, '2015-08-26 08:39:25', '', '2015-08-26 08:39:26', '2015-09-03 10:28:15', 7, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0, NULL, 'is-your-school-compliant-with-document-retention-requirements');
