(39, 'Cookies & Privacy', 'privacy_statement', 'Cookies & Privacy', 44, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span></strong>In  2011 there was a change to European Law, which is aimed at giving  website users more control over the data stored about them. You can read  more about it here <a href="http://www.ico.gov.uk/">http://www.ico.gov.uk/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are cookies?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cookies are very small text files that some websites store on your computer or mobile device when you visit them.</p>\r\n<p>Cookies do lots of different jobs, like letting you navigate between pages efficiently and remembering your preferences.</p>\r\n<p>We use cookies on our website to make your browsing experience  better. By using this website you accept our use of cookies for the  following functions.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Essential</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>These cookies let you move around the website and  use essential features like secure areas, shopping baskets and online  billing. <strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Performance</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>These cookies collect information on site usage &ndash;  all the collected information is anonymous and is only used to help us  improve how the website works.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Functionality</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong> </strong>These cookies are used to provide specific services  or to remember settings to improve your visit.This could include,  storing settings you''ve applied, such as layout, text size, or to  indicate if you have &lsquo;logged in&rsquo; to the website.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>We do not use cookies to gather any information about you  that could identify you or be used to track where you''ve been on the  internet.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<h2>Controlling the information websites can collect</h2>\r\n<p><strong><br /> </strong>You can manage your browser settings to accept  or reject all cookies or individually by website. You can also set your  browser to prompt you when a website would like to store a cookie on  your computer. All browsers&rsquo; settings are different and we would  recommend you use the &lsquo;help&rsquo; option in your browser menu to check your  settings, or check our <a href="http://eskimosoup.co.uk/managing_cookies" target="_blank">quick guide to managing cookies,</a>which covers the most popular browsers.</p>\r\n<h1></h1>\r\n<h1>Privacy</h1>\r\n<h2>1. Pledge on Privacy</h2>\r\n<p>The term "personal data" as used in this Policy refers to information such as your name, e-mail address or mailing address, that can be used to identify you. Arena Group will not process your personal data without your consent. In processing your personal data, we pledge to fully comply with internationally recognized standards of privacy protection. In so doing, we ensure compliance by our staff with strict standards of security and confidentiality. The next sections explain how and when we collect personal data from you.</p>\r\n<h2>2. Intended Use of Personal Data</h2>\r\n<p>Most of our services do not require any form of registration, allowing you to visit our site without telling us who you are. However, some services may require registration. When you register with us, you may need to complete certain fields (some are required and some are optional), as well as choose a user name and password. In these situations, if you choose to withhold any personal data requested by us, it may not be possible for you to gain access to certain parts of the site and for us to respond to your query. Arena Group process personal data for specific and limited purposes which we inform you about when we ask you for information. For example, we may collect and use personal data to provide you with products or services, to bill you for products and services you request, to market products and services which we think may be if interest to you, or to communicate with you for other purposes. Information you send to our customer service department is used only to help resolve your problem and is otherwise kept private. Arena Group keeps your data only for as long as is reasonably needed for such purposes and in accordance with any applicable legal or ethical reporting or documentation retention requirements.</p>\r\n<h2>3. Non-Disclosure of Information</h2>\r\n<p>Arena Group will not sell, share, or otherwise distribute your personal data to third parties outside the Arena Group group. However, personal data may occasionally be transferred to third parties who act for or on behalf of Arena Group, or in connection with the business of Arena Group, for further processing in accordance with the purpose(s) for which the data were originally collected. Where disclosure of personal data to a third party is likely or necessary for whatever reason, Arena Group will, wherever possible, endeavour to ensure that the disclosure and intended use of the data are clearly indicated. Such third parties may operate different privacy policies. However, we endeavour to ensure that such third parties provide the same level of protection as Arena Group and, where appropriate, we will contractually require them to process data transferred only for the purposes expressly authorized by Arena Group. Your consent may always be revoked at a later date. If consent is revoked Arena Group may not be able to carry out certain requests made by you. Arena Group will, where practicable, inform third parties to whom your data have been transferred of your withdrawal of consent.</p>\r\n<h2>4. Right of Access</h2>\r\n<p>You have the right to access and update your personal data or to require their deletion. We endeavour to ensure that personal data are up-to-date, accurate, and complete. If you wish to access or correct your personal data held by us, please contact the webmaster. Your requests will be dealt with in a prompt and proper manner. No charge will be levied for complying with a correction request, however, for all other requests Arena Group may charge a small fee to cover its costs. Requests to delete personal data will be subject to any applicable legal and ethical reporting or document filing or retention obligations imposed on Arena Group.</p>\r\n<h2>5. Security and Confidentiality</h2>\r\n<p>To ensure the security and confidentiality of personal data that Arena Group collects on-line, Arena Group uses data networks protected, by industry standard firewall and password protection. Access to personal data is restricted to those employees who have a need to use the data and who have been trained to handle such data properly and observe strict standards of confidentiality. If an employee breaches our policies and procedures he/she will be disciplined accordingly. Staff compliance with our policies and procedures is regularly audited and reviewed. While we cannot guarantee against any loss, misuse or alteration to data, we try to prevent such unfortunate occurrences.</p>\r\n<h2>6. Anonymous Data and "Cookies"</h2>\r\n<p>Most of the information that Arena Group collects from its website(s) is anonymous information, such as the pages you visit and searches you perform. When you visit our website we do not collect any personal data from you unless otherwise authorized by you. Anonymous information is processed by Arena Group to help improve the contents of the site and to compile aggregate statistics about individuals using our site for internal, market research purposes. In so doing, Arena Group may install "cookies" that collect the first level domain name of the user (e.g., "bigmail.com" from an e-mail address of "john@bigmail.com") and the date and time of access. "Cookies" by themselves cannot be used to discover the identity of the user. A "cookie" is a small piece of information which is sent to your browser and stored on your computer''s hard drive. Cookies do not damage your computer. You can set your browser to notify you when you receive a "cookie", this will enable you to decide if you want to accept it or not.</p>\r\n<h2>7. Spamming</h2>\r\n<p>Arena Group does not condone "spamming". Spamming is defined as sending unsolicited e-mails, usually of a commercial nature, in large numbers and repeatedly to individuals with whom the sender has had no previous contact or who have declined to receive such communications. In contrast, where Arena Group believes that certain product, or other information is of importance to you it reserves the right to inform you by e-mail whilst giving you the choice of opting out of such service.</p>\r\n<h2>8. Links to Other Sites</h2>\r\n<p>This Privacy Policy applies only to Arena Group'' websites to the exclusion of third party websites. Arena Group may provide links to other websites which we believe may be of interest to our visitors. We aim to ensure that such websites are of the highest standard. However, due to the nature of the World Wide Web, Arena Group cannot guarantee the standards of every website link it provides or be responsible for the contents of non- Arena Group sites.</p>\r\n<h2>9. Contact Arena Group</h2>\r\n<p>If you have any queries or complaints about our compliance with this Privacy Policy, or if you would like to make any recommendations or comments to improve the quality of our Privacy Policy, please contact the webmaster. This privacy policy is effective as of January 1, 2004. We aim to constantly improve the tools available to you to manage the data that you provide to us. Please refer to this page from time to time to review these and other new features.</p>', '2011-01-11 11:00:19', '2012-06-18 14:12:56', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(40, 'Terms of Use', 'terms_of_service', 'Terms of Use', 45, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<h2><strong>Legal notice</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The information in this site is published for general information purposes only. We accept no responsibility for any loss or damage resulting from reliance upon any information contained herein. If you enter the Arena Group Website ("the Site") you agree to be bound by the Terms of Use set out below.</p>\r\n<a id="eztoc2067_0_1" name="eztoc2067_0_1"></a>\r\n<h2><strong>Terms of Use</strong></h2>\r\n<p>In accessing and exploring the Site you hereby agree with Arena Group that the following Terms of Use are applicable to you as the user:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You will observe and comply with all proprietary notices and copyright information exhibited in the Site</li>\r\n<li>You will accept absolute responsibility for the protection of your computer system (which includes but is not limited to the computer hardware, software, stored data and the computer systems of third parties connected or having access to your computer system) whilst you are accessing, using and downloading from the Site</li>\r\n<li>You will accept absolute responsibility for the programmes and data downloaded or received from the Site ensuring that it is free from destructive or corrupting elements such as, but not limited to, viruses, worms and trojans</li>\r\n<li>Arena Group does not accept any responsibility whatsoever for any unauthorised third party access to and use of any data transmitted electronically to Arena Group by you</li>\r\n<li>Arena Group does not accept any responsibility whatsoever in respect of the effect of any Website which can be accessed through or via a hyper-link or otherwise to and from the Site</li>\r\n<li>Arena Group makes all reasonable efforts to ensure the accuracy of the information contained in the Site, however certain inaccuracies or mistakes may arise and you will have no claim against Arena Group in respect of these or their effect. Arena Group will correct any inaccurate information as soon as this is brought to its attention. Please direct any corrections or observations for the attention of the Marketing Manager, Tom Whiteley.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>A written copy of our full terms of business and legal obligations is available on request.</p>', '2011-01-11 11:01:24', '2011-02-08 10:31:34', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(41, 'Scanning Bureau Services - Document Scanning', 'edm_for_storing_protecting_and_retrieving_critical_documents', 'Document Scanning', 46, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p class="introduction"><img style="float: right;" src="../../../assets/page_contents/41/contained_images/c910527c0160_185_paper-stack1.jpg?1361468618" border="0" alt="" hspace="10" vspace="10" width="250" />Converting paper documents to electronic format can make them quicker and easier to access and use whilst also offering added security and protection from damage or loss.</p>\r\n<h2>Our Scanning Bureau Service</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Scanning of mono and colour documents such as invoices and client files </li>\r\n<li>Smaller documents such as tickets and receipts linked to expense claims</li>\r\n<li>Large documents such as A0 plans, either mono or colour</li>\r\n<li>Addition of index data (eg; bar codes or other references) for easy and quick document retrieval</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Better systems and processes always produce cost savings and reduced errors and wastage whilst creating &lsquo;greener&rsquo; ways of working.</p>\r\n<h2>How it works</h2>\r\n<h3>1. Collect and scan</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We collect your files using our own fleet of vans, store them securely and complete the scanning at our site in order to cause minimum disruption to your business</li>\r\n<li>We provide a full end-end service including preparation of documents by removing fastenings, clips and staples</li>\r\n<li>Blank page removal software means you only pay for the information you want.</li>\r\n<li>If you need access to the files whilst we&rsquo;re processing them, we can offer an urgent retrieval process.</li>\r\n<li>At full capacity our bureau can scan upto 600,000 documents per month.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>2. Supply electronic files</h3>\r\n<p>Arena supplies your documents to you in electronic format, most commonly PDF. These files can be passed to you in various different ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>DVD, with encryption for secure data transfer</li>\r\n<li>Electronic transfer for storage in your own copy of <strong>m</strong>store, Arena''s own software for electronic document and records management (EDRMS)</li>\r\n<li>Our Hosted Service - a secure online repository which allows you to store, search, view, share and print documents, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week from anywhere with an internet connection.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>3. Return or destroy</h3>\r\n<p>Once you have approved the electronic files we can shred the paper documents in our industrial shredder, or return them to you.&nbsp; Shredded documents are pulped and recycled, in line with our environmental policy.</p>\r\n<p>With this service, you do not have to make any bulk capital outlay&nbsp;as&nbsp;we only charge as each stage of work is completed. Large archives can be tackled in stages or as regular collections, to provide the conversion benefits with minimal impact on your cashflow.</p>\r\n<h2>Download our free guides</h2>\r\n<p>A consultation with one of our experts can very quickly point you in the right direction when it comes to digitising your paper documents. In the meantime we have produced a number of helpful guides which can help you to answer some basic questions.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/97_ARENA_mstore_ARCHIVING.pdf" target="_blank">Scanning Bureau Guide</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../free-guides-31-ways-to-reduce-paper-usage.pdf">31 Ways to Reduce Paper Usage</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../free-guides-top-tips-on-data-protection.pdf">Top Tips on Data Protection</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Useful Links</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/110">Questioning the Cost of Purchasing</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/97?tag=Expert+News">Tips on business continuinty planning</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../articles/38?tag=Expert+News">Safe, secure and speedy - Arena''s Scanning Bureau</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">More about <strong>m</strong>store - software for electronic document management</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-01-12 13:02:01', '2014-04-16 08:12:47', '', '', 1, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(44, 'Case Studies', 'case_studies_2', 'Case Studies', 49, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '', '2011-01-17 14:46:21', '2011-02-08 10:22:06', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(45, 'Partners', 'partners', 'Partners', 50, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Arena Group is partnered with several leading device manufacturers. We can provide a comprehensive print audit and prescribe the most suitable machines for your business needs.</p>\r\n<p>Our solutions cover low to high print volumes, colour and mono devices plus a range of software to help you control and monitor your print/copy output. We can also provide specialist machines such as duplicators and wide format systems for large scale printing of documents such as maps, structural plans and technical diagrams.</p>\r\n<p>We are also partnered with Blue Logic, a leading supplier of IT solutions.&nbsp;Blue Logic&nbsp;can advise on or supply networking, cabling, hardware and software - or provide a full IT support service.</p>\r\n<p>Click the logos below for further information about our partners and their product ranges:</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.toshiba.eu" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/7b8c9371c30b_23_Toshiba.jpg?1297084897" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.kyocera.com" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/0751f147527f_24_Kyocera.jpg?1297084933" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.ricoh-europe.com" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/51f72b0e511d_25_Ricoh.jpg?1297084953" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.riso.co.uk" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/3f89cc52ae6e_26_Riso.jpg?1297084965" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.utax.com" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/7c3c67dd7c3b_27_UTAX.jpg?1297084974" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.bluelogic.co.uk" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/d3538ee15b5f_115_Blue-Logic-Computers-RGB small.jpg?1329128211" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="160" /></a><a href="http://eset.co.uk/?gclid=CPevr_Xy_6YCFYHb4AodnQfxeg" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/bc4d57e87d28_34_ESET.jpg?1297432065" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.equitrac.com/" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/ed47a4d01f31_35_Equitrac.jpg?1297432111" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.rerite.com.au/Toshiba_Main.htm" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/e2040d3478f4_36_ToshibaReRite.jpg?1297432139" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://welcome.hp.com/country/uk/en/cs/home_c.html" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/538e1351fb44_37_HP.jpg?1297432161" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.konicaminolta.co.uk/" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/8f4ca2ca105f_38_KonicaMinolta.jpg?1297432185" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.planetpress.com.au/" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/2e414d551420_39_PlanetPress.jpg?1297432210" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.pcounter-europe.com/products.cfm" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/0b034f822289_40_PCounter.jpg?1297432228" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a>&nbsp; <a href="http://www.fmaudit.com/" target="_blank"><img src="../../../assets/page_contents/45/contained_images/e30a727cf6f1_41_FMAudit.jpg?1297432249" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="170" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2011-02-01 13:15:29', '2012-06-21 08:04:43', '', '', 1, 3, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(47, 'Customer Satisfaction', 'customer_satisfaction', 'Customer Satisfaction', 52, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p class="introduction">Customers are asked to score each area below on a scale of 1-5. A score of 3 or above represents satisfaction.</p>\r\n<p>Tasked with travelling around our existing client base, our Customer Relationship Managers are&nbsp;on hand&nbsp;to speedily handle any queries and make sure that&nbsp;our clients are satisfied and&nbsp;receiving maximum value in return for&nbsp;their investment in Arena. Our CRMs contact any client who raises a concern, and we endeavour to resolve their issues.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="../../../page/our-service-statistics" target="_blank">&gt; View our service statistics</a>.</p>\r\n<h6>*<em>Feedback from&nbsp;approximately&nbsp;500 surveys&nbsp;gathered from July-December 2014 by our Customer Relationship Managers who continually visit our clients to ensure that their needs are met.</em></h6>', '2011-02-02 11:45:55', '2015-03-04 10:45:13', '', '', 1, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(48, 'The Arena Story', 'the_arena_story', 'The Arena Story', 53, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>Arena came into being in October 1991. At the start, the workforce comprised of six partners, three sales staff and a secretary. Of the original ten employees, six are still part of Arena Group and this low turnover of staff continues today. The Company started with no customers and the first Partners meeting was held in a mobile caravan. During those first few years everyone worked every hour possible and since then the company has grown to encompass 5 sites employing around 120 people.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1993</strong> - Arena achieved Major Account Status with Toshiba. The Systems Division was set up, as the Company worked to expand in a developing area. The use of and possibilities for copiers to be networked to computers became a reality and the Systems Division started selling, installing and servicing networks, computers, and printers.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1994</strong> - The Company achieved ISO9002 registration, which meant that we were achieving consistent high standards of quality on all the work we undertook. In the same year, the Company achieved the status of Investors In People from the Training and Enterprise Council.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1996</strong> - The Company moved its administrative facility to its present location at Armitage House.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1999</strong> - With the acquisition of COS UK Limited, the Company became the largest distributor of Toshiba Copiers and Facsimile Machines in the UK.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2001</strong> &ndash; Arena Group acquired CP Independent.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2003</strong> - Arena Group acquired Sterling Business Systems and WRG Limited.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2005</strong> - Office 21 became part of the Arena Group and then M&amp;S Reprographics Limited based in Bolton, Lancashire came under the Arena umbrella. This acquisition offered a superb opportunity for the group to develop and grow in the North West of England.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2006</strong> - Mitral Systems Ltd joined Arena Group - one of the leading providers of Workflow, Document Management and bespoke software solutions. From a beautiful rural base on the outskirts of Huddersfield this specialist team have a client base which covers the UK and beyond. The addition of Mitral into the Arena Group family creates the perfect platform for the Company to move away from selling and servicing just photocopiers to the development and implementation of a Company who provide document management solutions.&nbsp;Arena appeared in the Sunday Times 100 Best Small Companies to Work for list and won the National Chamber of Commerce award for Excellence in People Development.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2007</strong> - Launch of CSR community projects with Leeds Ahead and Barnardos. All Arena employees are encouraged to volunteer two days annually to help with charitable community projects. In 2007 Arena became a Patron of the Leeds, York and North Yorkshire Chamber of Commerce in support of regional businesses.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2008</strong> - Arena opened its dedicated service, training academy and logistics center in Garforth, Leeds. In 2008 we also won the British Chamber of Commerce award for Excellence in Customer Service.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2009</strong> - Arena entered a strategic partnership with Kyocera.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2010</strong> - Arena entered a strategic partnership with Konica Minolta, further expanding our copy and print portfolio.</p>', '2011-02-02 14:03:04', '2011-02-15 15:58:30', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(49, 'mstore for Transport and Logistics', 'edm_for_transport_and_logistics', 'mstore for Transport and Logistics', 54, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p><span class="introduction"><img class="image_right" src="../../../assets/page_contents/49/contained_images/615db652a97a_120_Boxes_ws.jpg?1329134805" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="180" />The transport sector operates on tight profit margins and timescales. Customer expectations of deliveries are increasingly demanding and with rising fuel and competitive pressures, efficiency is more important than ever.</span></p>\r\n<p>Our focus is always on your business, we work closely with you to understand your business and then produce workflow systems to develop with you making you more profitable, ensuring security of your documents, minimising your archive costs and speeding up retrieval of documents.</p>\r\n<p>We have created our own software, <strong>m</strong>store, which can be integrated into your business systems and with any existing software, whether bespoke or brand packages. <strong>m</strong>store is very flexible and highly configurable, because we are the software author, we can be flexible on customisation and development to meet your needs</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Integration and tailoring of IT systems with those of customers and suppliers</li>\r\n<li>Fast and accurate access to customer delivery records to assist quick responses to customer queries and ensure invoices are paid on time</li>\r\n<li>Creating a cost-efficient audit trail</li>\r\n<li>Rapid confirmation that goods have been delivered</li>\r\n<li>Helping customers to respond quickly to changing demands in their markets</li>\r\n<li>Linking proof of delivery to speedy invoicing and securing cash flow.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Downloads:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/110_ARENA_mstoreTransport.pdf" target="_blank">EDRMS in Transport and Logistics (PDF)</a></p>\r\n<h2>Further Information:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">More about <strong>m</strong>store</a></p>', '2011-02-02 14:22:55', '2014-07-11 13:58:12', '', '', 1, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(50, 'Request a Duplicate Invoice', 'request_a_duplicate_invoice', 'Request a Duplicate Invoice', 55, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p>You can use the form below to request another invoice if you have misplaced the one you have been previously given.&nbsp;Please note that both fields are required.</p>', '2011-02-03 10:21:05', '2011-02-08 16:05:56', '', '', 1, 1, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(51, 'mstore for Purchasing', 'edm_for_accounts_payable', 'mstore for Purchasing', 56, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<p><span class="introduction"><img class="image_right" src="../../../assets/page_contents/51/contained_images/c116f249a287_121_iStock_000015909008Medium.jpg?1329135093" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" width="180" /> </span><span class="introduction">The purchase-to-pay process is an area in which many organisations are increasingly looking to improve spend control and management of information about costs whilst increasing efficiency.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Reducing your back office costs can add considerably to your bottom line and help your business to remain competitive &ndash; and streamlining your purchase-to-pay systems can play a core part in both cost reduction and improved cashflow.</p>\r\n<p>The Arena Group has developed&nbsp;<strong>m</strong>store for Purchasing, an electronic document and records management system (EDRMS). <strong>m</strong>store  delivers a user-friendly mechanism to improve the document  storage, retrieval, processing and archiving process. This is combined with functionality to improve&nbsp;legal compliance, keep sensitive files secure and analyse and report on costs and activity.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits Arena&rsquo;s mstore brings to the purchase-to-pay process:</strong></p>\r\n<h2>Efficiency<strong><br /></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Simplify the purchasing process </strong>to make it easier for employees to buy what they need.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Increase transparency</strong> through enabling quick access to complete information and reporting tools.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Minimise document loss and filing errors</strong> - records never leave the system and are processed electronically.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Link related documents for quick and simple review</strong>. For example, invoices can be matched to purchase orders.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Manage, link and view a multitude of document formats</strong> including emails, images/scanned pages and MS Office files.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Governance</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Prevent unnecessary purchases</strong> through improved enforcement of your authorisation policies, in support of ISO 9001 Compliance.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Track the purchasing processes</strong> through various stages and export reports for further analysis.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Free up storage space</strong> through compliance with BSI10008, which allows you to destroy paper copies.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Review activity by user, action or document type</strong> to evidence that documents have been processed correctly and in a timely fashion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Document Security</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Secure documents</strong> from deletion or over-writing.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Protect confidential information</strong> from documents that need to be shared with third parties and limit user-access to sensitive files.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Disaster recovery and resilience</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Digitise documents</strong> to protect them from physical damage or loss.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Reduce paper consumption</strong> and the movement of paper.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Easily incorporate mstore data</strong> into existing backup procedures.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Downloads:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../assets/stored_documents/original/111_ARENA_mstorePURCHASING.pdf" target="_blank">EDRMS in Purchasing (PDF)</a></p>\r\n<h2>Further Information:</h2>\r\n<p><a href="../../../articles/110" target="_blank"><strong></strong>How to spot common purchasing pitfalls</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="../../../page/electronic-document-management">More about <strong>m</strong>store</a></p>\r\n<div id="_mcePaste" class="mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow: hidden;">The purchase-to-pay process is an area in which many organisations are increasingly looking to improve spend control and management of information about costs whilst increasing efficiency. Reducing your back office costs can add considerably to your bottom line and help your business to remain competitive. Streamlining your purchase-to-pay process can play a core part in cost reduction and improved cash flow.</div>', '2011-02-08 09:10:18', '2014-07-11 13:59:31', '', '', 1, 7, 0, NULL, 1, 0),
(53, 'EDM for Human Resources', 'edm_for_human_resources', 'EDM for Human Resources', 58, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<img class="image_left" src="../../..//assets/page_contents/53/contained_images/dcd695e90f2a_43_ArenaEDM.jpg?1297853116" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="100" /><span class="introduction">Copy needed here.</span>', '2011-02-08 09:17:28', '2013-01-18 13:47:07', '', '', 1, 3, 1, '2013-01-18 13:47:07', 1, 0),
(54, 'EDM for Healthcare', 'edm_for_healthcare', 'EDM for Healthcare', 59, 0, 0, 1, '2010-04-29 08:55:42', '<img class="image_left" src="../../..//assets/page_contents/54/contained_images/79e0dc335ed1_43_ArenaEDM.jpg?1297853116" border="0" alt="" hspace="0" vspace="0" width="100" /><span class="introduction">Copy needed here.</span>', '2011-02-08 09:18:14', '2013-01-18 13:47:18', '', '', 1, 3, 1, '2013-01-18 13:47:18', 1, 0),
